(217, 'a&laß', 'from (251)', 'halas', '1:228,36', 'hal\'-as', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «251»; salt; figuratively, prudence:--salt.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>salt with which food is seasoned and sacrifices are sprinkled<LI>those kinds of saline matter used to fertilise arable land<LI>salt is a symbol of lasting concord, because it protects food from putrefaction and preserves it unchanged. Accordingly, in the solemn ratification of compacts, the orientals were, and are to this day, accustomed to partake of salt together<LI>wisdom and grace exhibited in speech</OL>'),
