(267, 'ajmavrturoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a form of (3144)', 'amarturos', 'None', 'am-ar\'-too-ros', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a form of «3144»; unattested:--without witness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>without witness or testimony, unattested</OL>'),
(268, 'aJmartwlovß', 'from (264)', 'hamartolos', '1:317,51', 'ham-ar-to-los\'', 'Adjective', 'from «264»; sinful, i.e. a sinner:--sinful, sinner.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>devoted to sin, a sinner<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>not free from sin<LI>pre-eminently sinful, especially wicked<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>all wicked men<LI>specifically of men stained with certain definite vices or crimes 1b</OL><LI>tax collectors, heathen</OL></OL>'),
(269, 'a[macoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (3163)', 'amachos', '4:527,573', 'am\'-akh-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «3163»; peaceable:--not a brawler.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not to be withstood, invincible<LI>not contentious<LI>abstaining from fighting</OL>'),
(270, 'ajmavw', 'from (260)', 'amao', 'None', 'am-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «260»; properly, to collect, i.e. (by implication) reap:--reap down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to reap, mow down</OL>'),
(271, 'ajmevqustoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (3184)', 'amethustos', 'None', 'am-eth\'-oos-tos', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «3184»; the \"amethyst\" (supposed to prevent intoxication):--amethyst.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>amethyst, a precious stone of a violet and purple colour</OL>'),
(272, 'ajmelevw', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (3199)', 'ameleo', 'None', 'am-el-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «3199»; to be careless of:--make light of, neglect, be negligent, no regard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be careless of, to neglect</OL>'),
(273, 'a[memptoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (3201)', 'amemptos', '4:571,580', 'am\'-emp-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «3201»; irreproachable:--blameless, faultless, unblamable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blameless, deserving no censure, free from fault or defect</OL>'),
(274, 'ajmevmptwß', 'from (273)', 'amemptos', 'None', 'am-emp\'-toce', 'Adverb', 'adverb from «273»; faultlessly:--blameless, unblamably.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>blameless, so that there is no cause for censure</OL>'),
(275, 'ajmevrimnoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (3308)', 'amerimnos', '4:593,584', 'am-er\'-im-nos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «3308»; not anxious:--without care(-fulness), secure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>free from anxiety, free from care</OL>'),
(276, 'ajmetavqetoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (3346)', 'ametathetos', 'None', 'am-et-ath\'-et-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «3346»; unchangeable, or (neuter as abstract) unchangeability:--immutable(-ility).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not transposed, not to be transferred, fixed, unalterable</OL>'),
(277, 'ajmetakivnhtoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (3334)', 'ametakinetos', 'None', 'am-et-ak-in\'-ay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «3334»; immovable:--unmovable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not to be moved from its place, unmoved<LI>metaph. firmly persistent</OL>'),
(278, 'ajmetamevlhtoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of (3338)', 'ametameletos', '4:626,589', 'am-et-am-el\'-ay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of «3338»; irrevocable:--without repentance, not to be repented of.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not repentant of, unregretted</OL>'),
(279, 'ajmetanovhtoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of (3340)', 'ametanoetos', '4:1009,636', 'am-et-an-o\'-ay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of «3340»; unrepentant:--impenitent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>admitting no change of mind, unrepented, impenitent</OL>'),
(280, 'a[metroß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (3358)', 'ametros', '4:632,590', 'am\'-et-ros', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «3358»; immoderate:--(thing) without measure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>without measure, immense</OL>'),
(281, 'ajmhvn', 'of Hebrew origin (0543)', 'amen', '1:335,53', 'am-ane\'', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>firm<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>metaph. faithful</OL><LI>verily, amen<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>at the beginning of a discourse - surely, truly, of a truth<LI>at the end - so it is, so be it, may it be fulfilled. It was a custom, which passed over from the synagogues to the Christian assemblies, that when he who had read or discoursed, had offered up solemn prayer to God, the others responded Amen, and thus made the substance of what was uttered their own.</OL></OL>The word \"amen\" is a most remarkable word. It was transliterateddirectly from the Hebrew into the Greek of the New Testament, theninto Latin and into English and many other languages, so that it ispractically a universal word. It has been called the best known wordin human speech. The word is directly related -- in fact, almostidentical -- to the Hebrew word for \"believe\" (amam), or faithful.Thus, it came to mean \"sure\" or \"truly\", an expression of absolutetrust and confidence. -- HMM', 'of Hebrew origin («0543»); properly, firm, i.e. (figuratively) trustworthy; adverbially, surely (often as interjection, so be it):--amen, verily.', ''),
(282, 'ajmhvtwr', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (3384)', 'ametor', 'None', 'am-ay\'-tore', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «3384»; motherless, i.e. of unknown maternity:--without mother.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>born without a mother<LI>bereft of a mother<LI>born of a base or unknown mother<LI>unmotherly, not worthy of the name of mother</OL>'),
(283, 'ajmivantoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (3392)', 'amiantos', '4:647,593', 'am-ee\'-an-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «3392»; unsoiled, i.e. (figuratively) pure:--undefiled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not defiled, unsoiled<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>free from that by which the nature of a thing is deformed and debased, or its force and vigour impaired</OL></OL>'),
(284, 'ÅAminadavb', 'of Hebrew origin (05992)', 'Aminadab', 'None', 'am-ee-nad-ab\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («05992»); Aminadab, an Israelite:--Aminadab.', 'Amminadab = \"one of the prince\'s people\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an ancestor of Christ</OL>'),
(285, 'a[mmoß', 'perhaps from (260)', 'ammos', 'None', 'am\'-mos', 'Noun Feminine', 'perhaps from «260»; sand (as heaped on the beach):--sand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sand, sandy ground</OL>'),
(286, 'ajmnovß', 'apparently a primary word', 'amnos', '1:338,54', 'am-nos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently a primary word; a lamb:--lamb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a lamb</OL>'),
(287, 'ajmoibhv', 'from ameibo (to exchange)', 'amoibe', 'None', 'am-oy-bay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from ameibo (to exchange); requital:--requite.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>requital, recompence</OL>'),
(288, 'a[mpeloß', 'probably from the base of (297) and that of (257)', 'ampelos', '1:342,54', 'am\'-pel-os', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from the base of «297» and that of «257»; a vine (as coiling about a support):--vine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a vine</OL>'),
(289, 'ajmpelourgovß', 'from (288) and (2041)', 'ampelourgos', 'None', 'am-pel-oor-gos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «288» and «2041»; a vine-worker, i.e. pruner:--vine-dresser.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a vinedresser</OL>'),
(290, 'ajmpelwvn', 'from (288)', 'ampelon', 'None', 'am-pel-ohn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «288»; a vineyard:--vineyard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a vineyard</OL>'),
(291, 'ÅAmplia\'toß', 'contracted for Latin ampliatus [enlarged]', 'Amplias', 'None', 'am-plee\'-as', 'Noun Masculine', 'contracted for Latin ampliatus (enlarged); Amplias, a Roman Christian:--Amplias.', 'Amplias = \"large\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Christian living in Rome</OL>'),
(292, 'ajmuvnw', 'middle voice of a primary verb', 'amunomai', 'None', 'am-oo\'-nom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice of a primary verb; to ward off (for oneself), i.e. protect:--defend.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>defend<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to ward off, keep off<LI>to aid or assist anyone<LI>to defend one\'s self against anyone<LI>to take vengeance on anyone</OL></OL>'),
(293, 'ajmfibavllw', 'from a compound of the base of (297) and (906)', 'amphiblestron', 'None', 'am-fib\'-lace-tron', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a compound of the base of «297» and «906»; a (fishing) net (as thrown about the fish):--net.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anything thrown around one to impede his motions, as chains, a garment, a net for fishing</OL>'),
(294, 'ajmfievnnumi', 'from the base of (297) and hennumi (to invest)', 'amphiennumi', 'None', 'am-fee-en\'-noo-mee', 'Verb', 'from the base of «297» and hennumi (to invest); to enrobe:--clothe.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to put on, to clothe</OL>'),
(295, 'ÅAmfivpoliß', 'from the base of (297) and (4172)', 'Amphipolis', 'None', 'am-fip\'-ol-is', 'Noun Location', 'from the base of «297» and «4172»; a city surrounded by a river; Amphipolis, a place in Macedonia:--Amphipolis.', 'Amphipolis = \"a city surrounded by the sea\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Macedonia Prima, so called because the Strymon flowed around it</OL>'),
(296, 'a[mfodon', 'from the base of (297) and (3598)', 'amphodon', 'None', 'am\'-fod-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'from the base of «297» and «3598»; a fork in the road:--where two ways meet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a road around anything, a street</OL>'),
(297, 'ajmfovteroi', 'comparative of amphi (around)', 'amphoteros', 'None', 'am-fot\'-er-os', 'Adjective', 'comparative of amphi (around); (in plural) both:--both.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>both of two, both the one and the other</OL>'),
(298, 'ajmwvmhtoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (3469)', 'amometos', '4:831,619', 'am-o\'-may-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «3469»; unblamable:--blameless.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that cannot be censured, blameless</OL>'),
(299, 'a[mwmon', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (3470)', 'amomos', '4:830,619', 'am\'-o-mos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «3470»; unblemished (literally or figuratively):--without blame (blemish, fault, spot), faultless, unblamable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>without blemish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as a sacrifice without spot or blemish</OL><LI>morally: without blemish, faultless, unblameable</OL>'),
(300, 'ÅAmwvn', 'of Hebrew origin (0526)', 'Amon', 'None', 'am-one\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («0526»); Amon, an Israelite:--Amon.', 'Amon = \"builder\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a king of Judah, son of Manasseh, and father of Josiah</OL>'),
(301, 'ÅAmwvß', 'of Hebrew origin (0531)', 'Amos', 'None', 'am-oce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («0531»); Amos, an Israelite:--Amos.', 'Amos = \"burden\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an ancestor of Christ</OL>'),
(302, 'a[n', 'a primary particle', 'an', 'None', 'an', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>has no exact English equivalent, see definitions under AV</OL>', 'a primary particle, denoting a supposition, wish, possibility or uncertainty:--(what-, where-, wither-, who-)soever. Usually unexpressed except by the subjunctive or potential mood. Also contracted for «1437».', '');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(303, 'ajnav', 'a primary prep and adv', 'ana', 'None', 'an-ah\'', 'Preposition', 'a primary preposition and adverb; properly, up; but (by extension) used (distributively) severally, or (locally) at (etc.):--and, apiece, by, each, every (man), in, through. In compounds (as a prefix) it often means (by implication) repetition, intensity, reversal, etc.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>into the midst, in the midst, amidst, among, between</OL>'),
(304, 'ajnabaqmovß', 'from (305) [cf (898)]', 'anabathmos', 'None', 'an-ab-ath-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «305» (compare «898»); a stairway:--stairs.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an ascent<LI>a means of going up, a flight of stairs, stairs</OL>'),
(305, 'ajnabaivnw', 'from (303) and the base of (939)', 'anabaino', '1:519,90', 'an-ab-ah\'-ee-no', 'Verb', 'from «303» and the base of «939»; to go up (literally or figuratively):--arise, ascend (up), climb (go, grow, rise, spring) up, come (up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ascend<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to go up<LI>to rise, mount, be borne up, spring up</OL></OL>'),
(306, 'ajnabavllw', 'middle voice from (303) and (906)', 'anaballomai', 'None', 'an-ab-al\'-lom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «303» and «906»; to put off (for oneself):--defer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to throw or toss up<LI>to put back or off, delay, postpone</OL>'),
(307, 'ajnabibavzw', 'from (303) and a derivative of the base of (939)', 'anabibazo', 'None', 'an-ab-ee-bad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «303» and a derivative of the base of «939»; to cause to go up, i.e. haul (a net):--draw.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to go up or ascend, to draw up</OL>'),
(308, 'ajnablevpw', 'from (303) and (991)', 'anablepo', 'None', 'an-ab-lep\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «991»; to look up; by implication, to recover sight:--look (up), see, receive sight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to look up<LI>to recover (lost) sight</OL>'),
(309, 'ajnavbleyiß', 'from (308)', 'anablepsis', 'None', 'an-ab\'-lep-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «308»; restoration of sight:--recovery of sight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>recovery of sight</OL>'),
(310, 'ajnaboavw', 'from (303) and (994)', 'anaboao', 'None', 'an-ab-o-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «994»; to halloo:--cry (aloud, out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to raise a cry, to cry out</OL>'),
(311, 'ajnabolhv', 'from (306)', 'anabole', 'None', 'an-ab-ol-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «306»; a putting off:--delay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>delay, a putting off</OL>'),
(312, 'ajnaggevllw', 'from (303) and the base of (32)', 'anaggello', '1:61,10', 'an-ang-el\'-lo', 'Verb', 'from «303» and the base of «32»; to announce (in detail):--declare, rehearse, report, show, speak, tell.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to announce, make known<LI>to report, bring back tidings, rehearse</OL>'),
(313, 'ajnagennavw', 'from (303) and (1080)', 'anagennao', '1:673,114', 'an-ag-en-nah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «1080»; to beget or (by extension) bear (again):--beget, (bear) × (again).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to produce again, be born again, born anew<LI>metaph. to have one\'s mind changed so that he lives a new life and one conformed to the will of God</OL>'),
(314, 'ajnaginwvskw', 'from (303) and (1097)', 'anaginosko', '1:343,55', 'an-ag-in-oce\'-ko', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «1097»; to know again, i.e. (by extension) to read:--read.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to distinguish between, to recognise, to know accurately, to acknowledge<LI>to read</OL>'),
(315, 'ajnagkavzw', 'from (318)', 'anagkazo', '1:344,55', 'an-ang-kad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «318»; to necessitate:--compel, constrain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to necessitate, compel, drive to, constrain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>by force, threats, etc.<LI>by permission, entreaties, etc.<LI>by other means</OL></OL>'),
(316, 'ajnagkai\'oß', 'from (318)', 'anagkaios', '1:344,55', 'an-ang-kah\'-yos', 'Adjective', 'from «318»; necessary; by implication, close (of kin):--near, necessary, necessity, needful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>necessary<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>what one can not do without, indispensable<LI>connected by bonds of nature or friendship<LI>what ought according to the law of duty be done, what is required by the circumstances</OL></OL>'),
(317, 'ajnagkastw\'ß', 'from a derivative of (315)', 'anagkastos', 'None', 'an-ang-kas-toce\'', 'Adverb', 'adverb from a derivative of «315»; compulsorily:--by constraint.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>by force or constrain</OL>'),
(318, 'ajnavgkh', 'from (303) and the base of (43)', 'anagke', '1:344,55', 'an-ang-kay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «303» and the base of «43»; constraint (literally or figuratively); by implication, distress:--distress, must needs, (of) necessity(-sary), needeth, needful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>necessity, imposed either by the circumstances, or by law of duty regarding to one\'s advantage, custom, argument<LI>calamity, distress, straits</OL>'),
(319, 'ajnagnwrivzw', 'middle voice from (303) and (1107)', 'anagnorizomai', 'None', 'an-ag-no-rid\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «303» and «1107»; to make (oneself) known:--be made known.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to recognise</OL>'),
(320, 'ajnavgnwsiß', 'from (314)', 'angnosis', '1:343,55', 'an-ag\'-no-sis', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>knowing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a knowing again, owning<LI>reading</OL></OL>', 'from «314»; (the act of) reading:--reading.', ''),
(321, 'ajnavgw', 'from (303) and (71)', 'anago', 'None', 'an-ag\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «71»; to lead up; by extension to bring out; specially, to sail away:--bring (again, forth, up again), depart, launch (forth), lead (up), loose, offer, sail, set forth, take up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead up, to lead or bring into a higher place<LI>of navigators: launch out, set sail, put to sea</OL>'),
(322, 'ajnadeivknumi', 'from (303) and (1166)', 'anadeiknumi', '2:30,141', 'an-ad-ike\'-noo-mee', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «1166»; to exhibit, i.e. (by implication) to indicate, appoint:--appoint, shew.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to proclaim any one as elected to office<LI>to announce as appointed a king, general, etc.<LI>to lift up anything on high and exhibit it for all to behold</OL>'),
(323, 'ajnavdeixiß', 'from (322)', 'anadeixis', '2:31,141', 'an-ad\'-ike-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «322»; (the act of) exhibition:--shewing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a pointing out, a public showing forth<LI>a proclaiming, announcing, inaugurating of such as are elected to office</OL>'),
(324, 'ajnadevcomai', 'from (303) and (1209)', 'anadechomai', 'None', 'an-ad-ekh\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «1209»; to entertain (as a guest):--receive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to take up, take upon\'s self, undertake, assume<LI>to receive, entertain anyone hospitably</OL>'),
(325, 'ajnadivdwmi', 'from (303) and (1325)', 'anadidomi', 'None', 'an-ad-eed\'-om-ee', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «1325»; to hand over:--deliver.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give forth, send up, so the earth producing plants, yielding fruit etc.<LI>to deliver up, hand over</OL>'),
(326, 'ajnazavw', 'from (303) and (2198)', 'anazao', '2:872,290', 'an-ad-zah\'-o', 'Verb', 'to recover life (literally or figuratively):--(be a-)live again, revive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>live again, recover life<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be restored to a correct life<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of one who returns to a better moral state</OL><LI>to revive, regain strength and vigour</OL></OL>'),
(327, 'ajnazhtevw', 'from (303) and (2212)', 'anazeteo', 'None', 'an-ad-zay-teh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «2212»; to search out:--seek.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to seek out, search through, make diligent search</OL>'),
(328, 'ajnazwvnnumi', 'from (303) and (2224)', 'anazonnumi', 'None', 'an-ad-zone\'-noo-mee', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «2224»; to gird afresh:--gird up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to gird up<LI>metaph. be prepared<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a metaphor derived from the practice of the Orientals, who in order to be unimpeded in their movements were accustomed, when starting a journey or engaging in any work, to bind their long flowing garments closely around their bodies and fastened them with a leather belt.</OL></OL>'),
(329, 'ajnazwpurevw', 'from (303) and a compound of the base of (2226) and (4442)', 'anazopureo', 'None', 'an-ad-zo-poor-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and a compound of the base of «2226» and «4442»; to re-enkindle:--stir up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to kindle up, inflame one\'s mind, strength, zeal</OL>'),
(330, 'ajnaqavllw', 'from (303) and thallo (to flourish)', 'anathallo', 'None', 'an-ath-al\'-lo', 'Verb', 'from «303» and thallo (to flourish); to revive:--flourish again.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shoot up, sprout again, grow green again, flourish again</OL>'),
(331, 'ajnavqema', 'from (394)', 'anathema', '1:354,57', 'an-ath\'-em-ah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «394»; a (religious) ban or (concretely) excommunicated (thing or person):--accused, anathema, curse, × great.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a thing set up or laid by in order to be kept<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>specifically, an offering resulting from a vow, which after being consecrated to a god was hung upon the walls or columns of the temple, or put in some other conspicuous place</OL><LI>a thing devoted to God without hope of being redeemed, and if an animal, to be slain; therefore a person or thing doomed to destruction<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a curse<LI>a man accursed, devoted to the direst of woes</OL></OL>'),
(332, 'ajnaqemativzw', 'from (331)', 'anathematizo', '1:355,57', 'an-ath-em-at-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «331»; to declare or vow under penalty of execration:--(bind under a) curse, bind with an oath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to devote to destruction<LI>to declare one\'s self liable to the severest divine penalties</OL>'),
(333, 'ajnaqewrevw', 'from (303) and (2334)', 'antheoreo', 'None', 'an-ath-eh-o-reh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «2334»; to look again (i.e. attentively) at (literally or figuratively):--behold, consider.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to look at attentively, to consider well, to observe accurately</OL>'),
(334, 'ajnavqhma', 'from (394) [like (331), but in a good sense]', 'anathema', '1:354,57', 'an-ath\'-ay-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «394» (like «331», but in a good sense); a votive offering:--gift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a gift consecrated and laid up in a temple<LI>an offering resulting from a vow</OL>'),
(335, 'ajnaivdeia', 'from a compound of (1) (as a negative particle [cf (427)]) and (127)', 'anaideia', 'None', 'an-ah\'-ee-die-ah\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a compound of «1» (as a negative particle (compare «427»)) and «127»; impudence, i.e. (by implication) importunity:--importunity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shamelessness, impudence</OL>'),
(336, 'ajnaivresiß', 'from (337)', 'anairesis', 'None', 'an-ah\'-ee-res-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «337»; (the act of) killing:--death.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a destroying, killing, murder</OL>'),
