(402, 'ajnacwrevw', 'from (303) and (5562)', 'anachoreo', 'None', 'an-akh-o-reh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «5562»; to retire:--depart, give place, go (turn) aside, withdraw self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go back, return<LI>to withdraw<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>so as to leave a room<LI>of those who through fear seek some other place, or shun sight</OL></OL>'),
(403, 'ajnavyuxiß', 'from (404)', 'anapsuxis', '9:664,1342', 'an-aps\'-ook-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «404»; properly, a recovery of breath, i.e. (figuratively) revival:--revival.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a cooling, refreshing</OL>'),
(404, 'ajnayuvcw', 'from (303) and (5594)', 'anapsucho', '9:663,1342', 'an-aps-oo\'-kho', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «5594»; properly, to cool off, i.e. (figuratively) relieve:--refresh.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cool again, to cool off, recover from the effects of heat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to refresh (one\'s spirit)</OL><LI>to recover breath, take the air, cool off, revive, refresh one\'s self</OL>'),
(405, 'ajndrapodisthvß', 'from a derivative of a compound of (435) and (4228)', 'andrapodistes', 'None', 'an-drap-od-is-tace\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a derivative of a compound of «435» and «4228»; an enslaver (as bringing men to his feet):--menstealer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a slave-dealer, kidnapper, man-stealer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of one who unjustly reduces free men to slavery<LI>of one who steals the slaves of others and sells them</OL></OL>'),
(406, 'ÅAndrevaß', 'from (435)', 'Andreas', 'None', 'an-dreh\'-as', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «435»; manly; Andreas, an Israelite:--Andrew.', 'Andrew = \"manly\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>A native of Bethsaida in Galilee, brother of Simon Peter, a disciple of John the Baptist, and afterwards an apostle of Christ. He is said to have been crucified at Patrae in Archaia.</OL>'),
(407, 'ajndrivzw', 'middle voice from (435)', 'andrizomai', '1:360,59', 'an-drid\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «435»; to act manly:--quit like men.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make a man of or make brave<LI>to show one\'s self a man, be brave</OL>'),
(408, 'ÅAndrovnikoß', 'from (435) and (3534)', 'Andronikos', 'None', 'an-dron\'-ee-kos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «435» and «3534»; man of victory; Andronicos, an Israelite:--Adronicus.', 'Andronicus = \"man of victory\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Jewish Christian and a kinsman of Paul</OL>'),
(409, 'ajndrofovnoß', 'from (435) and (5408)', 'androphonos', 'None', 'an-drof-on\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «435» and «5408»; a murderer:--manslayer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a murderer</OL>'),
(410, 'ajnevgklhtoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (1458)', 'anegkletos', '1:356,58', 'an-eng\'-klay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «1458»; unaccused, i.e. (by implication) irreproachable:--blameless.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that cannot be called into to account, unreproveable, unaccused, blameless</OL>'),
(411, 'ajnekdihvghtoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of (1555)', 'anekdiegetos', 'None', 'an-ek-dee-ay\'-gay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of «1555»; not expounded in full, i.e. indescribable:--unspeakable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the unspeakable, indescribable</OL>'),
(412, 'ajneklavlhtoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of (1583)', 'aneklaletos', 'None', 'an-ek-lal\'-ay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of «1583»; not spoken out, i.e. (by implication) unutterable:--unspeakable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unspeakable</OL>'),
(413, 'ajnevkleiptoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of (1587)', 'anekleiptos', 'None', 'an-ek\'-lipe-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of «1587»; not left out, i.e. (by implication) inexhaustible:--that faileth not.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unfailing</OL>'),
(414, 'ajnektovteroß', 'comparative of a derivative of (430)', 'anektoteros', '1:359,*', 'an-ek-tot\'-er-os', 'Adjective', 'comparative of a derivative of «430»; more endurable:--more tolerable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bearable, tolerable</OL>'),
(415, 'ajnelehvmwn', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (1655)', 'aneleemon', '2:487,222', 'an-eleh-ay\'-mone', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «1655»; merciless:--unmerciful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>without mercy, merciless</OL>'),
(416, 'ajnemivzw', 'from (417)', 'anemizo', 'None', 'an-em-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «417»; to toss with the wind:--drive with the wind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to agitate or drive by the wind</OL>'),
(417, 'a[nemoß', 'from the base of (109)', 'anemos', 'None', 'an\'-em-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the base of «109»; wind; (plural) by implication, (the four) quarters (of the earth):--wind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wind, a violent agitation and stream of air<LI>a very strong tempestuous wind<LI>the four principal or cardinal winds, hence the four corners of heaven</OL>'),
(418, 'ajnevndektoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of the same as (1735)', 'anendektos', 'None', 'an-en\'-dek-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of the same as «1735»; unadmitted, i.e. (by implication) not supposable:--impossible.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that cannot be admitted, inadmissible, unallowable, improper</OL>'),
(419, 'ajnexerauvnhtoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of (1830)', 'anexereunetos', '1:357,58', 'an-ex-er-yoo\'-nay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of «1830»; not searched out, i.e. (by implication) inscrutable:--unsearchable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that cannot be searched out</OL>'),
(420, 'ajnexivkakoß', 'from (430) and (2556)', 'anexikakos', '3:486,391', 'an-ex-ik\'-ak-os', 'Adjective', 'from «430» and «2556»; enduring of ill, i.e. forbearing:--patient.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>patient of ills and wrongs, forbearing</OL>'),
(421, 'ajnexicnivastoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of (1537) and a derivative of (2487)', 'anexichniastos', '1:358,58', 'an-ex-ikh-nee\'-as-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of «1537» and a derivative of «2487»; not tracked out, i.e. (by implication) untraceable:--past finding out; unsearchable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that cannot be searched out, that cannot be comprehended</OL>'),
(422, 'ajnepaivscuntoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of (1909) and (153)', 'anepaischuntos', 'None', 'an-ep-ah\'-ee-skhoon-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a compound of «1909» and «153»; not ashamed, i.e. irreprehensible: --that needeth not to be ashamed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>having no cause to be ashamed</OL>'),
(423, 'ajnepivlhmptoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (1949)', 'anepileptos', '4:9,495', 'an-ep-eel\'-ape-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «1949»; not arrested, i.e. (by implication) inculpable:--blameless, unrebukeable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not apprehended, that cannot be laid hold of<LI>that cannot be reprehended, not open to censure, irreproachable</OL>'),
(424, 'ajnevrcomai', 'from (303) and (2064)', 'anerchomai', 'None', 'an-erkh\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «2064»; to ascend:--go up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go up<LI>to go up to a higher place: to Jerusalem</OL>'),
(425, 'a[nesiß', 'from (447)', 'anesis', '1:367,60', 'an\'-es-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «447»; relaxation or (figuratively) relief:--eased, liberty, rest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a loosening, relaxing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>spoken of a more tolerable condition in captivity, to be held in less vigorous confinement<LI>relief, rest, from persecutions</OL></OL>'),
(426, 'ajnetavzw', 'from (303) and etazo (to test)', 'anetazo', 'None', 'an-et-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «303» and etazo (to test); to investigate (judicially):--(should have) examined(-d).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to investigate, to examine<LI>to examine judicially</OL>'),
(427, 'a[neu', 'a primary particle', 'aneu', 'None', 'an\'-yoo', 'Preposition', 'a primary particle; without:--without. Compare «1».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>without one\'s will or intervention</OL>'),
(428, 'ajneuvqetoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (2111)', 'aneuthetos', 'None', 'an-yoo\'-the-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «2111»; not well set, i.e. inconvenient:--not commodious.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not convenient, not commodious, not fit</OL>'),
(429, 'ajneurivskw', 'from (303) and (2147)', 'aneurisko', 'None', 'an-yoo-ris\'-ko', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «2147»; to find out:--find.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to find out by search</OL>'),
(430, 'ajnevcw', 'middle voice from (303) and (2192)', 'anechomai', '1:359,*', 'an-ekh\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «303» and «2192»; to hold oneself up against, i.e. (figuratively) put up with:--bear with, endure, forbear, suffer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hold up<LI>to hold one\'s self erect and firm<LI>to sustain, to bear, to endure</OL>'),
(431, 'ajneyiovß', 'from (1) (as a particle of union) and an obsolete nepos (a brood)', 'anepsios', 'None', 'an-eps\'-ee-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «1» (as a particle of union) and an obsolete nepos (a brood); properly, akin, i.e. (specially) a cousin:--sister\'s son.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a cousin</OL>'),
(432, 'a[nhqon', 'probably of foreign origin', 'anethon', 'None', 'an\'-ay-thon', 'Noun Neuter', 'probably of foreign origin; dill:--anise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anise, dill<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a used plant used as a spice and for medicine</OL></OL>'),
(433, 'ajnhvkw', 'from (303) and (2240)', 'aneko', '1:360,*', 'an-ay\'-ko', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «2240»; to attain to, i.e. (figuratively) be proper:--convenient, be fit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to have come up to, arrived at, to reach to<LI>to pertain to what is due, duty, as was fitting</OL>'),
(434, 'ajnhvmeroß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and hemeros (lame)', 'anemeros', 'None', 'an-ay\'-mer-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and hemeros (lame); savage:--fierce.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not tame, savage, fierce</OL>'),
(435, 'ajnhvr', 'a primary word cf (444)', 'aner', '1:360,59', 'an\'-ayr', 'Noun Masculine', 'a primary word (compare «444»); a man (properly as an individual male):--fellow, husband, man, sir.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>with reference to sex<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a male<LI>of a husband<LI>of a betrothed or future husband</OL><LI>with reference to age, and to distinguish an adult man from a boy<LI>any male<LI>used generically of a group of both men and women</OL>'),
(436, 'ajnqivsthmi', 'from (473) and (2476)', 'anthistemi', 'None', 'anth-is\'-tay-mee', 'Verb', 'from «473» and «2476»; to stand against, i.e. oppose:--resist, withstand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to set one\'s self against, to withstand, resist, oppose<LI>to set against</OL>'),
(437, 'ajnqomologevomai', 'from (473) and the middle voice of (3670)', 'anthomologeomai', '5:199,687', 'anth-om-ol-og-eh\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «473» and the middle voice of «3670»; to confess in turn, i.e. respond in praise:--give thanks.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to reply by professing or by confessing<LI>to agree mutually (in turn), to make a compact<LI>to acknowledge in the presence of<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to give thanks</OL></OL>'),
(438, 'a[nqoß', 'a primary word', 'anthos', 'None', 'anth\'-os', 'Noun Neuter', 'a primary word; a blossom:--flower.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a flower</OL>'),
(439, 'ajnqrakiav', 'from (440)', 'anthrakia', 'None', 'anth-rak-ee-ah\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «440»; a bed of burning coals:--fire of coals.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a heap of burning coals</OL>'),
(440, 'a[nqrax', 'of uncertain derivation', 'anthrax', 'None', 'anth\'-rax', 'Adjective', 'of uncertain derivation; a live coal:--coal of fire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a burning or live coal</OL>'),
(441, 'ajnqrwpavreskoß', 'from (444) and (700)', 'anthropareskos', '1:465,77', 'anth-ro-par\'-es-kos', 'Adjective', 'from «444» and «700»; man-courting, i.e. fawning:--men-pleaser.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>studying to please man, courting the favour of men</OL>'),
(442, 'ajnqrwvpinoß', 'from (444)', 'anthropinos', '1:366,59', 'anth-ro\'-pee-nos', 'Adjective', 'from «444»; human:--human, common to man, man(-kind), (man-)kind, men\'s, after the manner of men.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>human<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>applied to things belonging to men</OL></OL>'),
(443, 'ajnqrwpoktovnoß', 'from (444) and kteine (to kill)', 'anthropoktonos', 'None', 'anth-ro-pok-ton\'-os', 'Adjective', 'from «444» and kteino (to kill); a manslayer:--murderer. Compare «5406».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a manslayer, murderer</OL>'),
(444, 'a[nqrwpoß', 'from (435) and ops (the countenance, from (3700)); man-faced, i.e. a human being', 'anthropos', '1:364,59', 'anth\'-ro-pos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «435» and ops (the countenance; from «3700»); man-faced, i.e. a human being:--certain, man.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a human being, whether male or female<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>generically, to include all human individuals<LI>to distinguish man from beings of a different order<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of animals and plants<LI>of from God and Christ<LI>of the angels</OL><LI>with the added notion of weakness, by which man is led into a mistake or prompted to sin<LI>with the adjunct notion of contempt or disdainful pity<LI>with reference to two fold nature of man, body and soul<LI>with reference to the two fold nature of man, the corrupt and the truly Christian man, conformed to the nature of God<LI>with reference to sex, a male</OL><LI>indefinitely, someone, a man, one<LI>in the plural, people<LI>joined with other words, merchantman</OL>'),
(445, 'ajnqupateuvw', 'from (446)', 'anthupateuo', 'None', 'anth-oo-pat-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «446»; to act as proconsul:--be the deputy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be a proconsul</OL>'),
(446, 'ajnquvpatoß', 'from (473) and a superlative of (5228)', 'anthupatos', 'None', 'anth-oo\'-pat-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «473» and a superlative of «5228»; instead of the highest officer, i.e. (specially) a Roman proconsul:--deputy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a proconsul<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the emperor Augustus divided the Roman provinces into senatorial and imperial. The former were governed by proconsuls; the later by legates of the emperor, sometimes called propraetors</OL></OL>'),
(447, 'ajnivhmi', 'from (303) and hiemi (to send)', 'aniemi', '1:367,60', 'an-ee\'-ay-mee', 'Verb', 'from «303» and hiemi (to send); to let up, i.e. (literally) slacken or (figuratively) desert, desist from:--forbear, leave, loose.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to send back, relax, loosen<LI>to give up, omit, calm<LI>to leave, not to uphold, to let sink</OL>'),
(448, 'ajnivlewß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (2436)', 'anileos', '2:487,*', 'an-ee\'-leh-oce', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «2436»; inexorable:--without mercy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>without mercy, merciless</OL>'),
(449, 'a[niptoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of (3538)', 'aniptos', '4:947,635', 'an\'-ip-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of «3538»; without ablution:--unwashen.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unwashed</OL>'),
(450, 'ajnivsthmi', 'from (303) and (2476)', 'anistemi', '1:368,60', 'an-is\'-tay-mee', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «2476»; to stand up (literal or figurative, transitive or intransitive):--arise, lift up, raise up (again), rise (again), stand up(-right).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to rise up, raise up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>raise up from laying down<LI>to raise up from the dead<LI>to raise up, cause to be born, to cause to appear, bring forward</OL><LI>to rise, stand up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of persons lying down, of persons lying on the ground<LI>of persons seated<LI>of those who leave a place to go elsewhere<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of those who prepare themselves for a journey</OL><LI>of the dead</OL><LI>at arise, appear, stand forth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of kings prophets, priests, leaders of insurgents<LI>of those about to enter into conversation or dispute with anyone, or to undertake some business, or attempt something against others<LI>to rise up against any one</OL></OL>'),
(451, 'áAnna', 'of Hebrew origin (02584)', 'Anna', 'None', 'an\'-nah', 'Noun Feminine', 'of Hebrew origin («02584»); Anna, an Israelitess:--Anna.', 'Anna = \"grace\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>A prophetess in Jerusalem at the time of the Lord\'s presentation in the Temple. She was of the tribe of Asher.</OL>'),
(452, 'áAnnaß', 'of Hebrew origin (02608)', 'Annas', 'None', 'an\'-nas', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («02608»); Annas (i.e. «367»), an Israelite:--Annas.', 'Annas = \"humble\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>high priest of the Jews, elevated to the priesthood by Quirinius the governor of Syria c. 6 or 7 A.D., but afterwards deposed by Valerius Gratus, the procurator of Judaea, who put in his place, first Ismael, son of Phabi, and shortly after Eleazar, son of Annas. From the latter, the office passed to Simon; from Simon c. 18 A.D. to Caiaphas; but Annas even after he had been put out of office, continued to have great influence.</OL>'),
(453, 'ajnovhtoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (3539)', 'anoetos', '4:961,636', 'an-o\'-ay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «3539»; unintelligent; by implication, sensual:--fool(-ish), unwise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not understood, unintelligible<LI>not understanding, unwise, foolish</OL>'),
(454, 'a[noia', 'from a compound of (1) (as a negative particle) and (3563)', 'anoia', '4:962,636', 'an\'-oy-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a compound of «1» (as a negative particle) and «3563»; stupidity; by implication, rage:--folly, madness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>want of understanding, folly<LI>madness expressing itself in rage</OL>'),
(455, 'ajnoivgw', 'from (303) and oigo (to open)', 'anoigo', 'None', 'an-oy\'-go', 'Verb', 'from «303» and oigo (to open); to open up (literally or figuratively, in various applications):--open.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to open</OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(456, 'ajnoikodomevw', 'from (303) and (3618)', 'anoikodomeo', 'None', 'an-oy-kod-om-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and «3618»; to rebuild:--build again.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to build again</OL>'),
(457, 'a[noixiß', 'from (455)', 'anoixis', 'None', 'an\'-oix-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «455»; opening (throat):--X open.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an opening</OL>'),
(458, 'ajnomiva', 'from (459)', 'anomia', '4:1085,646', 'an-om-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «459»; illegality, i.e. violation of law or (genitive case) wickedness:--iniquity, × transgress(-ion of) the law, unrighteousness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the condition of without law<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>because ignorant of it<LI>because of violating it</OL><LI>contempt and violation of law, iniquity, wickedness</OL>'),
(459, 'a[nomoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (3551)', 'anomos', '4:1086,646', 'an\'-om-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «3551»; lawless, i.e. (negatively) not subject to (the Jewish) law; (by implication, a Gentile), or (positively) wicked:--without law, lawless, transgressor, unlawful, wicked.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>destitute of (the Mosaic) law<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the Gentiles</OL><LI>departing from the law, a violator of the law, lawless, wicked</OL>'),
(460, 'ajnovmwß', 'from (459)', 'anomos', 'None', 'an-om\'-oce', 'Adverb', 'adverb from «459»; lawlessly, i.e. (specially) not amenable to (the Jewish) law:--without law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>without the law, without the knowledge of the law<LI>to sin in ignorance of the Mosaic law<LI>live ignorant of law and discipline</OL>'),
(461, 'ajnorqovw', 'from (303) and a derivative of the base of (3717)', 'anorthoo', 'None', 'an-orth-o\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «303» and a derivative of the base of «3717»; to straighten up:--lift (set) up, make straight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to set up, make erect<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a deformed person</OL><LI>to rear again, build anew</OL>'),
(462, 'ajnovsioß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (3741)', 'anosios', '5:492,734', 'an-os\'-ee-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «3741»; wicked:--unholy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unholy, impious, wicked</OL>'),
(463, 'ajnochv', 'from (430)', 'anoche', '1:359,58', 'an-okh-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «430»; self-restraint, i.e. tolerance:--forbearance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>toleration, forbearance</OL>'),
(464, 'ajntagwnivzomai', 'from (473) and (75)', 'antagonizomai', '1:134,20', 'an-tag-o-nid\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «473» and «75»; to struggle against (figuratively) (\"antagonize\"):--strive against.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to struggle, fight</OL>'),
(465, 'ajntavllagma', 'from a compound of (473) and (236)', 'antallagma', '1:252,40', 'an-tal\'-ag-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a compound of «473» and «236»; an equivalent or ransom:--in exchange.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that which is given in place of another thing by way of exchange<LI>what is given either in order to keep or to acquire anything</OL>'),
(466, 'ajntanaplhrovw', 'from (473) and (378)', 'antanapleroo', '6:307,867', 'an-tan-ap-lay-ro\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «473» and «378»; to supplement:--fill up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fill up in turn<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in Col 1:24, the meaning is, \'what is wanting in the afflictions of Christ to be borne by me, that I supply in order to repay the benefits which Christ conferred on me by filling up the measure of the afflictions laid upon me\'.</OL></OL>'),
(467, 'ajntapodivdwmi', 'from (473) and (591)', 'antapodidomi', '2:169,166', 'an-tap-od-ee\'-do-mee', 'Verb', 'from «473» and «591»; to requite (good or evil):--recompense, render, repay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in a good sense, to repay, requite<LI>in a bad sense, penalty and vengeance</OL>'),
(468, 'ajntapovdoma', 'from (467)', 'antapodoma', '2:169,166', 'an-tap-od\'-om-ah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «467»; a requital (properly, the thing):--recompense.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the thing paid back, requital</OL>'),
(469, 'ajntapovdosiß', 'from (467)', 'antapodosis', '2:169,166', 'an-tap-od\'-os-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «467»; requital (properly, the act):--reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>recompence, to reward or repay someone</OL>'),
