(480, 'ajntivkeimai', 'from (473) and (2749)', 'antikeimai', '3:655,425', 'an-tik\'-i-mahee', 'Verb', 'from «473» and «2749»; to lie opposite, i.e. be adverse (figuratively, repugnant) to:--adversary, be contrary, oppose.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be set over against, opposite to<LI>to oppose, be adverse to, withstand</OL>'),
