(482, 'ajntilambavnw', 'from (473) and the middle voice of (2983)', 'antilambanomai', '1:375,62', 'an-tee-lam-ban\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «473» and the middle voice of «2983»; to take hold of in turn, i.e. succor; also to participate:--help, partaker, support.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lay hold of, hold fast to anything<LI>to take a person or thing in order as it were to be held, to take to, embrace<LI>to help, to be a partaker of, partake of (the benefits of the services rendered by the slaves)</OL>'),
