(501, 'ajntlevw', 'from antlos (the hold of a ship)', 'antleo', 'None', 'ant-leh-o', 'Verb', 'from antlos (the hold of a ship); to bale up (properly, bilge water), i.e. dip water (with a bucket, pitcher, etc.):--draw (out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw out of a ship\'s bilge-water, to bale or pump out<LI>to draw water</OL>'),
