(524, 'ajpalgevw', 'from (575) and algeo (to smart)', 'apalgeo', 'None', 'ap-alg-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «575» and algeo (to smart); to grieve out, i.e. become apathetic:--be past feeling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cease to feel pain or grief<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to bear troubles with greater equanimity, cease to feel pain at<LI>to become callous, insensible to pain, apathetic</OL></OL>'),
