(735, 'àArtemiß', 'probably from the same as (736)', 'Artemis', 'None', 'ar\'-tem-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from the same as «736»; prompt; Artemis, the name of a Grecian goddess borrowed by the Asiatics for one of their deities:--Diana.', 'Diana = \"complete light: flow restrained\"'),
(736, 'ajrtevmwn', 'from a derivative of (737)', 'artemon', 'None', 'ar-tem\'-ohn', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a derivative of «737»; properly, something ready (or else more remotely from «142» (compare «740»); something hung up), i.e. (specially) the topsail (rather foresail or jib) of a vessel:--mainsail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a top-sail or foresail of a ship</OL>'),
(737, 'a[rti', 'from a derivative of (142) (cf (740)) through the idea of suspension', 'arti', '4:1106,658', 'ar\'-tee', 'Adverb', 'adverb from a derivative of «142» (compare «740») through the idea of suspension; just now:--this day (hour), hence(-forth), here(-after), hither(-to), (even) now, (this) present.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>just now, this moment<LI>now at this time, at this very time, this moment</OL>'),
(738, 'ajrtigevnnhtoß', 'from (737) and (1084)', 'artigennetos', '1:672,114', 'ar-teeg-en\'-nay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «737» and «1084»; just born, i.e. (figuratively) a young convert:--new born.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>just born, newborn</OL>'),
(739, 'a[rtioß', 'from (737)', 'artios', '1:475,80', 'ar\'-tee-os', 'Adjective', 'from «737»; fresh, i.e. (by implication) complete:--perfect.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fitted<LI>complete, perfect<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>having reference apparently to \"special aptitude for given uses\"</OL></OL>'),
(740, 'a[rtoß', 'from (142)', 'artos', '1:477,80', 'ar\'-tos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «142»; bread (as raised) or a loaf:--(shew-)bread, loaf.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>food composed of flour mixed with water and baked<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the Israelites made it in the form of an oblong or round cake, as thick as one\'s thumb, and as large as a plate or platter hence it was not to be cut but broken<LI>loaves were consecrated to the Lord<LI>of the bread used at the love-feasts and at the Lord\'s Table</OL><LI>food of any kind</OL>'),
(741, 'ajrtuvw', 'from a presumed derivative of (142)', 'artuo', 'None', 'ar-too\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a presumed derivative of «142»; to prepare, i.e. spice (with stimulating condiments):--season.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prepare, arrange, with respect to food<LI>to season, make savory</OL>'),
(742, 'ÅArfaxavd', 'of Hebrew origin (0775)', 'Arphaxad', 'None', 'ar-fax-ad\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («0775»); Arphaxad, a post-diluvian patriarch:--Arphaxad.', 'Arphaxad = \"stronghold of Chaldees\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Shem and ancestor of Eber</OL>'),
(743, 'ajrcavggeloß', 'from (757) and (32)', 'archaggelos', '1:87,12', 'ar-khang\'-el-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «757» and «32»; a chief angel:--archangel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>archangel, or chief of the angels</OL>'),
(744, 'ajrcai\'oß', 'from (746)', 'archaios', '1:486,81', 'ar-khah\'-yos', 'Adjective', 'from «746»; original or primeval:--(them of) old (time).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that has been from the beginning, original, primal, old ancient<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of men, things, times, conditions</OL></OL>'),
(745, 'ÅArcevlaoß', 'from (757) and (2994)', 'Archelaos', 'None', 'ar-khel\'-ah-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «757» and «2994»; people-ruling; Archelaus, a Jewish king:--Archelaus.', 'Archelaus = \"prince of the people\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>A son of Herod the Great by Malthace, the Samaritan woman. He and his brother Antipas were brought up with a certain private man in Rome. After the death of his father, he ruled as ethnarch over Judaea, Samaria and Idumaea, (with the exception of the cities of Gaza, Gadara and Hipo). The Jews and the Samaritans having accused him at Rome of tyranny, he was banished by the emperor Augustus to Vienna of the Allobroges and died there.</OL>'),
(746, 'ajrchv', 'from (756)', 'arche', '1:479,81', 'ar-khay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «756»; (properly abstract) a commencement, or (concretely) chief (in various applications of order, time, place, or rank):--beginning, corner, (at the, the) first (estate), magistrate, power, principality, principle, rule.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beginning, origin<LI>the person or thing that commences, the first person or thing in a series, the leader<LI>that by which anything begins to be, the origin, the active cause<LI>the extremity of a thing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the corners of a sail</OL><LI>the first place, principality, rule, magistracy<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of angels and demons</OL></OL>'),
(747, 'ajrchgovß', 'from (746) and (71)', 'archegos', '1:487,81', 'ar-khay-gos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «746» and «71»; a chief leader:--author, captain, prince.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the chief leader, prince<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of Christ</OL><LI>one that takes the lead in any thing and thus affords an example, a predecessor in a matter, pioneer<LI>the author</OL>'),
(748, 'ajrcieratikovß', 'from (746) and a derivative of (2413)', 'archieratikos', 'None', 'ar-khee-er-at-ee-kos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «746» and a derivative of «2413»; high-priestly:--of the high-priest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>high priestly, pontifical</OL>'),
(749, 'ajrciereuvß', 'from (746) and (2409)', 'archiereus', '3:265,349', 'ar-khee-er-yuce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «746» and «2409»; the high-priest (literally, of the Jews, typically, Christ); by extension a chief priest:--chief (high) priest, chief of the priests.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chief priest, high priest</OL>'),
(750, 'ajrcipoivmhn', 'from (746) and (4166)', 'archipoimen', '6:485,901', 'ar-khee-poy\'-mane', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «746» and «4166»; a head shepherd:--chief shepherd.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chief shepherd<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of Christ the head of the church</OL></OL>'),
(751, 'àArcippoß', 'from (746) and (2462)', 'Archippos', 'None', 'ar\'-khip-pos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «746» and «2462»; horse-ruler; Archippus, a Christian:--Archippus.', 'Archippus = \"master of the horse\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a certain Christian teacher in Colosse</OL>'),
(752, 'ajrcisunavgwgoß', 'from (746) and (4864)', 'archisunagogos', '6:844,1107', 'ar-khee-soon-ag\'-o-gos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «746» and «4864»; director of the synagogue services:--(chief) ruler of the synagogue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ruler of the synagogue. It was his duty to select the readers or teachers in the synagogue, to examine the discourses of the public speakers, and to see that all things were done with decency and in accordance with ancestral usage.</OL>'),
(753, 'ajrcitevktwn', 'from (746) and (5045)', 'architekton', 'None', 'ar-khee-tek\'-tone', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «746» and «5045»; a chief constructor, i.e. \"architect\":--masterbuilder.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a master builder, an architect, the superintendent in the erection of buildings</OL>'),
(754, 'ajrcitelwvnhß', 'from (746) and (5057)', 'architelones', 'None', 'ar-khee-tel-o\'-nace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «746» and «5057»; a principle tax-gatherer:--chief among the publicans.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chief of tax collectors, chief publican</OL>'),
(755, 'ajrcitrivklinoß', 'from (746) and a compound of (5140) and (2827) (a dinner-bed, because composed of three couches)', 'architriklinos', 'None', 'ar-khee-tree\'-klee-nos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «746» and a compound of «5140» and «2827» (a dinner-bed, because composed of three couches); director of the entertainment:--governor (ruler) of the feast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the superintendent of the dining room, a table master.</OL>'),
(756, 'a[rcomai', 'middle voice of (757) (through the implication of precedence)', 'archomai', '1:478,*', 'ar\'-khom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice of «757» (through the implication, of precedence); to commence (in order of time):--(rehearse from the) begin(-ning).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be the first to do (anything), to begin<LI>to be chief, leader, ruler<LI>to begin, make a beginning</OL>'),
(757, 'a[rcw', 'a primary word', 'archo', '1:478,81', 'ar\'-kho', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to be first (in political rank or power):--reign (rule) over.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be chief, to lead, to rule</OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(758, 'a[rcwn', 'present participle of (757)', 'archon', '1:488,81', 'ar\'-khone', 'Noun Masculine', 'present participle of «757»; a first (in rank or power):--chief (ruler), magistrate, prince, ruler.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a ruler, commander, chief, leader</OL>'),
(759, 'a[rwma', 'from (142) (in the sense of sending off scent)', 'aroma', 'None', 'ar\'-o-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «142» (in the sense of sending off scent); an aromatic:--(sweet) spice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spice, perfume</OL>'),
(760, 'ÅAsavf', 'of Hebrew origin (0609)', 'Asa', 'None', 'as-ah\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («0609»); Asa, an Israelite:--Asa.', 'Asa = \"physician, or cure\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>son of Abijah and king of Judah</OL>'),
(761, 'ajsavleutoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (4531)', 'asaleutos', 'None', 'as-al\'-yoo-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «4531»; unshaken, i.e. (by implication) immovable (figuratively):--which cannot be moved, unmovable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unshaken, unmoved<LI>metaph. not liable to overthrow and disorder, firm stable</OL>'),
(762, 'a[sbestoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (4570)', 'asbestos', 'None', 'as\'-bes-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «4570»; not extinguished, i.e. (by implication) perpetual:--not to be quenched, unquenchable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unquenched, unquenchable<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of eternal hell fire to punish the damned</OL></OL>'),
(763, 'ajsevbeia', 'from (765)', 'asebeia', '7:185,1010', 'as-eb\'-i-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «765»; impiety, i.e. (by implication) wickedness:--ungodly(-liness).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>want of reverence towards God, impiety, ungodliness</OL>'),
(764, 'ajsebevw', 'from (765)', 'asebeo', '7:185,1010', 'as-eb-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «765»; to be (by implied act) impious or wicked:--commit (live, that after should live) ungodly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be ungodly, act impiously</OL>'),
(765, 'ajsebhvß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of (4576)', 'asebes', '7:185,1010', 'as-eb-ace\'', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of «4576»; irreverent, i.e. (by extension) impious or wicked:-- ungodly (man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>destitute of reverential awe towards God, condemning God, impious</OL>'),
(766, 'ajsevlgeia', 'from a compound of (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed selges (of uncertain derivation, but apparently meaning continent)', 'aselgeia', '1:490,83', 'as-elg\'-i-a', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a compound of «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed selges (of uncertain derivation, but apparently meaning continent); licentiousness (sometimes including other vices):--filthy, lasciviousness, wantonness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unbridled lust, excess, licentiousness, lasciviousness, wantonness, outrageousness, shamelessness, insolence</OL>'),
(767, 'a[shmoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and the base of (4591)', 'asemos', '7:267,1015', 'as\'-ay-mos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and the base of «4591»; unmarked, i.e. (figuratively) ignoble:--mean.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unmarked or unstamped<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of money</OL><LI>unknown, of no mark, insignificant, ignoble</OL>'),
(768, 'ÅAshvr', 'of Hebrew origin (0836)', 'Aser', 'None', 'as-ayr\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («0836»); Aser (i.e. Asher), an Israelite tribe:--Aser.', 'Asher = \"blessed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eighth son of Jacob</OL>'),
(769, 'ajsqevneia', 'from (772)', 'astheneia', '1:490,83', 'as-then\'-i-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «772»; feebleness (of mind or body); by implication, malady; morally, frailty:--disease, infirmity, sickness, weakness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>want of strength, weakness, infirmity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the body<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>its native weakness and frailty<LI>feebleness of health or sickness</OL><LI>of the soul<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>want of strength and capacity requisite 1b</OL><LI>to understand a thing 1b<LI>to do things great and glorious 1b<LI>to restrain corrupt desires 1b<LI>to bear trials and troubles</OL></OL>'),
(770, 'ajsqenevw', 'from (772)', 'astheneo', '1:490,83', 'as-then-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «772»; to be feeble (in any sense):--be diseased, impotent folk (man), (be) sick, (be, be made) weak.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be weak, feeble, to be without strength, powerless<LI>to be weak in means, needy, poor<LI>to be feeble, sick</OL>'),
(771, 'ajsqevnhma', 'from (770)', 'asthenema', '1:490,83', 'as-then\'-ay-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «770»; a scruple of conscience:--infirmity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>infirmity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of error arising from weakness of mind</OL></OL>'),
(772, 'ajsqenhvß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and the base of (4599)', 'asthenes', '1:490,83', 'as-then-ace\'', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and the base of «4599»; strengthless (in various applications, literal, figurative and moral):--more feeble, impotent, sick, without strength, weak(-er, -ness, thing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weak, infirm, feeble</OL>'),
(773, 'ÅAsiva', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Asia', 'None', 'as-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Asia, i.e. Asia Minor, or (usually) only its western shore:--Asia.', 'Asia = \"orient\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Asia proper or proconsular Asia embracing Mysia, Lydia, Phrygia, and Caria, corresponding closely to Turkey today</OL>'),
(774, 'ÅAsianovß', 'from (773)', 'Asianos', 'None', 'as-ee-an-os\'', 'Adjective', 'from «773»; an Asian (i.e. Asiatic) or an inhabitant of Asia:--of Asia.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a native of Asia, Asian, Asiatic</OL>'),
(775, 'ÅAsiavrchß', 'from (773) and (746)', 'Asiarches', 'None', 'as-ee-ar\'-khace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «773» and «746»; an Asiarch or president of the public festivities in a city of Asia Minor:--chief of Asia.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Asiarch, President of Asia.</OL>'),
(776, 'ajsitiva', 'from (777)', 'asitia', 'None', 'as-ee-tee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «777»; fasting (the state):--abstinence.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>abstinence from food (whether voluntary or enforced)</OL>'),
(777, 'a[sitoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (4621)', 'asitos', 'None', 'as\'-ee-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «4621»; without (taking) food:--fasting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fasting, without having eaten</OL>'),
(778, 'ajskevw', 'probably from the same as (4632)', 'askeo', '1:494,84', 'as-keh\'-o', 'Verb', 'probably from the same as «4632»; to elaborate, i.e. (figuratively) train (by implication, strive):--exercise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to form by art, to adorn<LI>to exercise (one\'s) self, take pains, labour, strive</OL>'),
(779, 'ajskovß', 'from the same as (778)', 'askos', 'None', 'as-kos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «778»; a leathern (or skin) bag used as a bottle:--bottle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a leathern bag or bottle, in which water or wine was kept</OL>'),
(780, 'ajsmevnwß', 'from a derivative of the base of (2237)', 'asmenos', 'None', 'as-men\'-oce', 'Adverb', 'adverb from a derivative of the base of «2237»; with pleasure:--gladly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>with joy, gladness</OL>'),
(781, 'a[sofoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (4680)', 'asophos', 'None', 'as\'-of-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «4680»; unwise:--fool.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unwise, foolish</OL>'),
(782, 'ajspavzomai', 'from (1) (as a particle of union) and a presumed form of (4685)', 'aspazomai', '1:496,84', 'as-pad\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «1» (as a particle of union) and a presumed form of «4685»; to enfold in the arms, i.e. (by implication) to salute, (figuratively) to welcome:--embrace, greet, salute, take leave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw to one\'s self<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to salute one, greet, bid welcome, wish well to<LI>to receive joyfully, welcome</OL></OL>'),
(783, 'ajspasmovß', 'from (782)', 'aspasmos', '1:496,84', 'as-pas-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «782»; a greeting (in person or by letter):--greeting, salutation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a salutation, either oral or written</OL>'),
(784, 'a[spiloß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (4695)', 'aspilos', '1:502,85', 'as\'-pee-los', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «4695»; unblemished (physically or morally):--without spot, unspotted.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>spotless<LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>free from censure, irreproachable<LI>free from vice, unsullied</OL></OL>'),
(785, 'ajspivß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'aspis', 'None', 'as-pece\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; a buckler (or round shield); used of a serpent (as coiling itself), probably the \"asp\":--asp.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an asp, a small and most venomous serpent, the bite of which is fatal unless the bitten part be immediately cut away</OL>'),
(786, 'a[spondoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (4689)', 'aspondos', 'None', 'as\'-pon-dos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «4689»; literally, without libation (which usually accompanied a treaty), i.e. (by implication) truceless:--implacable, truce-breaker.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>without a treaty or covenant<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of things not mutually agreed upon e.g. abstinences from hostilities</OL><LI>that cannot be persuaded to enter into a covenant, implacable</OL>'),
(787, 'ajssavrion', 'of Latin origin', 'assarion', 'None', 'as-sar\'-ee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'of Latin origin; an assarius or as, a Roman coin:--farthing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an assarium or assarius, the name of a coin equal to the tenth part of a drachma</OL>'),
(788, 'a\\sson', 'neuter comparative of the base of (1451)', 'asson', 'None', 'as\'-son', 'Adverb', 'neuter comparative of the base of «1451»; more nearly, i.e. very near:--close.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nearer</OL>'),
(789, 'àAssoß', 'probably of foreign origin', 'Assos', 'None', 'as\'-sos', 'Noun Location', 'probably of foreign origin; Assus, a city of Asia MInor:--Assos.', 'Assos = \"approaching\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a seaport of the Roman province of Asia in the district anciently called Mysia, on the north shore of the Gulf of Adramyttium, and about 7 miles (11 km) from Lesbos</OL>'),
(790, 'ajstatevw', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (2476)', 'astateo', '1:503,86', 'as-tat-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «2476»; to be non-stationary, i.e. (figuratively) homeless:--have no certain dwelling-place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wander about, to rove without a settled abode</OL>'),
(791, 'ajstei\'oß', 'from astu (a city)', 'asteios', 'None', 'as-ti\'-os', 'Adjective', 'from astu (a city); urbane, i.e. (by implication) handsome:--fair.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of the city<LI>of polished manners<LI>elegant (of body), comely, fair</OL>'),
(792, 'ajsthvr', 'probably from the base of (4766)', 'aster', '1:503,86', 'as-tare\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from the base of «4766»; a star (as strown over the sky), literally or figuratively:--star.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a star</OL>'),
(793, 'ajsthvriktoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of (4741)', 'asteriktos', '7:653,1085', 'as-tay\'-rik-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of «4741»; unfixed, i.e. (figuratively) vacillating:--unstable.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unstable, unsteadfast</OL>'),
(794, 'a[storgoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of stergo (to cherish affectionately)', 'astorgos', 'None', 'as\'-tor-gos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of stergo (to cherish affectionately); hard-hearted towards kindred:--without natural affection.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>without natural affection, unsociable (Rom 1:31 marg.), inhuman (2Ti. 3:3 RSV), unloving (2Ti. 3:3 NKJV)</OL>'),
(795, 'ajstocevw', 'from a compound of (1) (as a negative particle) and stoichos (an aim)', 'astocheo', 'None', 'as-tokh-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a compound of «1» (as a negative particle) and stoichos (an aim); to miss the mark, i.e. (figuratively) deviate from truth:--err, swerve.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to deviate from, miss (the mark)</OL>'),
(796, 'ajstraphv', 'from (797)', 'astrape', '1:505,86', 'as-trap-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «797»; lightning; by analogy, glare:--lightning, bright shining.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lightning<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the gleam of a lamp</OL></OL>'),
(797, 'ajstravptw', 'probably from (792)', 'astrapto', 'None', 'as-trap\'-to', 'Verb', 'probably from  «792»; to flash as lightning:--lighten, shine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lighten<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of dazzling objects</OL></OL>'),
(798, 'a[stron', 'from (792)', 'astron', '1:503,86', 'as\'-tron', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter from «792»; properly, a constellation; put for a single star (natural or artificial):--star.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a group of stars, a constellation<LI>a star</OL>'),
(799, 'ÅAsuvgkritoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (4793)', 'Asugkritos', 'None', 'as-oong\'-kree-tos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «4793»; incomparable; Asyncritus, a Christian:--Asyncritos.', 'Asyncritus = \"incomparable\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an unknown Christian at Rome saluted by Paul</OL>'),
(800, 'ajsuvmfwnoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (4859)', 'asumphonos', 'None', 'as-oom\'-fo-nos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «4859»; inharmonious (figuratively):--agree not.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>not agreeing in sound, dissonant, inharmonious, at variance</OL>'),
(801, 'ajsuvnetoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and (4908)', 'asunetos', '7:888,1119', 'as-oon\'-ay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and «4908»; unintelligent; by implication, wicked:--foolish, without understanding.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unintelligent, without understanding, stupid</OL>'),
(802, 'ajsuvnqetoß', 'from (1) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of (4934)', 'asunthetos', 'None', 'as-oon\'-thet-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1» (as a negative particle) and a derivative of «4934»; properly, not agreed, i.e. treacherous to compacts:-- covenant-breaker.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>uncompounded, simple<LI>covenant breaking, faithless</OL>'),
(803, 'ajsfavleia', 'from (804)', 'asphaleia', '1:506,87', 'as-fal\'-i-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «804»; security (literally or figuratively):--certainty, safety.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>firmness, stability<LI>certainty, undoubted truth<LI>security from enemies and dangers, safety</OL>'),
