(937, 'basilikovß', 'from (935)', 'basilikos', '1:591,97', 'bas-il-ee-kos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «935»; regal (in relation), i.e. (literally) belonging to (or befitting) the sovereign (as land, dress, or a courtier), or (figuratively) preeminent:--king\'s, nobleman, royal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of or belong to a king, kingly, royal, regal<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a man, the officer or minister of a prince, a courtier</OL><LI>subject to a king<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a country</OL><LI>befitting or worthy of a king, royal<LI>metaph. principal, chief</OL>'),
