(1272, 'dianoivgw', 'from (1223) and (455)', 'dianoigo', 'None', 'dee-an-oy\'-go', 'Verb', 'from «1223» and «455»; to open thoroughly, literally (as a first-born) or figuratively (to expound):--open.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to open by dividing or drawing asunder, to open thoroughly (what had been closed)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a male opening the womb (the closed matrix), i.e. the first-born<LI>of the eyes and the ears<LI>to open the mind of one, i.e. to cause to understand a thing<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to open one\'s soul, i.e. to rouse in one the faculty of understanding or the desire of learning</OL></OL></OL>'),
