(1287, 'diaskorpivzw', 'from (1223) and (4650)', 'diaskorpizo', '7:418,1048', 'dee-as-kor-pid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «1223» and «4650»; to dissipate, i.e. (genitive case) to rout or separate; specially, to winnow; figuratively, to squander:--disperse, scatter (abroad), strew, waste.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to scatter abroad, disperse, to winnow<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to throw the grain a considerable distance, or up into the air, that it may be separated from the chaff<LI>to gather the wheat, freed from the chaff into the granary<LI>to winnow grain</OL></OL>'),
