(1303, 'diativqhmi', 'middle voice from (1223) and (5087)', 'diatithemai', '2:104,157', 'dee-at-ith\'-em-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «1223» and «5087»; to put apart, i.e. (figuratively) dispose (by assignment, compact, or bequest):--appoint, make, testator.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to arrange, dispose of, one\'s own affairs<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of something that belongs to one<LI>to dispose of by will, make a testament</OL><LI>to make a covenant, enter into a covenant, with one</OL>'),
