(1449, 'ejggravfw', 'from (1722) and (1125)', 'eggrapho', '1:769,128', 'eng-graf\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «1125»; to \"engrave\", i.e. inscribe:--write (in).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to engrave, inscribe, write in or on<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to record, enrol</OL></OL>'),
(1450, 'e[gguoß', 'from (1722) and guion (a limb)', 'egguos', '2:329,194', 'eng\'-goo-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1722» and guion (a limb); pledged (as if articulated by a member), i.e. a bondsman:--surety.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a surety, a sponsor</OL>'),
(1451, 'ejgguvß', 'from a primary verb agcho (to squeeze or throttle; akin to the base of (43))', 'eggus', '2:330,194', 'eng-goos\'', 'Adverb', 'from a primary verb agcho (to squeeze or throttle; akin to the base of «43»); near (literally or figuratively, of place or time):--from , at hand, near, nigh (at hand, unto), ready.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>near, of place and position<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>near<LI>those who are near access to God<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Jews, as opposed to those who are alien from God and his blessings<LI>The Rabbis used the term \"to make nigh\" as equivalent to \"to make a proselyte\"</OL></OL><LI>of time<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of times imminent and soon to come pass</OL></OL>'),
(1452, 'ejgguvteron', 'from the comparative of (1451)', 'egguteron', 'None', 'eng-goo\'-ter-on', 'Adverb Neuter', 'neuter of the comparative of «1451»; nearer:--nearer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nearer</OL>'),
(1453, 'ejgeivrw', 'probably akin to the base of (58) (through the idea of collecting one\'s faculties)', 'egeiro', '2:333,195', 'eg-i\'-ro', 'Verb', 'probably akin to the base of «58» (through the idea of collecting one\'s faculties); to waken (transitively or intransitively), i.e. rouse (literally, from sleep, from sitting or lying, from disease, from death; or figuratively, from obscurity, inactivity, ruins, nonexistence):--awake, lift (up), raise (again, up), rear up, (a-)rise (again, up), stand, take up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to arouse, cause to rise<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to arouse from sleep, to awake<LI>to arouse from the sleep of death, to recall the dead to life<LI>to cause to rise from a seat or bed etc.<LI>to raise up, produce, cause to appear<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to appear, bring before the public<LI>to raise up, stir up, against one<LI>to raise up i.e. cause to be born<LI>of buildings, to raise up, construct, erect</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1454, 'e[gersiß', 'from (1453)', 'egersis', '2:337,195', 'eg\'-er-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1453»; a resurgence (from death):--resurrection.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a rousing, excitation<LI>a rising up<LI>resurrection from the dead</OL>'),
(1455, 'ejgkavqetoß', 'from (1722) and a derivative of (2524)', 'egkathetos', 'None', 'eng-kath\'-et-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1722» and a derivative of «2524»; subinduced, i.e. surreptitiously suborned as a lier-in-wait:--spy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>secretly to lie in wait, a spy<LI>one who is bribed by others to entrap a man by crafty words</OL>'),
(1456, 'ejgkaivnia', 'plural of a presumed compound from (1722) and (2537)', 'egkainia', 'None', 'eng-kah\'-ee-nee-ah', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter plural of a presumed compound from «1722» and «2537»; innovatives, i.e. (specially) renewal (of religious services after the Antiochian interruption):--dedication.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dedication, consecration<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in particular the annual feast celebrated eight days beginning in the 25th of Chislev (middle of our December), instituted by Judas Maccabaeus [164 BC] in memory of the cleansing of the temple from the pollution of Antiochus Epiphanes</OL></OL>'),
(1457, 'ejgkanivzw', 'from (1456)', 'egkainizo', '3:453,388', 'eng-kahee-nid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «1456»; to renew, i.e. inaugurate:--consecrate, dedicate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to renew<LI>to do anew, again<LI>to initiate, consecrate, dedication</OL>'),
(1458, 'ejgkalevw', 'from (1722) and (2564)', 'egkaleo', '3:496,394', 'eng-kal-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «2564»; to call in (as a debt or demand), i.e. bring to account (charge, criminate, etc.):--accuse, call in question, implead, lay to the charge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to come forward as accuser against, bring charge against<LI>to be accused</OL>'),
(1459, 'ejgkataleivpw', 'from (1722) and (2641)', 'egkataleipo', 'None', 'eng-kat-al-i\'-po', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «2641»; to leave behind in some place, i.e. (in a good sense) let remain over, or (in a bad sense) to desert:--forsake, leave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>abandon, desert<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>leave in straits, leave helpless<LI>totally abandoned, utterly forsaken</OL><LI>to leave behind among, to leave surviving</OL>'),
(1460, 'ejgkatoikevw', 'from (1722) and (2730)', 'egkatoikeo', 'None', 'eng-kat-oy-keh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «2730»; to settle down in a place, i.e. reside:--dwell among.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dwell among</OL>'),
(1461, 'ejgkaucavomai', 'from (1722) and a derivative of (2759)', 'egkentrizo', 'None', 'eng-ken-trid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and a derivative of «2759»; to prick in, i.e. ingraft:--graff in(-to).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut into for the sake of inserting a scion<LI>to inoculate, ingraft, graft in</OL>'),
(1462, 'e[gklhma', 'from (1458)', 'egklema', '3:496,394', 'eng\'-klay-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «1458»; an accusation, i.e. offence alleged:--crime laid against, laid to charge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>accusation: the crime of which one is accused</OL>'),
(1463, 'ejgkombovomai', 'middle voice from (1722) and komboo (to gird)', 'egkomboomai', '2:339,196', 'eng-kom-bo\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «1722» and komboo (to gird); to engirdle oneself (for labor), i.e. figuratively (the apron as being a badge of servitude) to wear (in token of mutual deference):--be clothed with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>knot or band by which two things are fastened together, to fasten or gird one\'s self</OL>'),
(1464, 'ejgkophv', 'from (1465)', 'egkope', '3:855,453', 'eng-kop-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1465»; a hindrance:--X hinder.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a cutting (made in a road to impede an enemy in pursuit)<LI>a hindrance</OL>'),
(1465, 'ejgkovptw', 'from (1722) and (2875)', 'egkopto', '3:855,453', 'eng-kop\'-to', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «2875»; to cut into, i.e. (figuratively) impede, detain:--hinder, be tedious unto.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut into, to impede one\'s course by cutting off his way<LI>hinder</OL>'),
(1466, 'ejgkravteia', 'from (1468)', 'egkrateia', '2:339,196', 'eng-krat\'-i-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1468»; self-control (especially continence):--temperance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>self-control (the virtue of one who masters his desires and passions, esp. his sensual appetites)</OL>'),
(1467, 'ejgkrateuvomai', 'middle voice from (1468)', 'egkrateuomai', '2:339,196', 'eng-krat-yoo\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «1468»; to exercise self-restraint (in diet and chastity):--can(-not) contain, be temperate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be self-controlled, continent<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to exhibit self-government, conduct, one\'s self temperately<LI>in a figure drawn from athletes, who in preparing themselves for the games abstained from unwholesome food, wine, and sexual indulgence</OL></OL>'),
(1468, 'ejgkrathvß', 'from (1722) and (2904)', 'egkrates', '2:339,196', 'eng-krat-ace\'', 'Adjective', 'from «1722» and «2904»; strong in a thing (masterful), i.e. (figuratively and reflexively) self-controlled (in appetite, etc.):--temperate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strong, robust<LI>having power over, possessed of (a thing)<LI>mastering, controlling, curbing, restraining<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>controlling one\'s self, temperate, continent</OL></OL>'),
(1469, 'ejgkrivnw', 'from (1722) and (2919)', 'egkrino', '3:951,469', 'eng-kree\'-no', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «2919»; to judge in, i.e. count among:--make of the number.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to reckon among, judge among<LI>to judge one worthy of being admitted to a certain class</OL>'),
(1470, 'ejgkruvptw', 'from (1722) and (2928)', 'ekgrupto', 'None', 'eng-kroop\'-to', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «2928»; to conceal in, i.e. incorporate with:--hid in.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to conceal in something<LI>to mingle one thing with another</OL>'),
(1471, 'e[gkuoß', 'from (1722) and the base of (2949)', 'egkuos', 'None', 'eng\'-koo-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1722» and the base of «2949»; swelling inside, i.e. pregnant:--great with child.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>big with child, pregnant</OL>'),
(1472, 'ejgcrivw', 'from (1722) and (5548)', 'egchrio', 'None', 'eng-khree\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «5548»; to rub in (oil), i.e. besmear:--anoint.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rub in, besmirch, anoint<LI>to anoint one\'s self</OL>'),
(1473, 'ejgwv', 'a primary pronoun of the first person I (only expressed when emphatic)', 'ego', '2:343,196', 'eg-o\'', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>I, me, my</OL>', 'a primary pronoun of the first person I (only expressed when emphatic):--I, me. For the other cases and the plural see «1691», «1698», «1700», «2248», «2249», «2254», «2257», etc.', ''),
(1474, 'ejdafivzw', 'from (1475)', 'edaphizo', 'None', 'ed-af-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «1475»; to raze:--lay even with the ground.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to throw to the ground<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>both of cities and buildings, to raze, level with the earth<LI>metaph. of men</OL></OL>'),
(1475, 'e[dafoß', 'from the base of (1476)', 'edaphos', 'None', 'ed\'-af-os', 'Noun Neuter', 'from the base of «1476»; a basis (bottom), i.e. the soil:--ground.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bottom, base, ground</OL>'),
(1476, 'eJdrai\'oß', 'from a derivative of hezomai (to sit)', 'hedraios', '2:362,200', 'hed-rah\'-yos', 'Adjective', 'from a derivative of hezomai (to sit); sedentary, i.e. (by implication) immovable:--settled, stedfast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sitting, sedentary<LI>firm, immovable, steadfast</OL>'),
(1477, 'eJdraivwma', 'from a derivative of (1476)', 'hedraioma', '2:362,200', 'hed-rah\'-yo-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a derivative of «1476»; a support, i.e. (figuratively) basis:--ground.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a stay, prop, support</OL>'),
(1478, 'ÔEzekivaß', 'of Hebrew origin (02396)', 'Ezekias', 'None', 'ed-zek-ee\'-as', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («02396»); Ezekias (i.e. Hezekeiah), an Israelite:--Ezekias.', 'Hezekiah = \"the might of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the twelfth king of Judah</OL>'),
(1479, 'ejqeloqrhskiva', 'from (2309) and (2356)', 'ethelothreskeia', '3:155,337', 'eth-el-oth-race-ki\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2309» and «2356»; voluntary (arbitrary and unwarranted) piety, i.e. sanctimony:--will worship.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>voluntary, arbitrary worship<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>worship which one prescribes and devises for himself, contrary to the contents and nature of faith which ought to be directed to Christ<LI>said of the misdirected zeal and the practice of ascetics</OL></OL>'),
(1480, 'ejqivzw', 'from (1485)', 'ethizo', 'None', 'eth-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «1485»; to accustom, i.e. (neuter passive participle) customary:--custom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to accustomed, usage, custom</OL>'),
(1481, 'ejqnavrchß', 'from (1484) and (746)', 'ethnarches', 'None', 'eth-nar\'-khace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «1484» and «746»; the governor (not king) of a district:--ethnarch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an ethnarch, one set over a people as ruler, but without the authority and name of a king</OL>'),
(1482, 'ejqnikovß', 'from (1484)', 'ethnikos', '2:372,201', 'eth-nee-kos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «1484»; national (\"ethnic\"), i.e. (specially) a Gentile:--heathen (man).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>adapted to the genius or customs of a people, peculiar to a people, national<LI>suited to the manners or language of foreigners, strange, foreign<LI>in the NT savouring of the nature of pagans, alien to the worship of the true God, heathenish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the pagan, the Gentile</OL></OL>'),
(1483, 'ejqnikw\'ß', 'from (1482)', 'ethnikos', 'None', 'eth-nee-koce\'', 'Adverb', 'adverb from «1482»; as a Gentile:--after the manner of Gentiles.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>like the Gentiles</OL>'),
(1484, 'e[qnoß', 'probably from (1486)', 'ethnos', '2:364,201', 'eth\'-nos', 'Noun Neuter', 'probably from «1486»; a race (as of the same habit), i.e. a tribe; specially, a foreign (non-Jewish) one (usually, by implication, pagan):--Gentile, heathen, nation, people.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a multitude (whether of men or of beasts) associated or living together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a company, troop, swarm</OL><LI>a multitude of individuals of the same nature or genus<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the human family</OL><LI>a tribe, nation, people group<LI>in the OT, foreign nations not worshipping the true God, pagans, Gentiles<LI>Paul uses the term for Gentile Christians</OL>'),
(1485, 'e[qoß', 'from (1486)', 'ethos', '2:372,202', 'eth\'-os', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «1486»; a usage (prescribed by habit or law):--custom, manner, be wont.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>custom<LI>usage prescribed by law, institute, prescription, rite</OL>'),
(1486, 'e[qw', 'a root word', 'etho', 'None', 'eth\'-o', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to be used (by habit or conventionality); neuter perfect participle usage:--be custom (manner, wont).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be accustomed, used, wont<LI>that which is wont<LI>usage, custom</OL>'),
(1487, 'eij', 'a primary particle of conditionality', 'ei', 'None', 'i', 'Conjunction', 'a primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.:--forasmuch as, if, that, (al-)though, whether. Often used in connection or composition with other particles, especially as in «1489», «1490», «1499», «1508», «1509», «1512», «1513», «1536», «1537». See also «1437».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>if, whether</OL>'),
(1488, 'ei\\', 'second person singular present of (1510)', 'ei', 'None', 'i', 'Verb', 'second person singular present of «1510»; thou art:--art, be.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>you are, thou art</OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(1489, 'ei[ge', 'from (1487) and (1065)', 'eige', 'None', 'i\'-gheh', 'Conjunction', 'from «1487» and «1065»; if indeed, seeing that, unless, (with negative) otherwise:--if (so be that, yet).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>if, indeed, inasmuch, as, since</OL>'),
(1490, 'eijdeva', 'from (1487), (1161), and (3361) (sometimes with (1065) added)', 'ei', 'None', 'me(ge)', 'Conjunction', 'from «1487», «1161», and «3361» (sometimes with «1065» added); but if not:--(or) else, if (not, otherwise), otherwise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>otherwise, but if not</OL>'),
(1491, 'ei\\don', 'from (1492)', 'eidos', '2:373,202', 'i\'-dos', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «1492»; a view, i.e. form (literally or figuratively):--appearance, fashion, shape, sight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the external or outward appearance, form figure, shape<LI>form, kind</OL>'),
(1492, 'ei[dw', 'a root word', 'eido', '5:116, 673', 'i\'-do', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; used only in certain past tenses, the others being borrowed from the equivalent «3700» and «3708»; properly, to see (literally or figuratively); by implication, (in the perfect tense only) to know:--be aware, behold, × can (+ not tell), consider, (have) know(-ledge), look (on), perceive, see, be sure, tell, understand, wish, wot. Compare «3700».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to see<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to perceive with the eyes<LI>to perceive by any of the senses<LI>to perceive, notice, discern, discover<LI>to see<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>i.e. to turn the eyes, the mind, the attention to anything<LI>to pay attention, observe<LI>to see about something 1d</OL></OL><LI>i.e. to ascertain what must be done about it<OL TYPE=\"d\"><OL TYPE=\"4\"><LI>to inspect, examine<LI>to look at, behold</OL><LI>to experience any state or condition<LI>to see i.e. have an interview with, to visit</OL><LI>to know<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to know of anything<LI>to know, i.e. get knowledge of, understand, perceive<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of any fact<LI>the force and meaning of something which has definite meaning<LI>to know how, to be skilled in</OL><LI>to have regard for one, cherish, pay attention to (1Th. 5:</OL><LI></OL>'),
(1493, 'eijdwlei\'on', 'from a presumed derivative of (1497)', 'eidoleion', '2:379,202', 'i-do-li\'-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of «1497»; an image-fane:--idol\'s temple.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an idol\'s temple, temple consecrated to idols</OL>'),
(1494, 'eijdwlovqutoß', 'neuter of a compound of (1497) and a presumed derivative of (2380)', 'eidolothuton', '2:378,202', 'i-do-loth\'-oo-ton', 'Adjective', 'neuter of a compound of «1497» and a presumed derivative of «2380»; an image-sacrifice, i.e. part of an idolatrous offering:--(meat, thing that is) offered (in sacrifice, sacrificed) to (unto) idols.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sacrificed to idols, the flesh left over from the heathen sacrifices<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>it was either eaten at the feasts or sold (by the poor and the miserly) in the market</OL></OL>'),
(1495, 'eijdwlolatriva', 'from (1497) and (2999)', 'eidololatreia', '2:379,202', 'i-do-lol-at-ri\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1497» and «2999»; image-worship (literally or figuratively):--idolatry.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the worship of false gods, idolatry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the formal sacrificial feats held in honour of false gods<LI>of avarice, as a worship of Mammon</OL><LI>in the plural, the vices springing from idolatry and peculiar to it</OL>'),
(1496, 'eijdwlolavtrhß', 'from (1497) and the base of (3000)', 'eidololatres', '2:379,202', 'i-do-lol-at\'-race', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «1497» and the base of «3000»; an image- (servant or) worshipper (literally or figuratively):--idolater.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a worshipper of false gods, a idolater<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used of any one even Christian, participant in any way in the worship of the heathen, esp. one who attends their sacrificial feasts and eats of the remains of offered victims</OL><LI>a covetous man as a worshipper of Mammon</OL>'),
(1497, 'ei[dwlon', 'from (1491); an image (i.e. for worship)', 'eidolon', '2:375,202', 'i\'-do-lon', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «1491»; an image (i.e. for worship); by implication, a heathen god, or (plural) the worship of such:--idol.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an image, likeness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>i.e. whatever represents the form of an object, either real or imaginary<LI>used of the shades of the departed, apparitions, spectres, phantoms of the mind, etc.</OL><LI>the image of an heathen god<LI>a false god</OL>'),
(1498, 'ei[hn', 'optative (i.e. English subjunctive) present of (1510) (including the other person)', 'eien', 'None', 'i\'-ane', 'Verb', 'optative (i.e. English subjunctive) present of «1510» (including the other person); might (could, would, or should) be:--mean, + perish, should be, was, were.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be, to exist, to happen, to be present</OL>'),
(1499, 'eij kaiv', 'from (1487) and (2532)', 'ei', 'None', '', 'Conjunction', 'from «1487» and «2532»; if also (or even):--if (that), though.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>even, if, although</OL>'),
(1500, 'eijkh\'/', 'probably from (1502) (through the idea of failure)', 'eike', '2:380,203', 'i-kay\'', 'Adverb', 'probably from «1502» (through the idea of failure); idly, i.e. without reason (or effect):--without a cause, (in) vain(-ly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>inconsiderably, without purpose, without just cause<LI>in vain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>without success or effort</OL></OL>'),
(1501, 'ei[kosi', 'of uncertain affinity', 'eikosi', 'None', 'i\'-kos-ee', 'Noun', 'of uncertain affinity; a score:--twenty.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>twenty</OL>'),
(1502, 'ei[kw', 'apparently a root word', 'eiko', 'None', 'i\'-ko', 'Verb', 'apparently a primary verb; properly, to be weak, i.e. yield:--give place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to yield</OL>'),
(1503, 'ei[kw', 'apparently a root word [perhaps akin to (1502) through the idea of faintness as a copy]', 'eiko', 'None', 'i\'-ko', 'Verb', 'apparently a primary verb (perhaps akin to «1502» through the idea of faintness as a copy); to resemble:--be like.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be like</OL>'),
(1504, 'eijkwvn', 'from (1503)', 'eikon', '2:381,203', 'i-kone\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1503»; a likeness, i.e. (literally) statue, profile, or (figuratively) representation, resemblance:--image.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an image, figure, likeness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an image of the things (the heavenly things)<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>used of the moral likeness of renewed men to God<LI>the image of the Son of God, into which true Christians are transformed, is likeness not only to the heavenly body, but also to the most holy and blessed state of mind, which Christ possesses</OL><LI>the image of one<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one in whom the likeness of any one is seen<LI>applied to man on account of his power of command<LI>to Christ on account of his divine nature and absolute moral excellence</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1505, 'eijlikrineiva', 'from (1506)', 'eilikrineia', '2:397,206', 'i-lik-ree\'-ni-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1506»; clearness, i.e. (by implication) purity (figuratively):--sincerity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>purity, sincerity, ingenuousness</OL>'),
(1506, 'eijlikrinhvß', 'from heile (the sun\'s ray) and (2919)', 'eilikrines', '2:397,206', 'i-lik-ree-nace\'', 'Adjective', 'from heile (the sun\'s ray) and «2919»; judged by sunlight, i.e. tested as genuine (figuratively):--pure, sincere.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pure, sincere, unsullied<LI>found pure when unfolded and examined by the sun\'s light</OL>'),
(1507, 'eiJlivssw', 'a prolonged form of a primary but defective verb heilo (of the same meaning)', 'heilisso', 'None', 'hi-lis\'-so', 'Verb', 'a prolonged form of a primary but defective verb heilo (of the same meaning); to coil or wrap:--roll together. See also «1667».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to roll up or together</OL>'),
(1508, 'eij mhv', 'from (1487) and (3361)', 'ei', 'None', '', 'Conjunction', 'from «1487» and «3361»; if not:--but, except (that), if not, more than, save (only) that, saving, till.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>if not, except, but</OL>'),
(1509, 'eij mhvti', 'from (1508) and the neuter of (5100)', 'ei', 'None', 'ti', 'Conjunction', 'from «1508» and the neuter of «5100»; if not somewhat:--except.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unless indeed, except, unless perhaps</OL>'),
(1510, 'eijmiv', 'the first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb', 'eimi', '2:398,206', 'i-mee\'', 'Verb', 'the first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist (used only when emphatic):--am, have been, × it is I, was. See also «1488», «1498», «1511», «1527», «2258», «2071», «2070», «2075», «2076», «2771», «2468», «5600».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be, to exist, to happen, to be present</OL>'),
