(1771, 'e[nnoia', 'from a compound of (1722) and (3563)', 'ennoia', '4:968,636', 'en\'-noy-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a compound of «1722» and «3563»; thoughtfulness, i.e. moral understanding:--intent, mind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the act of thinking, consideration, meditation<LI>a thought, notion, conception<LI>mind, understanding, will, manner of feeling, and thinking</OL>'),
(1772, 'e[nnomoß', 'from (1722) and (3551)', 'ennomos', '4:1087,646', 'en\'-nom-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1722» and «3551»; (subjectively) legal, or (objectively) subject to:--lawful, under law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bound to the law<LI>bound by the law, lawful<LI>lawful, regular</OL>'),
(1773, 'e[nnucoß', 'neuter of a compound of (1722) and (3571)', 'ennuchon', 'None', 'en\'-noo-khon', 'Adjective', 'neuter of a compound of «1722» and «3571»; (adverbially) by night:--before day.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nightly, nocturnal</OL>'),
(1774, 'ejnoikevw', 'from (1722) and (3611)', 'enoikeo', 'None', 'en-oy-keh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «3611»; to inhabit (figuratively):--dwell in.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dwell in<LI>metaph. to dwell in one and influence him (for good)</OL>'),
(1775, 'ejnorkivzw', 'from (1520)', 'henotes', 'None', 'hen-ot-ace\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1520»; oneness, i.e. (figuratively) unanimity:--unity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>unity<LI>unanimity, agreement</OL>'),
(1776, 'ejnoclevw', 'from (1722) and (3791)', 'enochleo', 'None', 'en-okh-leh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «3791»; to crowd in, i.e. (figuratively) to annoy:--trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to excite, disturbance, to trouble, annoy</OL>'),
(1777, 'e[nocoß', 'from (1758)', 'enochos', '2:828,286', 'en\'-okh-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1758»; liable to (a condition, penalty or imputation):--in danger of, guilty of, subject to.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bound, under obligation, subject to, liable<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used of one who is held by, possessed with love, and zeal for anything<LI>in a forensic sense, denoting the connection of a person either with his crime, or with the penalty or trial, or with that against whom or which he has offended<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>guilty, worthy of punishment<LI>guilty of anything<LI>of the crime<LI>of the penalty<LI>liable to this or that tribunal i.e. the punishment to by imposed by this or that tribunal<LI>of the place where punishment is to be suffered</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1778, 'e[ntalma', 'from (1781)', 'entalma', 'None', 'en\'-tal-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «1781»; an injunction, i.e. religious precept:--commandment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a precept</OL>'),
(1779, 'ejntafiavzw', 'from a compound of (1722) and (5028)', 'entaphiazo', 'None', 'en-taf-ee-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from a compound of «1722» and «5028»; to inswathe with cerements for interment:--bury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prepare a body for burial, by the use of every requisite provision and funeral adornment, that is, baths, vestments, flowers, wreathes, perfumes, libations, etc.<LI>to lay out a corpse</OL>'),
(1780, 'ejntafiasmovß', 'from (1779)', 'entaphiasmos', 'None', 'en-taf-ee-as-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «1779»; preparation for interment:--burying.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>preparation of a body for burial</OL>'),
(1781, 'ejntevllomai', 'from (1722) and the base of (5056)', 'entellomai', '2:544,234', 'en-tel\'-lom-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and the base of «5056»; to enjoin:--(give) charge, (give) command(-ments), injoin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to order, command to be done, enjoin</OL>'),
(1782, 'ejnteu\'qen', 'from the same as (1759)', 'enteuthen', 'None', 'ent-yoo\'-then', 'Adverb', 'from the same as «1759»; hence (literally or figuratively); (repeated) on both sides:--(from) hence, on either side.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>from this place, hence<LI>on the one side and on the other, on each side</OL>'),
(1783, 'e[nteuxiß', 'from (1793)', 'enteuxis', '8:244,1191', 'ent\'-yook-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1793»; an interview, i.e. (specially) supplication:--intercession, prayer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a falling in with, meeting with<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an interview<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a coming together<LI>to visit<LI>converse or for any other cause</OL><LI>that for which an interview is held<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a conference or conversation<LI>a petition, supplication</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1784, 'e[ntimoß', 'from (1722) and (5092)', 'entimos', 'None', 'en\'-tee-mos', 'Adjective', 'from «1722» and «5092»; valued (figuratively):--dear, more honourable, precious, in reputation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>held in honour, prized, precious</OL>'),
(1785, 'ejntolhv', 'from (1781)', 'entole', '2:545,234', 'en-tol-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1781»; injunction, i.e. an authoritative prescription:--commandment, precept.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an order, command, charge, precept, injunction<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>that which is prescribed to one by reason of his office</OL><LI>a commandment<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a prescribed rule in accordance with which a thing is done<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a precept relating to lineage, of the Mosaic precept concerning the priesthood<LI>ethically used of the commandments in the Mosaic law or Jewish tradition</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1786, 'ejntovpioß', 'from (1722) and (5117)', 'entopios', 'None', 'en-top\'-ee-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1722» and «5117»; a resident:--of that place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a dweller in a place<LI>a resident or native of a place</OL>'),
(1787, 'ejntovß', 'from (1722)', 'entos', 'None', 'en-tos\'', 'Preposition', 'from «1722»; inside (adverb or noun):--within.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>within, inside<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>within you i.e. in the midst of you<LI>within you i.e. your soul</OL></OL>'),
(1788, 'ejntrevpw', 'from (1722) and the base of (5157)', 'entrepo', 'None', 'en-trep\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and the base of «5157»; to invert, i.e. (figuratively and reflexively) in a good sense, to respect; or in a bad one, to confound:--regard, (give) reference, shame.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shame one<LI>to be ashamed<LI>to reverence a person<LI>to turn about</OL>'),
(1789, 'ejntrevfw', 'from (1722) and (5142)', 'entrepho', 'None', 'en-tref\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «5142»; (figuratively) to educate:--nourish up in.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to nourish in: a person or a thing<LI>metaph. to educate, form the mind</OL>'),
(1790, 'e[ntromoß', 'from (1722) and (5156)', 'entromos', 'None', 'en\'-trom-os', 'Adjective', 'from «1722» and «5156»; terrified:--X quake, × trembled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>trembling, terrified</OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(1791, 'ejntrophv', 'from (1788)', 'entrope', 'None', 'en-trop-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1788»; confusion:--shame.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>shame<LI>respect, reverence</OL>'),
(1792, 'ejntrufavw', 'from (1722) and (5171)', 'entruphao', 'None', 'en-troo-fah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «5171»; to revel in:--sporting selves.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to live in luxury, live delicately or luxuriously, to revel in<LI>to take delight in</OL>'),
(1793, 'ejntugcavnw', 'from (1722) and (5177)', 'entugchano', '8:242,1191', 'en-toong-khan\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «5177»; to chance upon, i.e. (by implication) confer with; by extension to entreat (in favor or against):--deal with, make intercession.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to light upon a person or a thing, fall in with, hit upon, a person or a thing<LI>to go to or meet a person, esp. for the purpose of conversation, consultation, or supplication<LI>to pray, entreat<LI>make intercession for any one</OL>'),
(1794, 'ejntulivssw', 'from (1722) and tulisso (to twist, probably akin to (1507))', 'entulisso', 'None', 'en-too-lis\'-so', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and tulisso (to twist; probably akin to «1507»); to entwine, i.e. wind up in:--wrap in (together).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to roll up, wrap together</OL>'),
(1795, 'ejntupovw', 'from (1722) and a derivative of (5179)', 'entupoo', 'None', 'en-too-po\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and a derivative of «5179»; to enstamp, i.e. engrave:--engrave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to engrave, imprint (a figure)</OL>'),
(1796, 'ejnubrivzw', 'from (1722) and (5195)', 'enubrizo', '8:295,1200', 'en-oo-brid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «1722» and «5195»; to insult:--do despite unto.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to insult</OL>'),
(1797, 'ejnupniavzomai', 'middle voice from (1798)', 'enupniazomai', '8:545,1233', 'en-oop-nee-ad\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «1798»; to dream:--dream(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dream (divinely suggested) dreams<LI>metaph., to be beguiled with sensual images and carried away to an impious course of conduct</OL>'),
(1798, 'ejnuvpnion', 'from (1722) and (5258)', 'enupnion', '8:545,1233', 'en-oop\'-nee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «1722» and «5258»; something seen in sleep, i.e. a dream (vision in a dream):--dream.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a dream</OL>'),
(1799, 'ejnwvpioß', 'neuter of a compound of (1722) and a derivative of (3700)', 'enopion', 'None', 'en-o\'-pee-on', 'Preposition', 'neuter of a compound of «1722» and a derivative of «3700»; in the face of (literally or figuratively):--before, in the presence (sight) of, to.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in the presence of, before<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of occupied place: in that place which is before, or over against, opposite, any one and towards which another turns his eyes</OL></OL>'),
(1800, 'ÅEnwvß', 'of Hebrew origin (0583)', 'Enos', 'None', 'en-oce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («0583»); Enos (i.e. Enosh), a patriarch:--Enos.', 'Enos = \"mortal man\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Seth</OL>'),
(1801, 'ejnwtivzomai', 'middle voice from a compound of (1722) and (3775)', 'enotizomai', '5:559,744', 'en-o-tid\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from a compound of «1722» and «3775»; to take in one\'s ear, i.e. to listen:--hearken.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to receive into the ear, to give ear to, listen</OL>'),
(1802, 'ÅEnwvc', 'of Hebrew origin (02585)', 'Enok', '2:556,237', 'en-oke\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («02585»); Enoch (i.e. Chanok), an antediluvian:--Enoch.', 'Enoch = \"dedicated\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Jared and father of Methuselah</OL>'),
(1803, 'e&x', 'a primary numeral', 'hex', 'None', 'hex', 'Noun', 'a primary numeral; six:--six.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>six</OL>'),
(1804, 'ejxaggevllw', 'from (1537) and the base of (32)', 'exaggello', '1:69,10', 'ex-ang-el\'-lo', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and the base of «32»; to publish, i.e. celebrate:--shew forth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tell out or forth<LI>to declare abroad, divulge, publish<LI>to make known by praising or proclaiming, to celebrate</OL>'),
(1805, 'ejxagoravzw', 'from (1537) and (59)', 'exagorazo', '1:124,19', 'ex-ag-or-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «59»; to buy up, i.e. ransom; figuratively, to rescue from loss (improve opportunity):--redeem.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to redeem<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>by payment of a price to recover from the power of another, to ransom, buy off<LI>metaph. of Christ freeing the elect from the dominion of the Mosaic Law at the price of his vicarious death</OL><LI>to buy up, to buy up for one\'s self, for one\'s use<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to make wise and sacred use of every opportunity for doing good, so that zeal and well doing are as it were the purchase money by which we make the time our own</OL></OL>'),
(1806, 'ejxavgw', 'from (1537) and (71)', 'exago', 'None', 'ex-ag\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «71»; to lead forth:--bring forth (out), fetch (lead) out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead out</OL>'),
(1807, 'ejxairevw', 'from (1537) and (138)', 'exaireo', 'None', 'ex-ahee-reh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «138»; actively, to tear out; middle voice, to select; figuratively, to release:--deliver, pluck out, rescue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pluck out, draw out, i.e. root out<LI>to choose out (for one\'s self), select, one person from many<LI>to rescue, deliver</OL>'),
(1808, 'ejxaivrw', 'from (1537) and (142)', 'exairo', 'None', 'ex-ah\'-ee-ro', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «142»; to remove:--put (take) away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lift up or take away out of a place<LI>to remove</OL>'),
(1809, 'ejxaitevw', 'middle voice from (1537) and (154)', 'exaiteomai', '1:194,*', 'ex-ahee-teh\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «1537» and «154»; to demand (for trial):--desire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to ask from, demand of<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to ask or beg for one\'s self, to ask that one be given up to one from the power of another<LI>in a good sense,<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to beg one from another<LI>ask for the pardon<LI>the safety of some one</OL><LI>in a bad sense<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>for torture<LI>for punishment</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1810, 'ejxaivfnhß', 'from (1537) and the base of (160)', 'exaiphnes', 'None', 'ex-ah\'-eef-nace', 'Adverb', 'from «1537» and the base of «160»; of a sudden (unexpectedly):--suddenly. Compare «1819».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of a sudden, suddenly, unexpectedly</OL>'),
(1811, 'ejxakolouqevw', 'from (1537) and (190)', 'exakoloutheo', '1:215,33', 'ex-ak-ol-oo-theh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «190»; to follow out, i.e. (figuratively) to imitate, obey, yield to:--follow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to follow out or up, tread in one\'s steps<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>metaph., to imitate one\'s ways of acting<LI>to follow one\'s authority<LI>to comply with, yield to</OL></OL>'),
(1812, 'eJxakovsioi', 'plural ordinal from (1803) and (1540)', 'hexakosioi', 'None', 'hex-ak-os\'-ee-oy', 'Adjective', 'plural ordinal from «1803» and «1540»; six hundred:--six hundred.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>six hundred</OL>'),
(1813, 'ejxaleivfw', 'from (1537) and (218)', 'exaleipho', 'None', 'ex-al-i\'-fo', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «218»; to smear out, i.e. obliterate (erase tears, figuratively, pardon sin):--blot out, wipe away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to anoint or wash in every part<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to besmear: i.e. cover with lime (to whitewash or plaster)</OL><LI>to wipe off, wipe away<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to obliterate, erase, wipe out, blot out</OL></OL>'),
(1814, 'ejxavllomai', 'from (1537) and (242)', 'exallomai', 'None', 'ex-al\'-lom-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «242»; to spring forth :--leap up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to leap up</OL>'),
(1815, 'ejxanavstasiß', 'from (1817)', 'exanastasis', '1:371,60', 'ex-an-as\'-tas-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «1817»; a rising from death:--resurrection.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a rising up, a rising again<LI>resurrection</OL>'),
(1816, 'ejxanatevllw', 'from (1537) and (393)', 'exanatello', 'None', 'ex-an-at-el\'-lo', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «393»; to start up out of the ground, i.e. germinate:--spring up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make spring up, cause to shoot forth<LI>to spring up</OL>'),
(1817, 'ejxanivsthmi', 'from (1537) and (450)', 'exanistemi', '1:368,60', 'ex-an-is\'-tay-mee', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «450»; objectively, to produce, i.e. (figuratively) beget; subjectively, to arise, i.e. (figuratively) object:--raise (rise) up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make to rise up, to rise up, to produce<LI>to rise (in an assembly to speak)</OL>'),
(1818, 'ejxapatavw', 'from (1537) and (538)', 'exapatao', '1:384,65', 'ex-ap-at-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «538»; to seduce wholly:--beguile, deceive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to deceive</OL>'),
(1819, 'ejxavpina', 'from (1537) and a derivative of the same as (160)', 'exapina', 'None', 'ex-ap\'-ee-nah', 'Adverb', 'from «1537» and a derivative of the same as «160»; of a sudden, i.e. unexpectedly:--suddenly. Compare «1810».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>suddenly</OL>'),
(1820, 'ejxaporevw', 'middle voice from (1537) and (639)', 'exaporeomai', 'None', 'ex-ap-or-eh\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «1537» and «639»; to be utterly at a loss, i.e. despond:--(in) despair.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be utterly at loss, be utterly destitute of measures or resources, to renounce all hope, be in despair</OL>'),
(1821, 'ejxapostevllw', 'from (1537) and (649)', 'exapostello', '1:406,67', 'ex-ap-os-tel\'-lo', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «649»; to send away forth, i.e. (on a mission) to despatch, or (peremptorily) to dismiss:--send (away, forth, out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to send forth<LI>to send away</OL>'),
(1822, 'ejxartivzw', 'from (1537) and a derivative of (739)', 'exartizo', '1:475,80', 'ex-ar-tid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and a derivative of «739»; to finish out (time); figuratively, to equip fully (a teacher):--accomplish, thoroughly furnish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to complete, finish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to furnish perfectly<LI>to finish, accomplish, (as it were, to render the days complete)</OL></OL>'),
(1823, 'ejxastravptw', 'from (1537) and (797)', 'exastrapto', 'None', 'ex-as-trap\'-to', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «797»; to lighten forth, i.e. (figuratively) to be radiant (of very white garments):--glistening.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to send forth lightning, to lighten<LI>to flash out like lightning, to shine, be radiant<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of garments</OL></OL>'),
(1824, 'ejxauth\'ß', 'from (1537) and the genitive case singular feminine of (846) ((5610) being understood)', 'exautes', 'None', 'ex-ow\'-tace', 'Adverb', 'from «1537» and the genitive case singular feminine of «846» (5610 being understood); from that hour, i.e. instantly:--by and by, immediately, presently, straightway.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>on the instant, forthwith</OL>'),
(1825, 'ejxegeivrw', 'from (1537) and (1453)', 'exegeiro', '2:338,195', 'ex-eg-i\'-ro', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «1453»; to rouse fully, i.e. (figuratively) to resuscitate (from death), release (from infliction):--raise up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to arouse, raise up (from sleep)<LI>to rouse up, stir up, incite</OL>'),
(1826, 'e[xeimi', 'from (1537) and eimi (to go)', 'exeimi', 'None', 'ex\'-i-mee', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and eimi (to go); to issue, i.e. leave (a place), escape (to the shore):--depart, get (to land), go out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go forth, go out</OL>'),
(1827, 'ejxelevgcw', 'from (1537) and (1651)', 'exelegcho', 'None', 'ex-el-eng\'-kho', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «1651»; to convict fully, i.e. (by implication) to punish:--convince.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prove to be in the wrong, convict</OL>'),
(1828, 'ejxevlkw', 'from (1537) and (1670)', 'exelko', 'None', 'ex-el\'-ko', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «1670»; to drag forth, i.e. (figuratively) to entice (to sin):--draw away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to draw out<LI>metaph. lure forth: in hunting and fishing as game is lured from its hiding place, so man by lure is allured from the safety of self-restraint to sin. In Jas 1:14, the language of the hunting is transferred to the seduction of a harlot.</OL>'),
(1829, 'ejxevrama', 'from a comparative of (1537) and a presumed erao (to spue)', 'exerama', 'None', 'ex-er\'-am-ah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a comparative of «1537» and a presumed erao (to spue); vomit, i.e. food disgorged:--vomit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vomit<LI>what is cast out by vomiting</OL>'),
(1830, 'ejxeraunavw', 'from (1537) and (2045)', 'exereunao', '2:655,255', 'ex-er-yoo-nah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «2045»; to explore (figuratively):--search diligently.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to search out, search anxiously and diligently</OL>To search after, thoroughly investigate (first used to tellof a dog sniffing out something with his nose). The prophetssearched to find out the time of Messiah\'s appearance.'),
(1831, 'ejxevrcomai', 'from (1537) and (2064)', 'exerchomai', '2:678,257', 'ex-er\'-khom-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «2064»; to issue (literally or figuratively):--come (forth, out), depart (out of), escape, get out, go (abroad, away, forth, out, thence), proceed (forth), spread abroad.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go or come forth of<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>with mention of the place out of which one goes, or the point from which he departs<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of those who leave a place of their own accord<LI>of those who are expelled or cast out</OL></OL><LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to go out of an assembly, i.e. forsake it<LI>to come forth from physically, arise from, to be born of<LI>to go forth from one\'s power, escape from it in safety<LI>to come forth (from privacy) into the world, before the public, (of those who by novelty of opinion attract attention)<LI>of things<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of reports, rumours, messages, precepts<LI>to be made known, declared<LI>to be spread, to be proclaimed<LI>to come forth 2e</OL><LI>emitted as from the heart or the mouth 2e<LI>to flow forth from the body 2e<LI>to emanate, issue 2e<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>used of a sudden flash of lightning 2e<LI>used of a thing vanishing 2e<LI>used of a hope which has disappeared</OL></OL></OL>'),
(1832, 'e[xesti', 'third person singular present indicative of a compound of (1537) and (1510)', 'exesti', '2:560,238', 'ex\'-es-tee', 'Verb', 'third person singular present indicative of a compound of «1537» and «1510»; so also   exon  ex-on\' neuter present participle of the same (with or without some form of «1510» expressed); impersonally, it is right (through the figurative idea of being out in public):--be lawful, let, × may(-est).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>it is lawful</OL>'),
(1833, 'ejxetavzw', 'from (1537) and etazo (to examine)', 'exetazo', 'None', 'ex-et-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and etazo (to examine); to test thoroughly (by questions), i.e. ascertain or interrogate:--ask, enquire, search.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to search out<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to examine strictly, enquire<LI>enquire of someone</OL></OL>'),
(1834, 'ejxhgevomai', 'from (1537) and (2233)', 'exegeomai', '2:908,303', 'ex-ayg-eh\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «1537» and «2233»; to consider out (aloud), i.e. rehearse, unfold:--declare, tell.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead out, be leader, go before<LI>metaph., to draw out in narrative, unfold a teaching<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to recount, rehearse<LI>to unfold, declare<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the things relating to God<LI>used in Greek writing of the interpretation of things sacred and divine, oracles, dreams, etc.</OL></OL></OL>'),
