(2319, 'qeostughvß', 'from (2316) and the base of (4767)', 'theostuges', 'None', 'theh-os-too-gace\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2316» and the base of «4767»; hateful to God, i.e. impious:--hater of God.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hateful to God, exceptionally impious and wicked</OL>'),
(2320, 'qeovthß', 'from (2316)', 'theotes', '3:119,322', 'theh-ot\'-ace', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2316»; divinity (abstractly):--godhead.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>deity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the state of being God, Godhead</OL></OL>'),
(2321, 'Qeovfiloß', 'from (2316) and (5384)', 'Theophilos', 'None', 'theh-of\'-il-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2316» and «5384»; friend of God; Theophilus, a Christian:--Theophilus.', 'Theophilus = \"friend of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the person to whom Luke addressed his Gospel and the book of Acts</OL>'),
(2322, 'qerapeiva', 'from (2323)', 'therapeia', '3:131,331', 'ther-ap-i\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2323»; attendance (specially, medical, i.e. cure); figuratively and collectively, domestics:--healing, household.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>service rendered by one to another<LI>spec. medical service: curing, healing<LI>household service<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>body of attendants, servants, domestics</OL></OL>'),
(2323, 'qerapeuvw', 'from the same as (2324)', 'therapeuo', '3:128,331', 'ther-ap-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from the same as «2324»; to wait upon menially, i.e. (figuratively) to adore (God), or (specially) to relieve (of disease):--cure, heal, worship.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to serve, do service<LI>to heal, cure, restore to health</OL>'),
(2324, 'qeravpwn', 'apparently a participle from an otherwise obsolete derivative of the base of (2330)', 'therapon', '3:132,331', 'ther-ap\'-ohn', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently a participle from an otherwise obsolete derivative of the base of «2330»; a menial attendant (as if cherishing):--servant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an attendant, servant: of God<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>spoken of Moses discharging the duties committed to him by God</OL></OL>'),
(2325, 'qerivzw', 'from (2330) (in the sense of the crop)', 'therizo', '3:132,332', 'ther-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2330» (in the sense of the crop); to harvest:--reap.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to reap, harvest<LI>proverbial expression for sowing and reaping<LI>cut off, destroy<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as crops are cut down with a sickle</OL></OL>'),
(2326, 'qerismovß', 'from (2325)', 'therismos', '3:133,332', 'ther-is-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2325»; reaping, i.e. the crop:--harvest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>harvest, the act of reaping<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fig. of the gathering of men into the kingdom of God<LI>referring to time of reaping, the final judgment, when the righteous are gathered into the kingdom of God and the wicked are cast into hell for ever</OL></OL>'),
(2327, 'qeristhvß', 'from (2325)', 'theristes', 'None', 'ther-is-tace\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2325»; a harvester:--reaper.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a reaper</OL>'),
(2328, 'qermaivnw', 'from (2329)', 'thermaino', 'None', 'ther-mah\'-ee-no', 'Verb', 'from «2329»; to heat (oneself):--(be) warm(-ed, self).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make warm, to heat<LI>to warm one\'s self</OL>'),
(2329, 'qevrmh', 'from the base of (2330)', 'therme', 'None', 'ther\'-may', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the base of «2330»; warmth:--heat.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>heat</OL>'),
(2330, 'qevroß', 'from a primary thero (to heat)', 'theros', 'None', 'ther\'-os', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a primary thero (to heat); properly, heat, i.e. summer:--summer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>summer</OL>'),
(2331, 'Qessalonikeuvß', 'from (2332)', 'Thessalonikeus', 'None', 'thes-sal-on-ik-yoos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2332»; a Thessalonican, i.e. inhabitant of Thessalonice:--Thessalonian.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Thessalonians</OL>'),
(2332, 'Qessalonivkh', 'from Thessalos (a Thessalian) and (3529)', 'Thessalonike', 'None', 'thes-sal-on-ee\'-kay', 'Noun Location', 'from Thessalos (a Thessalian) and «3529»; Thessalonice, a place in Asia Minor:--Thessalonica.', 'Thessalonica = \"victory of falsity\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a famous and populous city, situated on the Thermaic Gulf, the capital of the second division of Macedonia and the residence of a Roman governor and quaestor</OL>'),
(2333, 'Qeuda\'ß', 'of uncertain origin', 'Theudas', 'None', 'thyoo-das\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain origin; Theudas, an Israelite:--Theudas.', 'Theudas = \"God-given\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name of an insurgent mentioned in Gamaliel\'s speech before the Jewish council, Acts 5:35-39, at the time of the arraignment of the apostles. He appeared, according to Luke\'s account, at the head of about four hundred men. He was probably one of the insurrectionary chiefs or fanatics by whom the land was overrun in the last year of Herod\'s reign. Josephus speaks of a Theudas who played a similar part at the time of Claudius, about A.D. 44; but the Theudas mentioned by Luke must be a different person from the one spoken of by Josephus.</OL>'),
(2334, 'qewrevw', 'from a derivative of (2300) (perhaps by add. of (3708))', 'theoreo', '5:315,706', 'theh-o-reh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a derivative of «2300» (perhaps by addition of «3708»); to be a spectator of, i.e. discern, (literally, figuratively (experience) or intensively (acknowledge)):--behold, consider, look on, perceive, see. Compare «3700».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be a spectator, look at, behold<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to view attentively, take a view of, survey<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to view mentally, consider</OL></OL><LI>to see<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to perceive with the eyes, to enjoy the presence of one<LI>to discern, descry<LI>to ascertain, find out by seeing</OL></OL>'),
(2335, 'qewriva', 'from the same as (2334)', 'theoria', 'None', 'theh-o-ree\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «2334»; spectatorship, i.e. (concretely) a spectacle:--sight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a viewing, beholding<LI>that which is viewed, a spectacle, sight</OL>'),
(2336, 'qhvkh', 'from (5087)', 'theke', 'None', 'thay\'-kay', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «5087»; a receptacle, i.e. scabbard:--sheath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that which a thing is put or laid away, a receptacle, repository, chest, box<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used of the sheath of a sword</OL></OL>'),
(2337, 'qhlavzw', 'from thele (the nipple)', 'thelazo', 'None', 'thay-lad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from thele (the nipple); to suckle, (by implication) to suck:--(give) suck(-ling).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give the breast, give suck, to suckle<LI>to suck</OL>'),
(2338, 'qh\'luß', 'from the same as (2337)', 'thelus', 'None', 'thay\'-loos', 'Adjective', 'from the same as «2337»; female:--female, woman.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of the female sex<LI>a woman, a female</OL>'),
(2339, 'qhvra', 'from ther (a wild animal, as game)', 'thera', 'None', 'thay\'-rah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from ther (a wild animal, as game); hunting, i.e. (figuratively) destruction:--trap.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a hunting of wild beasts to destroy them<LI>metaph. of preparing destruction for men</OL>'),
(2340, 'qhreuvw', 'from (2339)', 'thereuo', 'None', 'thay-ryoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2339»; to hunt (an animal), i.e. (figuratively) to carp at:--catch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go a hunting, to hunt, to catch in hunting<LI>metaph. to lay wait for, strive to ensnare, catch artfully</OL>'),
(2341, 'qhriomacevw', 'from a compound of (2342) and (3164)', 'theriomacheo', 'None', 'thay-ree-om-akh-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a compound of «2342» and «3164»; to be a beast-fighter (in the gladiatorial show), i.e. (figuratively) to encounter (furious men):--fight with wild beasts.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fight with wild beasts</OL>'),
(2342, 'qhrivon', 'diminutive from the same as (2339)', 'therion', '3:133,333', 'thay-ree\'-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'diminutive from the same as «2339»; a dangerous animal:--(venomous, wild) beast.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an animal<LI>a wild animal, wild beast, beast<LI>metaph. a brutal, bestial man, savage, ferocious</OL>'),
(2343, 'qhsaurivzw', 'from (2344)', 'thesaurizo', '3:138,333', 'thay-sow-rid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2344»; to amass or reserve (literally or figuratively):--lay up (treasure), (keep) in store, (heap) treasure (together, up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to gather and lay up, to heap up, store up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to accumulate riches<LI>to keep in store, store up, reserve</OL><LI>metaph. so to live from day to day as to increase either the bitterness or the happiness of one\'s consequent lot</OL>'),
(2344, 'qhsaurovß', 'from (5087)', 'thesauros', '3:136,333', 'thay-sow-ros\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5087»; a deposit, i.e. wealth (literally or figuratively):--treasure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the place in which good and precious things are collected and laid up<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a casket, coffer, or other receptacle, in which valuables are kept<LI>a treasury<LI>storehouse, repository, magazine</OL><LI>the things laid up in a treasury, collected treasures</OL>'),
(2345, 'qiggavnw', 'a prolonged form of an obsolete primary thigo (to finger)', 'thiggano', 'None', 'thing-gan\'-o', 'Verb', 'a prolonged form of an obsolete primary thigo (to finger); to manipulate, i.e. have to do with; by implication, to injure:--handle, touch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to touch, handle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to do violence to, injury</OL></OL>'),
(2346, 'qlivbw', 'akin to the base of (5147)', 'thlibo', '3:139,334', 'thlee\'-bo', 'Verb', 'akin to the base of «5147»; to crowd (literally or figuratively):--afflict, narrow, throng, suffer tribulation, trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to press (as grapes), press hard upon<LI>a compressed way<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>narrow straitened, contracted</OL><LI>metaph. to trouble, afflict, distress</OL>'),
(2347, 'qli\'yiß', 'from (2346)', 'thlipsis', '3:139,334', 'thlip\'-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2346»; pressure (literally or figuratively):--afflicted(-tion), anguish, burdened, persecution, tribulation, trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a pressing, pressing together, pressure<LI>metaph. oppression, affliction, tribulation, distress, straits</OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2348, 'qnhv/skw', 'a strengthened form of a simpler primary thano {than\'-o} (which is used for it only in certain tenses)', 'thnesko', '3:7,312', 'thnay\'-sko', 'Verb', 'a strengthened form of a simpler primary thano than\'-o (which is used for it only in certain tenses); to die (literally or figuratively):--be dead, die.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to die, to be dead<LI>metaph. to be spiritually dead</OL>'),
(2349, 'qnhtovß', 'from (2348)', 'thnetos', '3:21,312', 'thnay-tos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2348»; liable to die:--mortal(-ity).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>liable to death, mortal</OL>'),
(2350, 'qorubavzw', 'from (2351)', 'thorubeo', 'None', 'thor-oo-beh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2351»; to be in tumult, i.e. disturb, clamor:--make ado (a noise), trouble self, set on an uproar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make a noise or uproar, be turbulent<LI>to disturb, throw into confusion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be troubled in mind<LI>to wail tumultuously</OL></OL>'),
(2351, 'qovruboß', 'from the base of (2360)', 'thorubos', 'None', 'thor\'-oo-bos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the base of «2360»; a disturbance:--tumult, uproar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a noise, tumult, uproar<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of persons wailing<LI>of a clamorous and excited multitude<LI>of riotous persons</OL><LI>a tumult, as a breach of public order</OL>'),
(2352, 'qrauvw', 'a root word', 'thrauo', 'None', 'throw\'-o', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to crush:--bruise. Compare «4486».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break, break in pieces, shatter, smite through</OL>'),
(2353, 'qrevmma', 'from (5142)', 'thremma', 'None', 'threm\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «5142»; stock (as raised on a farm):--cattle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>whatever is fed or nursed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a ward, nursling, child</OL><LI>a flock, cattle, esp. sheep and goats</OL>'),
(2354, 'qrhnevw', 'from (2355)', 'threneo', '3:148,335', 'thray-neh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2355»; to bewail:--lament, mourn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mourn, to lament<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of singers of dirges, [to wail]</OL><LI>to bewail, deplore</OL>'),
(2355, 'qrh\'noß', 'from the base of (2360)', 'threnos', '3:148,335', 'thray\'-nos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the base of «2360»; wailing:--lamentation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a lamentation</OL>'),
(2356, 'qrhskeiva', 'from a derivative of (2357)', 'threskeia', '3:155,337', 'thrace-ki\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a derivative of «2357»; ceremonial observance:--religion, worshipping.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>religious worship<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>esp. external, that which consists of ceremonies<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>religious discipline, religion</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2357, 'qrh\'skoß', 'probably from the base of (2360)', 'threskos', '3:155,337', 'thrace\'-kos', 'Adjective', 'probably from the base of «2360»; ceremonious in worship (as demonstrative), i.e. pious:--religious.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fearing or worshipping God<LI>to tremble<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>trembling, fearful</OL></OL>'),
(2358, 'qriambeuvw', 'from a prolonged compound of the base of (2360)', 'thriambeuo', '3:159,337', 'three-am-byoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a prolonged compound of the base of «2360»; and a derivative of «680» (meaning a noisy iambus, sung in honor of Bacchus); to make an acclamatory procession, i.e. (figuratively) to conquer or (by Hebraism) to give victory:--(cause) to triumph (over).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to triumph, to celebrate a triumph<LI>cause one to triumph</OL>'),
(2359, 'qrivx', 'genitive case trichos, etc., of uncertain derivation', 'thrix', 'None', 'threeks', 'Noun Feminine', 'genitive case trichos, etc.; of uncertain derivation; hair:--hair. Compare «2864».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the hair of the head<LI>the hair of animals</OL>'),
(2360, 'qroevw', 'from threomai {to wail}', 'throeo', 'None', 'thro-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from threomai to wail; to clamor, i.e. (by implication) to frighten:--trouble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cry aloud, make a noise by outcry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in the NT, to trouble, frighten<LI>to be troubled in mind, to be frightened, alarmed</OL></OL>'),
(2361, 'qrovmboß', 'perhaps from (5142) (in the sense of thickening)', 'thrombos', 'None', 'throm\'-bos', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps from «5142» (in the sense of thickening); a clot:--great drop.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a large thick drop, esp. of clotted blood</OL>'),
(2362, 'qrovnoß', 'from thrao (to sit), a stately seat (\"throne\")', 'thronos', '3:160,338', 'thron\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from thrao (to sit); a stately seat (\"throne\"); by implication, power or (concretely) a potentate:--seat, throne.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a throne seat<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a chair of state having a footstool<LI>assigned in the NT to kings, hence, kingly power or royalty<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>metaph. to God, the governor of the world<LI>to the Messiah, Christ, the partner and assistant in the divine administration 1b</OL><LI>hence divine power belonging to Christ<OL TYPE=\"3\"><LI>to judges i.e. tribunal or bench<LI>to elders</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2363, 'Quavteira', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Thuateira', 'None', 'thoo-at\'-i-rah', 'Noun Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Thyatira, a place in Asia Minor:--Thyatira.', 'Thyatira = \"odour of affliction\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a colony of Macedonia Greeks, situated between Sardis and Pergamos on the river Lycus; its inhabitants gained their living by traffic and the art of dyeing in purple</OL>'),
(2364, 'qugavthr', 'apparently a root word [cf \"daughter\"]', 'thugater', 'None', 'thoo-gat\'-air', 'Noun Feminine', 'apparently a primary word (compare \"daughter\"); a female child, or (by Hebraism) descendant (or inhabitant):--daughter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a daughter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a daughter of God<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>acceptable to God, rejoicing in God\'s peculiar care and protection</OL><LI>with the name of a place, city, or region<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>denotes collectively all its inhabitants and citizens</OL><LI>a female descendant</OL></OL>'),
(2365, 'qugavtrion', 'from (2364)', 'thugatrion', 'None', 'thoo-gat\'-ree-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2364»; a daughterling:--little (young) daughter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a little daughter</OL>'),
(2366, 'quvella', 'from (2380) (in the sense of blowing)', 'thuella', 'None', 'thoo\'-el-lah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2380» (in the sense of blowing) a storm:--tempest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a sudden storm, tempest, whirlwind</OL>'),
(2367, 'quvi>noß', 'from a derivative of (2380) (in the sense of blowing, denoting a certain fragrant tree)', 'thuinos', 'None', 'thoo\'-ee-nos', 'Adjective', 'from a derivative of «2380» (in the sense of blowing; denoting a certain fragrant tree); made of citron-wood:--thyine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the citrus, an odoriferous North African tree used as incense, prized by the ancient Greeks and Romans on account of the beauty of its wood for various ornamental purposes</OL>'),
(2368, 'qumivama', 'from (2370)', 'thumiama', 'None', 'thoo-mee\'-am-ah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2370»; an aroma, i.e. fragrant powder burnt in religious service; by implication, the burning itself:--incense, odour.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an aromatic substance burnt, incense</OL>'),
(2369, 'qumiathvrion', 'from a derivative of (2370)', 'thumiasterion', 'None', 'thoo-mee-as-tay\'-ree-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a derivative of «2370»; a place of fumigation, i.e. the alter of incense (in the Temple):--censer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a utensil for fumigating or burning incense<LI>an altar of incense</OL>'),
(2370, 'qumiavw', 'from a derivative of (2380) (in the sense of smoking)', 'thumiao', 'None', 'thoo-mee-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a derivative of «2380» (in the sense of smoking); to fumigate, i.e. offer aromatic fumes:--burn incense.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to burn incense</OL>'),
(2371, 'qumomacevw', 'from a presumed compound of (2372) and (3164)', 'thumomacheo', 'None', 'thoo-mom-akh-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a presumed compound of «2372» and «3164»; to be in a furious fight, i.e. (figuratively) to be exasperated:--be highly displeased.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to carry on war with great animosity<LI>to be very angry, be exasperated</OL>'),
(2372, 'qumovß', 'from (2380)', 'thumos', '3:167,339', 'thoo-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2380»; passion (as if breathing hard):--fierceness, indignation, wrath. Compare «5590».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>passion, angry, heat, anger forthwith boiling up and soon subsiding again<LI>glow, ardour, the wine of passion, inflaming wine (which either drives the drinker mad or kills him with its strength)</OL>'),
(2373, 'qumovw', 'from (2372)', 'thumoo', 'None', 'tho-mo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2372»; to put in a passion, i.e. enrage:--be wroth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause one to become incensed, to provoke to anger<LI>to be wroth</OL>'),
(2374, 'quvra', 'apparently a root word [cf \"door\"]', 'thura', '3:173,340', 'thoo\'-rah', 'Noun Feminine', 'apparently a primary word (compare \"door\"); a portal or entrance (the opening or the closure, literally or figuratively):--door, gate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a door<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the vestibule<LI>used of any opening like a door, an entrance, way or passage into<LI>in a parable or metaphor<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the door through which sheep go in and out, the name of him who brings salvation to those who follow his guidance<LI>\"an open door\" is used of the opportunity of doing something<LI>the door of the kingdom of heaven (likened to a palace) denotes the conditions which must be complied with in order to be received into the kingdom of God</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2375, 'qureovß', 'from (2374)', 'thureos', '5:312,702', 'thoo-reh-os\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2374»; a large shield (as door-shaped):--shield.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a shield, a large oblong, four cornered shield</OL>'),
(2376, 'qurivß', 'from (2374)', 'thuris', 'None', 'thoo-rece\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2374»; an aperture, i.e. window:--window.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a window</OL>'),
(2377, 'qurwrovß', 'from (2374) and ouros (a watcher)', 'thuroros', 'None', 'thoo-ro-ros\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2374» and ouros (a watcher); a gate- warden:--that kept the door, porter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a doorkeeper, porter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a male or female janitor</OL></OL>'),
(2378, 'qusiva', 'from (2380)', 'thusia', '3:180,342', 'thoo-see\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2380»; sacrifice (the act or the victim, literally or figuratively):--sacrifice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a sacrifice, victim</OL>'),
(2379, 'qusiasthvrion', 'from a derivative of (2378)', 'thusiasterion', '3:180,342', 'thoo-see-as-tay\'-ree-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a derivative of «2378»; a place of sacrifice, i.e. an altar (special or genitive case, literal or figurative):--altar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the altar for slaying and burning of victims used of<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the altar of whole burnt offerings which stood in the court of the priests in the temple at Jerusalem<LI>the altar of incense which stood in the sanctuary or the Holy Place<LI>any other altar<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>metaph., the cross on which Christ suffered an expiatory death: to eat of this altar i.e. to appropriate to one\'s self the fruits of Christ\'s expiatory death</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2380, 'quvw', 'a root word', 'thuo', '3:180,342', 'thoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; properly, to rush (breathe hard, blow, smoke), i.e. (by implication) to sacrifice (properly, by fire, but genitive case); by extension to immolate (slaughter for any purpose):--kill, (do) sacrifice, slay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sacrifice, immolate<LI>to slay, kill<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the paschal lamb</OL><LI>slaughter</OL>'),
(2381, 'Qwma\'ß', 'of Aramaic origin, cf (08380)', 'Thomas', 'None', 'tho-mas\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Chaldee origin (compare «08380»); the twin; Thomas, a Christian:--Thomas.', 'Thomas = \"a twin\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the apostles</OL>'),
(2382, 'qwvrax', 'of uncertain affinity', 'thorax', '5:308,702', 'tho\'-rax', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain affinity; the chest (\"thorax\"), i.e. (by implication) a corslet:--breast-plate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the breast, the part of the body from the neck to the navel, where the ribs end<LI>a breastplate or corset consisting of two parts and protecting the body on both sides from the neck to the middle</OL>'),
(2383, 'ÅIavi>roß', 'of Hebrew origin (02971)', 'Iaeiros', 'None', 'ee-ah\'-i-ros', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («02971»); Jairus (i.e. Jair), an Israelite:--Jairus.', 'Jairus = \"whom God enlightens\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a ruler of a synagogue, probably near the western shore of the Sea of Galilee</OL>'),
(2384, 'ÅIakwvb', 'of Hebrew origin (03290)', 'Iakob', '*,344', 'ee-ak-obe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03290»); Jacob (i.e. Ja`akob), the progenitor of the Israelites:--also an Israelite:--Jacob.', 'Jacob = \"heel-catcher or supplanter\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>was the second son of Isaac<LI>the father of Joseph, the husband of Mary</OL>'),
