(2409, 'iJereuvß', 'from (2413)', 'hiereus', '3:257,349', 'hee-er-yooce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2413»; a priest (literally or figuratively):--(high) priest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a priest, one who offers sacrifices and in general in busied with sacred rites<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>referring to priests of Gentiles or the Jews,</OL><LI>metaph. of Christians, because, purified by the blood of Christ and brought into close intercourse with God, they devote their life to him alone and to Christ</OL>'),
(2410, 'ÅIericwv', 'of Hebrew origin (03405)', 'Hiericho', 'None', 'hee-er-ee-kho\'', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin («03405»); Jericho, a place in Palestine:--Jericho.', 'Jericho = \"place of fragrance\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a noted city, abounding in balsam, honey, cyprus, myrobalanus, roses and other fragrant products. It was near the north shore of the Dead Sea in the tribe of Benjamin, between Jerusalem and the Jordan River</OL>'),
