(2442, 'iJmeivromai', 'middle voice from himeros (a yearning, of uncertain affinity)', 'himeiromai', '5:176,*', 'him-i\'-rom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from himeros (a yearning; of uncertain affinity); to long for:--be affectionately desirous.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to desire, long for, esp. the longing of love</OL>'),
(2443, 'i&na', 'probably from the same as the former part of (1438) (through the demonstrative idea, cf (3588))', 'hina', '3:323,366', 'hin\'-ah', 'Conjunction', 'probably from the same as the former part of «1438» (through the demonstrative idea; compare «3588»); in order that (denoting the purpose or the result):--albeit, because, to the intent (that), lest, so as, (so) that, (for) to. Compare «3363».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that, in order that, so that</OL>Wigram\'s frequency count is 569 not 621. The original J.B. Smithcount is 665 but this includes many places where the word isassigned a different Strong\'s number because it is used in a phrase.'),
(2444, 'iJnativ', 'from (2443) and (5101)', 'hinati', 'None', 'hin-at-ee\'', 'Conjunction', 'from «2443» and «5101»; for what reason ?, i.e. why?:--wherefore, why.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>for what purpose, wherefore, why</OL>'),
(2445, 'ÅIovpph', 'of Hebrew origin (03305)', 'Ioppe', 'None', 'ee-op\'-pay', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin («03305»); Joppe (i.e. Japho), a place in Palestine:--Joppa.', 'Joppa or Japho = \"beautiful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city of Palestine on the Mediterranean, lying on the border of the tribes of Dan and Ephraim. It was subject to the Jews from the times of the Maccabees. It had a famous but dangerous port and carried on a flourishing trade. It is now called Jaffa.</OL>'),
(2446, 'ÅIordavnhß', 'of Hebrew origin (03383)', 'Iordanes', '6:608,921', 'ee-or-dan\'-ace', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin («03383»); the Jordanes (i.e. Jarden), a river of Palestine:--Jordan.', 'Jordan = \"the descender\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the one river of Palestine, has its course of little more than 200 miles (300 km), from the roots of Anti-Lebanon to the head of the Dead Sea.</OL>'),
(2447, 'ijovß', 'perhaps from eimi (to go) or hiemi (to send)', 'ios', '3:334,368', 'ee-os\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps from eimi (to go) or hiemi (to send); rust (as if emitted by metals); also venom (as emitted by serpents):--poison, rust.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>poison (of animals)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>poison of asps is under their lips,<LI>spoken of men given to reviling and calumniating and thereby injuring others</OL><LI>rust</OL>'),
(2448, 'ÅIouvda', 'of Hebrew origin (03063) or perhaps (03194)', 'Iouda', 'None', 'ee-oo-dah\'', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin (3063 or perhaps «03194»); Judah (i.e. Jehudah or Juttah), a part of (or place in) Palestine:--Judah.', 'Judah = \"he shall be praised\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the fourth son of the patriarch Jacob<LI>the tribe that were the offspring of Judah<LI>the region occupied by the tribe<LI>a city of the tribe of Judah, conjectured to be Hebron, which was a city assigned to the priests and located in the hill country, and the native place of John the Baptist according to Jewish tradition</OL>'),
(2449, 'ÅIoudaiva', 'feminine of (2453) (with (1093) implied)', 'Ioudaia', '3:356,372', 'ee-oo-dah\'-yah', 'Noun Location', 'feminine of «2453» (with «1093» implied); the Judaean land (i.e. Judaea), a region of Palestine:--Judaea.', 'Judaea = \"he shall be praised\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in a narrower sense, to the southern portion of Palestine lying on this side of the Jordan and the Dead Sea, to distinguish it from Samaria, Galilee, Peraea, and Idumaea<LI>in a broader sense, referring to all Palestine</OL>'),
(2450, 'ÅIoudai?zw', 'from (2453)', 'Ioudaizo', '3:356,372', 'ee-oo-dah-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2453»; to become a Judaean, i.e. \"Judaize\":--live as the Jews.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to adopt Jewish customs and rites, imitate the Jews, Judaise<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>one who observes the ritual law of the Jews</OL></OL>'),
(2451, 'ÅIoudai>kovß', 'from (2453)', 'Ioudaikos', '3:356,372', 'ee-oo-dah-ee-kos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2453»; Judaic, i.e. resembling a Judaean:--Jewish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Jewish</OL>'),
(2452, 'ÅIoudai>kw\'ß', 'from (2451)', 'Ioudaikos', 'None', 'ee-oo-dah-ee-koce\'', 'Adverb', 'adverb from «2451»; Judaically or in a manner resembling a Judaean:--as do the Jews.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Jewishly, after the manner of the Jews</OL>'),
(2453, 'ÅIoudai\'oß', 'from (2448) (in the sense of (2455) as a country)', 'Ioudaios', '3:356,372', 'ee-oo-dah\'-yos', 'Adjective', 'from «2448» (in the sense of «2455» as a country); Judaean, i.e. belonging to Jehudah:--Jew(-ess), of Judaea.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Jewish, belonging to the Jewish nation<LI>Jewish as respects to birth, origin, religion</OL>'),
(2454, 'ÅIoudai>smovß', 'from (2450)', 'Ioudaismos', '3:356,372', 'ee-oo-dah-is-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2450»; \"Judaism\", i.e. the Jewish faith and usages:--Jews\' religion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the Jewish faith and worship, religion of the Jews, Judaism</OL>'),
(2455, 'ÅIouvdaß', 'of Hebrew origin (03063)', 'Ioudas', 'None', 'ee-oo-das\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03063»); Judas (i.e. Jehudah), the name of ten Israelites; also of the posterity of one of them and its region:--Juda(-h, -s); Jude.', 'Judah or Judas = \"he shall be praised\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the fourth son of Jacob<LI>an unknown ancestor of Christ<LI>a man surnamed the Galilean, who at the time of the census of Quirinus, excited the revolt in Galilee, Acts 5:<LI>a certain Jew of Damascus, Acts 9:<LI>a prophet surnamed Barsabas, of the church at Jerusalem, Acts 15:22,27,<LI>the apostle, Jn 14:22, who was surnamed Lebbaeus or Thaddaeus, and according to opinion wrote the Epistle of Jude.<LI>the half-brother of Jesus, Mt. 13:<LI>Judas Iscariot, the apostle who betrayed Jesus</OL>'),
(2456, 'ÅIouliva', 'feminine of the same as (2457)', 'Ioulia', 'None', 'ee-oo-lee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of the same as «2457»; Julia, a Christian woman:--Julia.', 'Julia = \"soft haired\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Christian woman</OL>'),
(2457, 'ÅIouvlioß', 'of Latin origin', 'Ioulios', 'None', 'ee-oo\'-lee-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; Julius, a centurion:--Julius.', 'Julius = \"soft-haired\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the centurion of \"Augustus Band\", to whose charge Paul was delivered when he was sent prisoner from Caesarea to Rome</OL>'),
(2458, 'ÅIounia\'ß', 'of Latin origin', 'Iounias', 'None', 'ee-oo-nee\'-as', 'Noun Feminine', 'of Latin origin; Junias, a Christian:--Junias.', 'Junia = \"youthful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Christian woman at Rome, mentioned by Paul as one of his kinsfolk and fellow prisoners</OL>'),
(2459, 'ÅIou\'stoß', 'of Latin origin (\"just\")', 'Ioustos', 'None', 'ee-ooce\'-tos', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin (\"just\"); Justus, the name of three Christian:--Justus.', 'Justus = \"just\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a surname of Joseph, called Barsabas. Acts 1:<LI>of Titus, a Christian at Corinth, with whom Paul lodged. Acts 18:<LI>a surname of Jesus, a friend of Paul. Col. 4:11</OL>'),
(2460, 'iJppeuvß', 'from (2462)', 'hippeus', 'None', 'hip-yooce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2462»; an equestrian, i.e. member of a cavalry corps:--horseman.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a horseman</OL>'),
(2461, 'iJppikovß', 'neuter of a derivative of (2462)', 'hippikon', 'None', 'hip-pee-kon\'', 'Adjective', 'neuter of a derivative of «2462»; the cavalry force:--horse(-men).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>equestrian, the horse(men), cavalry</OL>'),
(2462, 'i&ppoß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'hippos', '3:336,369', 'hip\'-pos', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain affinity; a horse:--horse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a horse</OL>'),
(2463, 'i\\riß', 'perhaps from (2046) (as a symbol of the female messenger of the pagan deities)', 'iris', '3:339,369', 'ee\'-ris', 'Noun Feminine', 'perhaps from «2046» (as a symbol of the female messenger of the pagan deities); a rainbow (\"iris\"):--rainbow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a rainbow</OL>'),
(2464, 'ÅIsaavk', 'of Hebrew origin (03327)', 'Isaak', 'TDNT 3:191,*', 'ee-sah-ak\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03327»); Isaac (i.e. Jitschak), the son of Abraham:--Isaac.', 'Isaac = \"to laugh\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Abraham and Sarah</OL>'),
(2465, 'ijsavggeloß', 'from (2470) and (32)', 'isaggelos', '1:87,12', 'ee-sang\'-el-los', 'Adjective', 'from «2470» and «32»; like an angel, i.e. angelic:--equal unto the angels.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>like the angels</OL>'),
(2466, 'ÅIsacavr', 'of Hebrew origin (03485)', 'Isachar', 'None', 'ee-sakh-ar\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03485»); Isachar (i.e. Jissaskar), a son of Jacob (figuratively, his descendant):--Issachar.', 'Issachar = \"reward\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the ninth son of Jacob and the fifth of Leah</OL>'),
(2467, 'assumed by some as the base of cert. irregular forms of (1942)', 'Isemi', 'isemi', 'is\'-ay-mee', 'is\'-ay-mee', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to know</OL>', 'assumed by some as the base of certain irregular forms of «1942»; to know:--know.', ''),
(2468, 'i[sqi', 'second person imperative present of (1510)', 'isthi', 'None', 'is\'-thee', 'Verb', 'second person imperative present of «1510»; be thou:--+ agree, be, × give thyself wholly to.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>be thou</OL>'),
(2469, 'ÅIskariwvthß', 'of Hebrew origin probably (0377) and (07149)', 'Iskariotes', 'None', 'is-kar-ee-o\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin (probably «0377» and «07149»); inhabitant of Kerioth; Iscariotes (i.e. Keriothite), an epithet of Judas the traitor:--Iscariot.', 'Iscariot = \"men of Kerioth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the apostle who betrayed Jesus</OL>'),
(2470, 'i[soß', 'probably from (1492) (through the idea of seeming)', 'isos', '3:343,370', 'ee\'-sos', 'Adjective', 'probably from «1492» (through the idea of seeming); similar (in amount and kind):--+ agree, as much, equal, like.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>equal, in quantity or quality</OL>'),
(2471, 'ijsovthß', 'likeness (in condition or proportion)', 'isotes', '3:343,370', 'ee-sot\'-ace', 'Noun Feminine', 'likeness (in condition or proportion); by implication, equity:--equal(-ity).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>equality<LI>equity, fairness, what is equitable</OL>'),
(2472, 'ijsovtimoß', 'from (2470) and (5092)', 'isotimos', '3:343,370', 'ee-sot\'-ee-mos', 'Adjective', 'from «2470» and «5092»; of equal value or honor:--like precious.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>equally precious<LI>equally honoured, to be esteemed equal to</OL>'),
(2473, 'ijsovyucoß', 'from (2470) and (5590)', 'isopsuchos', 'None', 'ee-sop\'-soo-khos', 'Adjective', 'from «2470» and «5590»; of similar spirit:--likeminded.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>equal in soul</OL>'),
(2474, 'ÅIsrahvl', 'of Hebrew origin (03478)', 'Israel', '3:356,372', 'is-rah-ale\'', 'Adjective', 'of Hebrew origin («03478»); Israel (i.e. Jisrael), the adopted name of Jacob, including his descendants (literally or figuratively):--Israel.', 'Israel = \"he shall be a prince of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name given to the patriarch Jacob (and borne by him in addition to his former name)<LI>the family or descendants of Israel, the nation of Israel<LI>Christians, the Israel of God (Gal 6:<LI></OL>'),
(2475, 'ÅIsrahlivthß', 'from (2474)', 'Israelites', '3:356,372', 'is-rah-ale-ee\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2474»; an \"Israelite\", i.e. descendant of Israel (literally or figuratively):--Israelite.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an Israelite, one of the nation of Israel, a name to be held in honour</OL>'),
(2476, 'i&sthmi', 'a prolonged form of a primary stao {stah\'-o} (of the same meaning, and used for it in certain tenses)', 'histemi', '7:638,1082', 'his\'-tay-mee', 'Verb', 'a prolonged form of a primary stao stah\'-o (of the same meaning, and used for it in certain tenses); to stand (transitively or intransitively), used in various applications (literally or figuratively):--abide, appoint, bring, continue, covenant, establish, hold up, lay, present, set (up), stanch, stand (by, forth, still, up). Compare «5087».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause or make to stand, to place, put, set<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to bid to stand by, [set up]<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in the presence of others, in the midst, before judges, before members of the Sanhedrin;<LI>to place</OL><LI>to make firm, fix establish<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause a person or a thing to keep his or its place<LI>to stand, be kept intact (of family, a kingdom), to escape in safety<LI>to establish a thing, cause it to stand 1b</OL></OL><LI>to uphold or sustain the authority or force of anything<OL TYPE=\"c\"><LI>to set or place in a balance<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to weigh: money to one (because in very early times before the introduction of coinage, the metals used to be weighed)</OL></OL><LI>to stand<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to stand by or near<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stop, stand still, to stand immovable, stand firm 2a</OL><LI>of the foundation of a building<LI>to stand<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>continue safe and sound, stand unharmed, to stand ready or prepared<LI>to be of a steadfast mind<LI>of quality, one who does not hesitate, does not waiver</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2477, 'iJstorevw', 'from a derivative of (1492)', 'historeo', '3:391,377', 'his-tor-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a derivative of «1492»; to be knowing (learned), i.e. (by implication) to visit for information (interview):--see.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to enquire into, examine, investigate<LI>to find out, learn, by enquiry<LI>to gain knowledge of by visiting<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of some distinguished person, to become personally acquainted with, know face to face</OL></OL>'),
(2478, 'ijscurovß', 'from (2479)', 'ischuros', '3:397,378', 'is-khoo-ros\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2479»; forcible (literally or figuratively):--boisterous, mighty(-ier), powerful, strong(-er, man), valiant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strong, mighty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of living beings<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strong either in body or in mind<LI>of one who has strength of soul to sustain the attacks of Satan, strong and therefore exhibiting many excellences</OL><LI>on inanimate things<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>strong, violent, forcibly uttered, firm, sure</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2479, 'ijscuvß', 'from a derivative of is (force, cf eschon, a form of (2192))', 'ischus', '3:397,378', 'is-khoos\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a derivative of is (force; compare eschon, a form of «2192»); forcefulness (literally or figuratively):--ability, might(-ily), power, strength.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ability, force, strength, might</OL>'),
(2480, 'ijscuvw', 'from (2479)', 'ischuo', '3:397,378', 'is-khoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2479»; to have (or exercise) force (literally or figuratively):--be able, avail, can do(-not), could, be good, might, prevail, be of strength, be whole, + much work.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be strong<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be strong in body, to be robust, to be in sound health</OL><LI>to have power<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to have power as shown by extraordinary deeds<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to exert, wield power, to have strength to overcome</OL><LI>to be a force, avail<LI>to be serviceable<LI>to be able, can</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2481, 'i[swß', 'from (2470)', 'isos', 'None', 'ee\'-soce', 'Adverb', 'adverb from «2470»; likely, i.e. perhaps:--it may be.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>equally, in like manner<LI>agreeably to expectation, i.e. it may be, probably</OL>'),
(2482, 'ÅItaliva', 'probably of foreign origin', 'Italia', 'None', 'ee-tal-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Location', 'probably of foreign origin; Italia, a region of Europe:--Italy.', 'Italy = \"calf like\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the whole peninsula between the Alps and the Straits of Messina</OL>'),
(2483, 'ÅItalikovß', 'from (2482)', 'Italikos', 'None', 'ee-tal-ee-kos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2482»; Italic, i.e. belonging to Italia:--Italian.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Italian</OL>'),
(2484, 'ÅItourai\'oß', 'of Hebrew origin (03195)', 'Itouraia', 'None', 'ee-too-rah\'-yah', 'Adjective', 'of Hebrew origin («03195»); Ituraea (i.e. Jetur), a region of Palestine:--Ituraea.', 'Ituraea = \"past the limits\" or \"he will arrange\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mountainous region, lying northeast of Palestine and west of Damascus. At the time when John the Baptist made his public appearance it was subject to Philip the tetrarch, son of Herod the Great, among the regions assigned to this prince after his father\'s death. It was brought under Jewish control by king Aristobulus around 100 B.C. Its inhabitants had been noted for robbery and skilful use of the bow.</OL>'),
(2485, 'ijcquvdion', 'diminutive from (2486)', 'ichthudion', 'None', 'ikh-thoo\'-dee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'diminutive from «2486»; a petty fish:--little (small) fish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a little fish</OL>'),
(2486, 'ijcquvß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'ichthus', 'None', 'ikh-thoos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain affinity; a fish:--fish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a fish</OL>'),
(2487, 'i[cnoß', 'from ikneomai (to arrive, cf (2240))', 'ichnos', '3:402,379', 'ikh\'-nos', 'Noun Neuter', 'from ikneomai (to arrive; compare «2240»); a track (figuratively):--step.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a footprint, track, footstep<LI>in the NT, metaph. of imitating the example of any one</OL>'),
(2488, 'ÅIwaqavm', 'of Hebrew origin (03147)', 'Ioatham', 'None', 'ee-o-ath\'-am', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03147»); Joatham (i.e. Jotham), an Israelite:--Joatham.', 'Jotham = \"Jehovah is upright\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of King Uzziah or Azariah and Jerusha</OL>'),
(2489, 'ÅIwanavn', 'of the same as (2491)', 'Ioanna', 'None', 'ee-o-an\'-nah', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of the same as «2491»; Joanna, a Christian:--Joanna.', 'Joanna = \"Jehovah is a gracious giver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the wife of Chuza, Herod\'s steward, and a follower of Jesus</OL>'),
(2490, 'ÅIwanna\'ß', 'a form of (2491)', 'Ioannas', 'None', 'ee-o-an-nas\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'a form of «2491»; Joannas, an Israelite:--Joannas.', 'Joanna = \"grace or gift of God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the ancestors of Christ</OL>'),
(2491, 'ÅIwavnnhß', 'of Hebrew origin (03110)', 'Ioannes', 'None', 'ee-o-an\'-nace', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03110»); Joannes (i.e. Jochanan), the name of four Israelites:--John.', 'John = \"Jehovah is a gracious giver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>John the Baptist was the son of Zacharias and Elisabeth, the forerunner of Christ. By order of Herod Antipas he was cast into prison and afterwards beheaded.<LI>John the apostle, the writer of the Fourth Gospel, son of Zebedee and Salome, brother of James the elder. He is that disciple who (without mention by name) is spoken of in the Fourth Gospel as especially dear to Jesus and according to the traditional opinion is the author of the book of Revelation.<LI>John surnamed Mark, the companion of Barnabas and Paul. Acts 12:<LI>John a certain man, a member of the Sanhedrin Acts 5:6</OL>'),
(2492, 'ÅIwvb', 'of Hebrew origin (0347)', 'Iob', 'None', 'ee-obe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («0347»); Job (i.e. Ijob), a patriarch:--Job.', 'Job = \"the cry of woe\" or \"I will exclaim\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man known for his piety and, consistency and fortitude in the endurance of trials. His experiences are related in the OT book bearing his name.</OL>'),
(2493, 'ÅIwdav', 'of Hebrew origin (03100)', 'Ioel', 'None', 'ee-o-ale\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03100»); Joel, an Israelite:--Joel.', 'Joel = \"to whom Jehovah is God\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the second of the twelve minor prophets, the son of Pethuel, probably prophesied in Judah in the reign of Uzziah</OL>'),
(2494, 'ÅIwnavm', 'probably for (2491) or (2495)', 'Ionan', 'None', 'ee-o-nan\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably for «2491» or «2495»; Jonan, an Israelite:--Jonan.', 'Jonan = \"Jehovah is a gracious giver\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the ancestors of Christ</OL>'),
(2495, 'ÅIwna\'ß', 'of Hebrew origin (03124)', 'Ionas', '3:406,380', 'ee-o-nas\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03124»); Jonas (i.e. Jonah), the name of two Israelites:--Jonas.', 'Jonah or Jonas = \"dove\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the fifth minor prophet, the son of Amittai, and a native of Gath-hepher and lived during the reign of Jeroboam II, king of Israel<LI>Jonas, the father of Peter</OL>'),
(2496, 'ÅIwravm', 'of Hebrew origin (03141)', 'Ioram', 'None', 'ee-o-ram\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03141»); Joram, an Israelite:--Joram.', 'Jehoram = \"whom Jehovah has exalted\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah, succeeded his father on the throne of Judah</OL>'),
(2497, 'ÅIwrivm', 'perhaps for (2496)', 'Ioreim', 'None', 'ee-o-rime\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps for «2496»; Jorim, an Israelite:--Jorim.', 'Jorim = \"whom Jehovah has exalted\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Matthat, in the genealogy of Christ</OL>'),
(2498, 'ÅIwsafavt', 'of Hebrew origin (03092)', 'Iosaphat', 'None', 'ee-o-saf-at\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03092»); Josaphat (i.e. Jehoshaphat), an Israelite:--Josaphat.', 'Jehoshaphat = \"whom Jehovah judges\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the king of Judah, son of Asa</OL>'),
(2499, 'ÅIwshv', 'genitive case of (2500)', 'Iose', 'None', 'ee-o-say\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'genitive case of «2500»; Jose, an Israelite:--Jose.', 'Jose = \"he will be sustained of Jehovah\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the son of Eliezer, in the genealogy of Jesus Christ</OL>'),
(2500, 'ÅIwsh\'ß', 'perhaps for (2501)', 'Ioses', 'None', 'ee-o-sace\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps for «2501»; Joses, the name of two Israelites:--Joses. Compare «2499».', 'Joses = \"exalted\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the ancestors of Christ, Lk 3:<LI>Joses, the brother of Jesus, Mk 6:<LI>Joses, the son of Mary, the sister of the mother of Jesus, Mt. 27:<LI>Joses, a Levite, Acts 4:36</OL>'),
(2501, 'ÅIwshvf', 'of Hebrew origin (03130)', 'Ioseph', 'None', 'ee-o-safe\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03130»); Joseph, the name of seven Israelites:--Joseph.', 'Joseph = \"let him add\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the patriarch, the eleventh son of Jacob<LI>the son of Jonan or Jonam, one of the ancestors of Christ, Lk 3:<LI>the son of Judah [or Judas; better Joda] another ancestor of Jesus, Lk 3:<LI>the son of Mattathias, another ancestor of Christ, Lk 3:<LI>the husband of Mary, the mother of Jesus<LI>a half-brother of Jesus Mat. 13:<LI>Joseph of Arimathaea, a member of the Sanhedrin, who favoured Jesus. Mt. 27:57,59; Mk 15:43,<LI>Joseph surnamed Barnabas Acts 4:<LI>Joseph call Barsabas and surnamed Justus, Acts 1:23</OL>'),
(2502, 'ÅIwshvc', 'of Hebrew origin (02977)', 'Iosias', 'None', 'ee-o-see\'-as', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («02977»); Josias (i.e. Joshiah), an Israelite:--Josias.', 'Josiah = \"whom Jehovah heals\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>king of Judah, who restored among the Jews the worship of the true God, and after a reign of thirty one years was slain in battle about 611 BC</OL>'),
