(2560, 'kakw\'ß', 'from (2556)', 'kakos', '4:1091,*', 'kak-oce\'', 'Adverb', 'from «2556»; badly (physically or morally):--amiss, diseased, evil, grievously, miserably, sick, sore.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>miserable, to be ill<LI>improperly, wrongly<LI>to speak ill of, revile, one</OL>'),
(2561, 'kavkwsiß', 'from (2559)', 'kakosis', 'None', 'kak\'-o-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2559»; maltreatment:--affliction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>ill treatment, ill usage</OL>'),
(2562, 'kalavmh', 'from (2563)', 'kalame', 'None', 'kal-am\'-ay', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «2563»; a stalk of grain, i.e. (collectively) stubble:--stubble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a stalk of grain or a reed, stubble,<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the stalk left after the ears are cut off</OL></OL>'),
(2563, 'kavlamoß', 'or uncertain affinity', 'kalamos', 'None', 'kal\'-am-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'or uncertain affinity; a reed (the plant or its stem, or that of a similar plant); by implication, a pen:--pen, reed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a reed<LI>a staff made of a reed, a reed staff<LI>a measuring reed or rod<LI>a writer\'s reed, a pen</OL>'),
(2564, 'kalevw', 'akin to the base of (2753)', 'kaleo', '3:487,394', 'kal-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'akin to the base of «2753»; to \"call\" (properly, aloud, but used in a variety of applications, directly or otherwise):--bid, call (forth), (whose, whose sur-)name (was (called)).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to call<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to call aloud, utter in a loud voice<LI>to invite</OL><LI>to call i.e. to name, by name<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to give a name to<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to receive the name of, receive as a name<LI>to give some name to one, call his name</OL><LI>to be called i.e. to bear a name or title (among men)<LI>to salute one by name</OL></OL>'),
(2565, 'kallievlaioß', 'from the base of (2566) and (1636)', 'kallielaios', 'None', 'kal-le-el\'-ah-yos', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the base of «2566» and «1636»; a cultivated olive tree, i.e. a domesticated or improved one:--good olive tree.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the garden olive as opposed to the wild olive</OL>'),
(2566, 'kallivon', 'neuter of the (irregular) comparative of (2570)', 'kallion', 'None', 'kal-lee\'-on', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>better</OL>', 'neuter of the (irregular) comparative of «2570»; (adverbially) better than many:--very well.', ''),
(2567, 'kalodidavskaloß', 'from (2570) and (1320)', 'kalodidaskalos', '2:159,161', 'kal-od-id-as\'-kal-os', 'Adjective', 'from «2570» and «1320»; a teacher of the right:--teacher of good things.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>teaching that which is good, a teacher of goodness</OL>'),
(2568, 'Kaloi; Limevneß', 'plural of (2570) and (3040)', 'Kaloi', 'None', '', 'Noun Location', 'plural of «2570» and «3040»; Good Harbors, i.e. Fairhaven, a bay of Crete:--fair havens.', 'Fair Havens = \"goodly ports\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a bay of Crete, near the city Lasaea, so called because it had a good harbour</OL>'),
(2569, 'kalopoievw', 'from (2570) and (4160)', 'kalopoieo', 'None', 'kal-op-oy-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2570» and «4160»; to do well, i.e. live virtuously:--well doing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to do well, act uprightly</OL>'),
(2570, 'kalovß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'kalos', '3:536,402', 'kal-os\'', 'Adjective', 'of uncertain affinity; properly, beautiful, but chiefly (figuratively) good (literally or morally), i.e. valuable or virtuous (for appearance or use, and thus distinguished from «18», which is properly intrinsic):--X better, fair, good(-ly), honest, meet, well, worthy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beautiful, handsome, excellent, eminent, choice, surpassing, precious, useful, suitable, commendable, admirable<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>beautiful to look at, shapely, magnificent<LI>good, excellent in its nature and characteristics, and therefore well adapted to its ends<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>genuine, approved<LI>precious<LI>joined to names of men designated by their office, competent, able, such as one ought to be<LI>praiseworthy, noble</OL><LI>beautiful by reason of purity of heart and life, and hence praiseworthy<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>morally good, noble</OL><LI>honourable, conferring honour<LI>affecting the mind agreeably, comforting and confirming</OL></OL>'),
(2571, 'kavlumma', 'from (2572)', 'kaluma', '3:558,405', 'kal\'-oo-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2572»; a cover, i.e. veil:--vail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a veil, covering</OL>'),
(2572, 'kaluvptw', 'akin to (2813) and (2928)', 'kalupto', '3:536,405', 'kal-oop\'-to', 'Verb', 'akin to «2813» and «2928»; to cover up (literally or figuratively):--cover, hide.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hide, veil<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to hinder the knowledge of a thing</OL></OL>'),
(2573, 'kalw\'ß', 'from (2570)', 'kalos', 'None', 'kal-oce\'', 'Adverb', 'adverb from «2570»; well (usually morally):--(in a) good (place), honestly, + recover, (full) well.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>beautifully, finely, excellently, well<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>rightly, so that there shall be no room for blame, well, truly<LI>excellently, nobly, commendably<LI>honourably, in honour<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in a good place, comfortable</OL><LI>to speak well of one, to do good<LI>to be well (of those recovering health)</OL></OL>'),
(2574, 'kavmhloß', 'of Hebrew origin (01581)', 'kamelos', '3:592,413', 'kam\'-ay-los', 'Noun', 'of Hebrew origin («01581»); a \"camel\":--camel.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>camel</OL>'),
(2575, 'kavminoß', 'probably from (2545)', 'kaminos', 'None', 'kam\'-ee-nos', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from «2545»; a furnace:--furnace.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a furnace<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>for smelting<LI>for burning earthen ware<LI>for baking bread</OL></OL>'),
(2576, 'kammuvw', 'from a compound of (2596) and the base of (3466)', 'kammuo', 'None', 'kam-moo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a compound of «2596» and the base of «3466»; to shut down, i.e. close the eyes:--close.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shut the eyes, close the eyes</OL>'),
(2577, 'kavmnw', 'apparently a primary verb', 'kamno', 'None', 'kam\'-no', 'Verb', 'apparently a primary verb; properly, to toil, i.e. (by implication) to tire (figuratively, faint, sicken):--faint, sick, be wearied.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to grow weary, be weary<LI>to be sick</OL>'),
(2578, 'kavmptw', 'apparently a primary verb', 'kampto', '3:594,413', 'kamp\'-to', 'Verb', 'apparently a primary verb; to bend:--bow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bend, bow, the knee (the knees)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to one<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in honour of one<LI>in religious veneration</OL><LI>used of worshippers</OL><LI>to bow one\'s self</OL>'),
(2579, 'ka[n', 'from (2532) and (1437)', 'kan', 'None', 'kan', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>and if<LI>also or even if<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of only, at least<LI>even if</OL></OL>', 'from «2532» and «1437»; and (or even) if:--and (also) if (so much as), if but, at the least, though, yet.', ''),
(2580, 'Kanav', 'of Hebrew origin, cf (07071)', 'Kana', 'None', 'kan-ah\'', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin (compare «07071»); Cana, a place in Palestine:--Cana.', 'Cana = \"place of reeds\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a village in Galilee about 5 miles (8 km) NW from Nazareth</OL>'),
(2581, 'Kananai\'oß', 'of Aramaic origin, cf (07067)', 'Kananites', 'None', 'kan-an-ee\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Chaldee origin (compare «07067»); zealous; Cananites, an epithet:--Canaanite (by mistake for a derivative from «5477»).', 'Canaanite = \"zealous\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the surname of apostle Simon, otherwise known as \"Simon Zelotes\"</OL>'),
(2582, 'Kandavkh', 'of foreign origin', 'Kandake', 'None', 'kan-dak\'-ay', 'Noun Feminine', 'of foreign origin:--Candace, an Egyptian queen:--Candace.', 'Candace = \"prince of servants\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a queen of Ethiopia mentioned in Acts 8:27. (A.D.<LI>The name was not a proper name of an individual, but that of a dynasty of Ethiopian queens.</OL>'),
(2583, 'kanwvn', 'from kane (a straight reed, i.e. rod)', 'kanon', '3:596,414', 'kan-ohn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from kane (a straight reed, i.e. rod); a rule (\"canon\"), i.e. (figuratively) a standard (of faith and practice); by implication, a boundary, i.e. (figuratively) a sphere (of activity):--line, rule.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a rod or straight piece of rounded wood to which any thing is fastened to keep it straight<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used for various purposes<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a measuring rod, rule<LI>a carpenter\'s line or measuring tape<LI>the measure of a leap, as in the Olympic games</OL></OL><LI>a definitely bounded or fixed space within the limits of which one\'s power of influence is confined<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the province assigned one<LI>one\'s sphere of activity</OL><LI>metaph. any rule or standard, a principle or law of investigating, judging, living, acting</OL>'),
(2584, 'Kapernaouvm', 'of Hebrew origin, probably (03723) and (05151)', 'Kapernaoum', 'None', 'cap-er-nah-oom\'', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin (probably «03723» and «05151»); Capernaum (i.e. Caphanachum), a place in Palestine:--Capernaum.', 'Capernaum = \"village of comfort\"'),
(2585, 'kaphleuvw', 'from kapelos (a huckster)', 'kapeleuo', '3:603,415', 'kap-ale-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from kapelos (a huckster); to retail, i.e. (by implication) to adulterate (figuratively):--corrupt.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be a retailer, to peddle<LI>to make money by selling anything<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to get sordid gain by dealing in anything, to do a thing for base gain<LI>to trade in the word of God<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to try to get base gain by teaching divine truth</OL><LI>to corrupt, to adulterate<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>peddlers were in the habit of adulterating their commodities for the sake of gain</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2586, 'kapnovß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'kapnos', 'None', 'kap-nos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain affinity; smoke:--smoke.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>smoke</OL>'),
(2587, 'Kappadokiva', 'of foreign origin', 'Kappadokia', 'None', 'kap-pad-ok-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Location', 'of foreign origin; Cappadocia, a region of Asia Minor:--Cappadocia.', 'Cappadocia = \"province of good horses\"'),
(2588, 'kardiva', 'prolonged from a primary kar (Latin, cor, \"heart\")', 'kardia', '3:605,415', 'kar-dee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'prolonged from a primary kar (Latin cor, \"heart\"); the heart, i.e. (figuratively) the thoughts or feelings (mind); also (by analogy) the middle:--(+ broken-)heart(-ed).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the heart<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>that organ in the animal body which is the centre of the circulation of the blood, and hence was regarded as the seat of physical life<LI>denotes the centre of all physical and spiritual life<LI>the vigour and sense of physical life<LI>the centre and seat of spiritual life<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the soul or mind, as it is the fountain and seat of the thoughts, passions, desires, appetites, affections, purposes, endeavours<LI>of the understanding, the faculty and seat of the intelligence<LI>of the will and character<LI>of the soul so far as it is affected and stirred in a bad way or good, or of the soul as the seat of the sensibilities, affections, emotions, desires, appetites, passions</OL><LI>of the middle or central or inmost part of anything, even though inanimate</OL></OL>'),
(2589, 'kardiognwvsthß', 'from (2588) and (1097)', 'kardiognostes', '3:613,415', 'kar-dee-og-noce\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2588» and «1097»; a heart-knower:--which knowest the hearts.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>knower of the hearts</OL>'),
(2590, 'karpovß', 'probably from the base of (726)', 'karpos', '3:614,416', 'kar-pos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from the base of «726»; fruit (as plucked), literally or figuratively:--fruit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fruit<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the fruit of the trees, vines, of the fields<LI>the fruit of one\'s loins, i.e. his progeny, his posterity</OL><LI>that which originates or comes from something, an effect, result<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>work, act, deed<LI>advantage, profit, utility<LI>praises, which are presented to God as a thank offering<LI>to gather fruit (i.e. a reaped harvest) into life eternal (as into a granary), is used in fig. discourse of those who by their labours have fitted souls to obtain eternal life</OL></OL>'),
(2591, 'Kavrpoß', 'perhaps for (2590)', 'Karpos', 'None', 'kar\'-pos', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps for «2590»; Carpus, probably a Christian:--Carpus.', 'Carpus = \"fruit\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Christian at Troas 2 Ti. 4:13</OL>'),
(2592, 'karpoforevw', 'from (2593)', 'karpophoreo', '3:616,416', 'kar-pof-or-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2593»; to be fertile (literally or figuratively):--be (bear, bring forth) fruit(-ful).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear fruit<LI>to bear, bring forth, deeds<LI>to bear fruit of one\'s self</OL>'),
(2593, 'karpofovroß', 'from (2590) and (5342)', 'karpophoros', 'None', 'kar-pof-or\'-os', 'Adjective', 'from «2590» and «5342»; fruitbearing (figuratively):--fruitful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fruit bearing, fruitful, productive</OL>'),
(2594, 'karterevw', 'from a derivative of (2904) (transp.)', 'kartereo', '3:617,417', 'kar-ter-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a derivative of «2904» (transposed); to be strong, i.e. (figuratively) steadfast (patient):--endure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be steadfast</OL>'),
(2595, 'kavrfoß', 'from karpho (to wither)', 'karphos', 'None', 'kar\'-fos', 'Noun Neuter', 'from karpho (to wither); a dry twig or straw:--mote.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a dry stalk or twig, a straw<LI>chaff</OL>'),
(2596, 'katav', 'a primary particle', 'kata', 'None', 'kat-ah\'', 'Preposition', 'a primary particle; (prepositionally) down (in place or time), in varied relations (according to the case (genitive, dative or accusative) with which it is joined):--about, according as (to), after, against, (when they were) × alone, among, and, × apart, (even, like) as (concerning, pertaining to touching), × aside, at, before, beyond, by, to the charge of, (charita-)bly, concerning, + covered, (dai-)ly, down, every, (+ far more) exceeding, × more excellent, for, from ... to, godly, in(-asmuch, divers, every, -to, respect of), ... by, after the manner of, + by any means, beyond (out of) measure, × mightily, more, × natural, of (up-)on (X part), out (of every), over against, (+ your) × own, + particularly, so, through(-oughout, -oughout every), thus, (un-)to(-gether, -ward), × uttermost, where(-by), with. In composition it retains many of these applications, and frequently denotes opposition, distribution, or intensity.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>down from, through out<LI>according to, toward, along</OL>'),
(2597, 'katabaivnw', 'from (2596) and the base of (939)', 'katabaino', '1:522,90', 'kat-ab-ah\'-ee-no', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and the base of «939»; to descend (literally or figuratively):--come (get, go, step) down, fall (down).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go down, come down, descend<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the place from which one has come down from<LI>to come down<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as from the temple at Jerusalem, from the city of Jerusalem<LI>of celestial beings coming down to earth</OL><LI>to be cast down</OL><LI>of things<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to come (i.e. be sent) down<LI>to come (i.e. fall) down<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>from the upper regions of the air</OL></OL><LI>metaph. to (go i.e.) be cast down to the lowest state of wretchedness and shame</OL>'),
(2598, 'katabavllw', 'from (2596) and (906)', 'kataballo', 'None', 'kat-ab-al\'-lo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «906»; to throw down:--cast down, lay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cast down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to throw to the ground, prostate</OL><LI>to put in a lower place<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to lay (down) a foundation</OL></OL>'),
(2599, 'katabarevw', 'from (2596) and (916)', 'katabareo', 'None', 'kat-ab-ar-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «916»; to impose upon:--burden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to press down by an imposing weight<LI>to weigh down<LI>metaph. to burden</OL>'),
(2600, 'katavbasiß', 'from (2597)', 'katabasis', 'None', 'kat-ab\'-as-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2597»; a declivity:--descent.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>descent<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the act of descending<LI>the place of descent<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that part of the mountain where the descent is made</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2601, 'katabibavzw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of the base of (939)', 'katabibazo', 'None', 'kat-ab-ib-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of the base of «939»; to cause to go down, i.e. precipitate:--bring (thrust) down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to go down<LI>to bring down<LI>to cast down, thrust down</OL>'),
(2602, 'katabolhv', 'from (2598)', 'katabole', '3:620,418', 'kat-ab-ol-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2598»; a deposition, i.e. founding; figuratively, conception:--conceive, foundation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a throwing or laying down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the injection or depositing of the virile semen in the womb<LI>of the seed of plants and animals</OL><LI>a founding (laying down a foundation)</OL>'),
(2603, 'katabrabeuvw', 'from (2596) and (1018) (in its original sense)', 'katabrabeuo', 'None', 'kat-ab-rab-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «1018» (in its original sense); to award the price against, i.e. (figuratively) to defraud (of salvation):--beguile of reward.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to decide as umpire against someone<LI>to defraud or beguile of the prize of victory<LI>metaph. to deprive of salvation</OL>'),
(2604, 'kataggeleuvß', 'from (2605)', 'kataggeleus', '1:70,10', 'kat-ang-gel-yooce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2605»; a proclaimer:--setter forth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>announcer, proclaimer</OL>'),
(2605, 'kataggevllw', 'from (2596) and the base of (32)', 'kataggello', '1:70,10', 'kat-ang-gel\'-lo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and the base of «32»; to proclaim, promulgate:--declare, preach, shew, speak of, teach.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to announce, declare, promulgate, make known<LI>to proclaim publicly, publish<LI>to denounce, report, betray</OL>'),
(2606, 'katagelavw', 'a primitive root', 'katagelao', '1:658,113', 'kat-ag-el-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'to laugh down, i.e. deride:--laugh to scorn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to deride</OL>'),
(2607, 'kataginwvskw', 'from (2596) and (1097)', 'kataginosko', '1:714,119', 'kat-ag-in-o\'-sko', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «1097»; to note against, i.e. find fault with:--blame, condemn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to find fault with, blame<LI>to accuse, condemn</OL>'),
(2608, 'katavgnumi', 'from (2596) and the base of (4486)', 'katagnumi', 'None', 'kat-ag\'-noo-mee', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and the base of «4486»; to rend in pieces, i.e. crack apart:--break.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break</OL>'),
(2609, 'katavgw', 'from (2596) and (71)', 'katago', 'None', 'kat-ag\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «71»; to lead down; specially, to moor a vessel:--bring (down, forth), (bring to) land, touch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead down, bring down<LI>to bring the vessel from deep water to the land<LI>to be brought (down) in a ship, to land, touch at</OL>'),
(2610, 'katagwnivzomai', 'from (2596) and (75)', 'katagonizomai', '1:134,20', 'kat-ag-o-nid\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «75»; to struggle against, i.e. (by implication) to overcome:--subdue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to struggle against<LI>to overcome</OL>'),
(2611, 'katadevw', 'from (2596) and (1210)', 'katadeo', 'None', 'kat-ad-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «1210»; to tie down, i.e. bandage (a wound):--bind up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bind up</OL>'),
(2612, 'katavdhloß', 'from (2596) intensive and (1212)', 'katadelos', 'None', 'kat-ad\'-ay-los', 'Adjective', 'from «2596» intensive and «1212»; manifest:--far more evident.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thoroughly clear, plain, evident</OL>'),
(2613, 'katadikavzw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of (1349)', 'katadikazo', '3:621,418', 'kat-ad-ik-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of «1349»; to adjudge against, i.e. pronounce guilty:--condemn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give judgment against (one), to pronounce guilty<LI>to condemn</OL>'),
(2614, 'katadiwvkw', 'from (2596) and (1377)', 'katadioko', 'None', 'kat-ad-ee-o\'-ko', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «1377»; to hunt down, i.e. search for:--follow after.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to follow after, follow up</OL>'),
(2615, 'katadoulovw', 'from (2596) and (1402)', 'katadouloo', '2:279,182', 'kat-ad-oo-lo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «1402»; to enslave utterly:--bring into bondage.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bring into bondage, enslave<LI>to enslave to one\'s self, bring into bondage to one\'s self</OL>'),
(2616, 'katadunasteuvw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of (1413)', 'katadunasteuo', 'None', 'kat-ad-oo-nas-tyoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of «1413»; to exercise dominion against, i.e. oppress:--oppress.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to exercise harsh control over one, to use one\'s power against one<LI>to oppress one</OL>'),
(2617, 'kataqemativzw', 'from (2596) and (153)', 'kataischuno', '1:189,29', 'kat-ahee-skhoo\'-no', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «153»; to shame down, i.e. disgrace or (by implication) put to the blush:--confound, dishonour, (be a-, make a-)shame(-d).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dishonour, disgrace<LI>to put to shame, make ashamed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be ashamed, blush with shame<LI>one is said to be put to shame who suffers a repulse, or whom some hope has deceived</OL></OL>'),
(2618, 'katakaivw', 'from (2596) and (2545)', 'katakaio', 'None', 'kat-ak-ah\'-ee-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2545»; to burn down (to the ground), i.e. consume wholly:--burn (up, utterly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to burn up, consume by fire</OL>'),
(2619, 'katakaluvptw', 'from (2596) and (2572)', 'katakalupto', '3:561,405', 'kat-ak-al-oop\'-to', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2572»; to cover wholly, i.e. veil:--cover, hide.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cover up<LI>to veil or cover one\'s self</OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2620, 'katakaucavomai', 'from (2596) and (2744)', 'katakauchaomai', '3:653,423', 'kat-ak-ow-khah\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2744»; to exult against (i.e. over):--boast (against), glory, rejoice against.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to glory against, to exult over, to boast one\'s self to the injury (of a person or thing)</OL>'),
(2621, 'katavkeimai', 'from (2596) and (2749)', 'katakeimai', '3:655,425', 'kat-ak\'-i-mahee', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2749»; to lie down, i.e. (by implication) be sick; specially, to recline at a meal:--keep, lie, sit at meat (down).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to have lain down, i.e. to lie prostrate<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the sick<LI>of those at meals, to recline</OL></OL>'),
(2622, 'kataklavw', 'from (2596) and (2806)', 'kataklao', 'None', 'kat-ak-lah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2806»; to break down, i.e. divide:--break.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break in pieces</OL>'),
(2623, 'katakleivw', 'from (2596) and (2808)', 'katakleio', 'None', 'kat-ak-li\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2808»; to shut down (in a dungeon), i.e. incarcerate:--shut up.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shut up, confine</OL>'),
(2624, 'kataklhronomevw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of a compound of (2819) and (1325)', 'kataklerodoteo', 'None', 'kat-ak-lay-rod-ot-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of a compound of «2819» and «1325»; to be a giver of lots to each, i.e. (by implication) to apportion an estate:--divide by lot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to distribute by lot<LI>to distribute as an inheritance</OL>'),
(2625, 'kataklivnw', 'from (2596) and (2827)', 'kataklino', 'None', 'kat-ak-lee\'-no', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2827»; to recline down, i.e. (specially) to take a place at table:--(make) sit down (at meat).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in the NT in reference to eating, to make to recline<LI>to recline (at a table)</OL>'),
(2626, 'katakluvzw', 'from (2596) and the base of (2830)', 'katakluzo', 'None', 'kat-ak-lood\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and the base of «2830»; to dash (wash) down, i.e. (by implication) to deluge:--overflow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to overwhelm with water, to submerge, deluge</OL>'),
(2627, 'kataklusmovß', 'from (2626)', 'kataklusmos', 'None', 'kat-ak-looce-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2626»; an inundation:--flood.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>inundation, deluge<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of Noah\'s deluge</OL></OL>'),
(2628, 'katakolouqevw', 'from (2596) and (190)', 'katakoloutheo', 'None', 'kat-ak-ol-oo-theh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «190»; to accompany closely:--follow (after).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to follow after</OL>'),
(2629, 'katakovptw', 'from (2596) and (2875)', 'katakopto', 'None', 'kat-ak-op\'-to', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2875»; to chop down, i.e. mangle:--cut.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut up in pieces<LI>to slay<LI>to beat, bruise<LI>to cut, gash, mangle</OL>'),
(2630, 'katakrhmnivzw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of (2911)', 'katakremnizo', 'None', 'kat-ak-rame-nid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of «2911»; to precipitate down:--cast down headlong.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cast down a precipice<LI>to through down headlong</OL>'),
(2631, 'katavkrima', 'from (2632)', 'katakrima', '3:951,469', 'kat-ak\'-ree-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2632»; an adverse sentence (the verdict):--condemnation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>damnatory sentence, condemnation</OL>'),
(2632, 'katakrivnw', 'from (2596) and (2919)', 'katakrino', '3:951,469', 'kat-ak-ree\'-no', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2919»; to judge against, i.e. sentence:--condemn, damn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to give judgment against, to judge worthy of punishment<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to condemn<LI>by one\'s good example to render another\'s wickedness the more evident and censurable</OL></OL>'),
(2633, 'katavkrisiß', 'from (2632)', 'katakrisis', '3:951,469', 'kat-ak\'-ree-sis', 'Verb', 'from «2632»; sentencing adversely (the act):--condemn(-ation).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>condemnation</OL>'),
(2634, 'katakuvptw', 'from (2596) and (2961)', 'katakurieuo', '3:1098,486', 'kat-ak-oo-ree-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2961»; to lord against, i.e. control, subjugate:--exercise dominion over (lordship), be lord over, overcome.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bring under one\'s power, to subject one\'s self, to subdue, master<LI>to hold in subjection, to be master of, exercise lordship over</OL>'),
(2635, 'katalalevw', 'from (2637)', 'katalaleo', '4:3,495', 'kat-al-al-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2637»; to be a traducer, i.e. to slander:--speak against (evil of).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to speak against one, to criminate, traduce</OL>'),
(2636, 'katalaliav', 'from (2637)', 'katalalia', '4:3,495', 'kat-al-al-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2637»; defamation:--backbiting, evil speaking.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>defamation, evil speaking</OL>'),
(2637, 'katavlaloß', 'from (2596) and the base of (2980)', 'katalalos', '4:3,495', 'kat-al\'-al-os', 'Adjective', 'from «2596» and the base of «2980»; talkative against, i.e. a slanderer:--backbiter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a defamer, evil speaker</OL>'),
(2638, 'katalambavnw', 'from (2596) and (2983)', 'katalambano', '4:9,495', 'kat-al-am-ban\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «2983»; to take eagerly, i.e. seize, possess, etc. (literally or figuratively):--apprehend, attain, come upon, comprehend, find, obtain, perceive, (over-)take.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lay hold of<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to lay hold of so as to make one\'s own, to obtain, attain to, to make one\'s own, to take into one\'s self, appropriate<LI>to seize upon, take possession of<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of evils overtaking one, of the last day overtaking the wicked with destruction, of a demon about to torment one<LI>in a good sense, of Christ by his holy power and influence laying hold of the human mind and will, in order to prompt and govern it</OL><LI>to detect, catch<LI>to lay hold of with the mind<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to understand, perceive, learn, comprehend</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2639, 'katalevgw', 'from (2596) and (3004) (in its orig. meaning)', 'katalego', 'None', 'kat-al-eg\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3004» (in its original meaning); to lay down, i.e. (figuratively) to enrol:--take into the number.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lay down, to lie down<LI>to narrate at length, recount, set forth<LI>to set down in a list or register, to enrol<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of soldiers<LI>of those widows who held a prominent place in the church and exercised a certain superintendence over the rest of the women, and had charge of the widows and orphans supported at the public expense</OL></OL>'),
(2640, 'katavleimma', 'from (2641)', 'kataleimma', '4:194,523', 'kat-al\'-ime-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2641»; a remainder, i.e. (by implication) a few:--remnant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>remnant, remains</OL>'),
(2641, 'kataleivpw', 'from (2596) and (3007)', 'kataleipo', '4:194,523', 'kat-al-i\'-po', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3007»; to leave down, i.e. behind; by implication, to abandon, have remaining:--forsake, leave, reserve.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to leave behind<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to depart from, leave<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be left</OL><LI>to bid (one) to remain<LI>to forsake, leave to one\'s self a person or thing by ceasing to care for it, to abandon, leave in the lurch<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be abandoned, forsaken</OL><LI>to cause to be left over, to reserve, to leave remaining<LI>like our \"leave behind\", it is used of one who on being called away cannot take another with him<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>especially of the dying (to leave behind)</OL><LI>like our \"leave\", leave alone, disregard<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of those who sail past a place without stopping</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2642, 'kataliqavzw', 'from (2596) and (3034)', 'katalithazo', '4:267,533', 'kat-al-ith-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3034»; to stone down, i.e. to death:--stone.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to overwhelm with stones, to stone</OL>'),
(2643, 'katallaghv', 'from (2644)', 'katallage', '1:258,40', 'kat-al-lag-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2644»; exchange (figuratively, adjustment), i.e. restoration to (the divine) favor:--atonement, reconciliation(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>exchange<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the business of money changers, exchanging equivalent values</OL><LI>adjustment of a difference, reconciliation, restoration to favour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in the NT of the restoration of the favour of God to sinners that repent and put their trust in the expiatory death of Christ</OL></OL>'),
(2644, 'katallavssw', 'from (2596) and (236)', 'katallasso', '1:254,40', 'kat-al-las\'-so', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «236»; to change mutually, i.e. (figuratively) to compound a difference:--reconcile.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to change, exchange, as coins for others of equivalent value<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to reconcile (those who are at variance)<LI>return to favour with, be reconciled to one<LI>to receive one into favour</OL></OL>'),
(2645, 'katavloipoß', 'from (2596) and (3062)', 'kataloipos', 'None', 'kat-al\'-oy-pos', 'Adjective', 'from «2596» and «3062»; left down (behind), i.e remaining (plural the rest):--residue.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>left remaining</OL>'),
(2646, 'katavluma', 'from (2647)', 'kataluma', '4:338,543', 'kat-al\'-oo-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2647»; properly, a dissolution (breaking up of a journey), i.e. (by implication) a lodging-place:-- guestchamber, inn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inn, lodging place<LI>an eating room, dining room</OL>'),
(2647, 'kataluvw', 'from (2596) and (3089)', 'kataluo', '4:338,543', 'kat-al-oo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3089»; to loosen down (disintegrate), i.e. (by implication) to demolish (literally or figuratively); specially (compare «2646») to halt for the night:--destroy, dissolve, be guest, lodge, come to nought, overthrow, throw down.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dissolve, disunite<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>(what has been joined together), to destroy, demolish<LI>metaph. to overthrow i.e. render vain, deprive of success, bring to naught<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to subvert, overthrow 1b</OL><LI>of institutions, forms of government, laws, etc., to deprive of force, annul, abrogate, discard<LI>of travellers, to halt on a journey, to put up, lodge (the figurative expression originating in the circumstance that, to put up for the night, the straps and packs of the beasts of burden are unbound and taken off; or, more correctly from the fact that the traveller\'s garments, tied up when he is on the journey, are unloosed at it end)</OL></OL>'),
(2648, 'katamanqavnw', 'from (2596) and (3129)', 'katamanthano', '4:414,552', 'kat-am-an-than\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3129»; to learn thoroughly, i.e. (by implication) to note carefully:--consider.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to learn thoroughly, examine carefully<LI>to consider well</OL>'),
(2649, 'katamarturevw', 'from (2596) and (3140)', 'katamartureo', '4:508,564', 'kat-am-ar-too-reh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3140»; to testify against:--witness against.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bear witness against, to testify against one</OL>'),
(2650, 'katamevnw', 'from (2596) and (3306)', 'katameno', 'None', 'kat-am-en\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3306»; to stay fully, i.e. reside:--abide.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to remain permanently, to abide</OL>'),
(2651, 'katamovnaß', 'from (2596) and accusative case plural feminine of (3441) (with (5561) implied)', 'katamonas', 'None', 'kat-am-on\'-as', 'Adjective', 'from «2596» and accusative case plural feminine of «3441» (with «5561» implied); according to sole places, i.e. (adverbially) separately:--alone.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>apart, alone</OL>'),
(2652, 'katanavqema', 'from (2596) (intensive) and (331)', 'katanathema', '1:354,*', 'kat-an-ath\'-em-ah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2596» (intensive) and «331»; an imprecation:--curse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>curse</OL>'),
(2653, 'katanaqemativzw', 'from (2596) (intensive) and (332)', 'katanathematizo', '1:355,*', 'kat-an-ath-em-at-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» (intensive) and «332»; to imprecate:--curse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to curse</OL>'),
(2654, 'katanalivskw', 'from (2596) and (355)', 'katanalisko', 'None', 'kat-an-al-is\'-ko', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «355»; to consume utterly:--consume.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to consume<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of fire</OL></OL>'),
(2655, 'katanarkavw', 'from (2596) and narkao (to be numb)', 'katanarkao', 'None', 'kat-an-ar-kah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and narkao (to be numb); to grow utterly torpid, i.e. (by implication) slothful (figuratively, expensive):--be burdensome (chargeable).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to grow numb or torpid<LI>to be torpid, inactive, to be to the detriment of one<LI>to weigh heavily upon, be burdensome to</OL>'),
(2656, 'kataneuvw', 'from (2596) and (3506)', 'kataneuo', 'None', 'kat-an-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3506»; to nod down (towards), i.e. (by analogy) to make signs to:--beckon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to nod to, make a sign<LI>to indicate to another by a nod or sign what one wishes him to do</OL>'),
(2657, 'katanoevw', 'from (2596) and (3539)', 'katanoeo', '4:973,636', 'kat-an-o-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3539»; to observe fully:--behold, consider, discover, perceive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to perceive, remark, observe, understand<LI>to consider attentively, fix one\'s eyes or mind upon</OL>'),
(2658, 'katantavw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of (473)', 'katantao', '3:623,419', 'kat-an-tah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of «473»; to meet against, i.e. arrive at (literally or figuratively):--attain, come.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to come to, arrive<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to come to a place over against, opposite another<LI>metaph. to attain to a thing</OL></OL>'),
(2659, 'katavnuxiß', 'from (2660)', 'katanuxis', '3:626,419', 'kat-an\'-oox-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2660»; a prickling (sensation, as of the limbs asleep), i.e. (by implication, (perhaps by some confusion with «3506» or even with «3571»)) stupor (lethargy):--slumber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a pricking, piercing<LI>severe sorrow, extreme grief<LI>insensibility or torpor of mind, such as extreme grief easily produces<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hence a \"spirit of stupor\", which renders their souls torpid so insensible that they are not affected at all by the offer made them of salvation through the Messiah</OL></OL>'),
(2660, 'katanuvssw', 'from (2596) and (3572)', 'katanusso', '3:626,419', 'kat-an-oos\'-so', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3572»; to pierce thoroughly, i.e. (figuratively) to agitate violently (\"sting to the quick\"):--prick.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to prick, pierce<LI>metaph. to pain the mind sharply, agitate it vehemently<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>esp. of the emotion of sorrow</OL></OL>'),
(2661, 'kataxiovw', 'from (2596) and (515)', 'kataxioo', '1:380,63', 'kat-ax-ee-o\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «515»; to deem entirely deserving:--(ac-)count worthy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to account worthy, judge worthy</OL>'),
(2662, 'katapatevw', 'from (2596) and (3961)', 'katapateo', '5:940,804', 'kat-ap-at-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3961»; to trample down; figuratively, to reject with disdain:--trample, tread (down, underfoot).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tread down, trample under foot, to trample on<LI>metaph. to treat with rudeness and insult<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to spurn, treat with insulting neglect</OL></OL>'),
(2663, 'katavpausiß', 'from (2664)', 'katapausis', '3:628,419', 'kat-ap\'-ow-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2664»; reposing down, i.e. (by Hebraism) abode:--rest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a putting to rest<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>calming of the winds</OL><LI>a resting place<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>metaph. the heavenly blessedness in which God dwells, and of which he has promised to make persevering believers in Christ partakers after the toils and trials of life on earth are ended</OL></OL>'),
(2664, 'katapauvw', 'from (2596) and (3973)', 'katapauo', '3:627,419', 'kat-ap-ow\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «3973»; to settle down, i.e. (literally) to colonize, or (figuratively) to (cause to) desist:--cease, (give) rest(-rain).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make quiet, to cause to be at rest, to grant rest<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to lead to a quiet abode<LI>to still, restrain, to cause (one striving to do something) to desist</OL><LI>to rest, take rest</OL>'),
(2665, 'katapevtasma', 'from a compound of (2596) and a congener of (4072)', 'katapetasma', '3:628,420', 'kat-ap-et\'-as-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a compound of «2596» and a congener of «4072»; something spread thoroughly, i.e. (specially) the door screen (to the Most Holy Place) in the Jewish Temple:--vail.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a veil spread out, a curtain<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the name given to the two curtains in the temple at Jerusalem, one of them at the entrance to the temple separated the Holy Place from the outer court, the other veiled the Holy of Holies from the Holy Place</OL></OL>'),
(2666, 'katapivnw', 'from (2596) and (4095)', 'katapino', '6:158,841', 'kat-ap-ee\'-no', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «4095»; to drink down, i.e. gulp entire (literally or figuratively):--devour, drown, swallow (up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drink down, swallow down<LI>to devour<LI>to swallow up, destroy</OL>'),
(2667, 'katapivptw', 'from (2596) and (4098)', 'katapipto', '6:169,846', 'kat-ap-ip\'-to', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «4098»; to fall down:--fall (down)', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fall down</OL>'),
(2668, 'kataplevw', 'from (2596) and (4126)', 'katapleo', 'None', 'kat-ap-leh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «4126»; to sail down upon a place, i.e. to land at:--arrive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sail down from the deep sea to the land<LI>to put in</OL>'),
(2669, 'kataponevw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of (4192)', 'kataponeo', 'None', 'kat-ap-on-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of «4192»; to labor down, i.e. wear with toil (figuratively, harass):--oppress, vex.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tire down with toil, exhaust with labour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to afflict or oppress with evils<LI>to make trouble for<LI>to treat roughly</OL></OL>'),
(2670, 'katapontivzw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of the same as (4195)', 'katapontizo', 'None', 'kat-ap-on-tid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of the same as «4195»; to plunge down, i.e. submerge:--drown, sink.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to plunge or sink into the sea<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to sink, to go down<LI>a grievous offender for the purpose of killing him, to drown</OL></OL>'),
(2671, 'katavra', 'from (2596) (intensive) and (685)', 'katara', '1:449,75', 'kat-ar\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2596» (intensive) and «685»; imprecation, execration:--curse(-d, ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an execration, imprecation, curse</OL>'),
(2672, 'kataravomai', 'middle voice from (2671)', 'kataraomai', '1:448,75', 'kat-ar-ah\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «2671»; to execrate; by analogy, to doom:--curse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to curse, doom, imprecate evil upon</OL>'),
(2673, 'katargevw', 'from (2596) and (691)', 'katargeo', '1:452,76', 'kat-arg-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «691»; to be (render) entirely idle (useless), literally or figuratively:--abolish, cease, cumber, deliver, destroy, do away, become (make) of no (none, without) effect, fail, loose, bring (come) to nought, put away (down), vanish away, make void.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to render idle, unemployed, inactivate, inoperative<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to cause a person or thing to have no further efficiency<LI>to deprive of force, influence, power</OL><LI>to cause to cease, put an end to, do away with, annul, abolish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to cease, to pass away, be done away<LI>to be severed from, separated from, discharged from, loosed from any one<LI>to terminate all intercourse with one</OL></OL>'),
(2674, 'katariqmevw', 'from (2596) and (705)', 'katarithmeo', 'None', 'kat-ar-ith-meh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «705»; to reckon among:--number with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to number with</OL>'),
(2675, 'katartivzw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of (739)', 'katartizo', '1:475,80', 'kat-ar-tid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of «739»; to complete thoroughly, i.e. repair (literally or figuratively) or adjust:--fit, frame, mend, (make) perfect(-ly join together), prepare, restore.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to render, i.e. to fit, sound, complete<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to mend (what has been broken or rent), to repair<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to complete</OL><LI>to fit out, equip, put in order, arrange, adjust<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to fit or frame for one\'s self, prepare</OL><LI>ethically: to strengthen, perfect, complete, make one what he ought to be</OL></OL>'),
(2676, 'katavrtisiß', 'from (2675)', 'katartisis', '1:475,80', 'kat-ar\'-tis-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2675»; thorough equipment (subjectively):--perfection.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a strengthening, perfecting of the soul<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a training, disciplining, instructing</OL></OL>'),
(2677, 'katartismovß', 'from (2675)', 'katartismos', '1:475,80', 'kat-ar-tis-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2675»; complete furnishing (objectively):--perfecting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>complete furnishing, equipping</OL>'),
(2678, 'kataseivw', 'from (2596) and (4579)', 'kataseio', 'None', 'kat-as-i\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «4579»; to sway downward, i.e. make a signal:--beckon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shake down, throw down<LI>to shake<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to make a sign, to signal with the hand to one</OL></OL>'),
(2679, 'kataskavptw', 'from (2596) and (4626)', 'kataskapto', 'None', 'kat-as-kap\'-to', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and «4626»; to undermine, i.e. (by implication) destroy:--dig down, ruin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dig under, dig down, demolish, destroy</OL>'),
(2680, 'kataskeuavzw', 'from (2596) and a derivative of (4632)', 'kataskeuazo', 'None', 'kat-ask-yoo-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2596» and a derivative of «4632»; to prepare thoroughly (properly, by external equipment; whereas «2090» refers rather to internal fitness); by implication, to construct, create:--build, make, ordain, prepare.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to furnish, equip, prepare, make ready<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of one who makes anything ready for a person or thing<LI>of builders, to construct, erect, with the included idea of adorning and equipping with all things necessary</OL></OL>'),
