(2744, 'kaucavomai', 'from some (obsolete) base akin to that of aucheo (to boast) and (2172)', 'kauchaomai', '3:645,423', 'kow-khah\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'from some (obsolete) base akin to that of aucheo (to boast) and «2172»; to vaunt (in a good or a bad sense):--(make) boast, glory, joy, rejoice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to glory (whether with reason or without)<LI>to glory on account of a thing<LI>to glory in a thing</OL>'),
(2745, 'kauvchma', 'from (2744)', 'kauchema', '3:645,423', 'kow\'-khay-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2744»; a boast (properly, the object; by implication, the act) in a good or a bad sense:--boasting, (whereof) to glory (of), glorying, rejoice(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that of which one glories or can glory, matter or ground of glorying<LI>a glorying or boasting</OL>'),
(2746, 'kauvchsiß', 'from (2744)', 'kauchesis', '3:645,423', 'kow\'-khay-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2744»; boasting (properly, the act; by implication, the object), in a good or a bad sense:--boasting, whereof I may glory, glorying, rejoicing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the act of glorying</OL>'),
(2747, 'Kegcreaiv', 'probably from kegchros (millet)', 'Kegchreai', 'None', 'keng-khreh-a\'-hee', 'Noun Location', 'probably from kegchros (millet); Cenchreae, a port of Corinth:--Cencrea.', 'Cenchrea = \"millet\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eastern harbour of Corinth (i.e. its harbour on the Saronic Gulf) and the emporium of its trade with the Asiatic shores of the Mediterranean, as Lechaeum on the Corinthian Gulf connected it with Italy and the west</OL>'),
(2748, 'Kedrwvn', 'of Hebrew origin (06939)', 'Kedron', 'None', 'ked-rone\'', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin («06939»); Cedron (i.e. Kidron), a brook near Jerusalem:--Cedron.', 'Cedron or Kidron = \"turbid\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name of a winter torrent, rising near Jerusalem and flowing down through a valley of Kidron, having the Mount of Olives on the east, into the Dead Sea</OL>'),
(2749, 'kei\'mai', 'middle voice of a primary verb', 'keimai', '3:654,425', 'ki\'-mahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice of a primary verb; to lie outstretched (literally or figuratively):--be (appointed, laid up, made, set), lay, lie. Compare «5087».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lie<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of an infant<LI>of one buried<LI>of things that quietly cover some spot<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of a city situated on a hill</OL><LI>of things put or set in any place, in ref. to which we often use \"to stand\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of vessels, of a throne, of the site of a city, of grain and other things laid up together, of a foundation</OL></OL><LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be (by God\'s intent) set, i.e. destined, appointed<LI>of laws, to be made, laid down<LI>lies in the power of the evil one, i.e. is held in subjection by the devil</OL></OL>'),
(2750, 'keiriva', 'of uncertain affinity', 'keiria', 'None', 'ki-ree\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain affinity; a swathe, i.e. winding-sheet:--graveclothes.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a band, either for bed-girth, or for tying up a corpse after it has been swathed in linen</OL>'),
(2751, 'keivrw', 'a primary verb', 'keiro', 'None', 'ki\'-ro', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to shear:--shear(-er).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sheer: a sheep<LI>to get or let be shorn<LI>of shearing or cutting short the hair of the head</OL>'),
(2752, 'kevleusma', 'from (2753)', 'keleuma', '3:656,*', 'kel\'-yoo-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2753»; a cry of incitement:--shout.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an order, command, spec. a stimulating cry, either that by which animals are roused and urged on by man, as horses by charioteers, hounds by hunters, etc., or that by which a signal is given to men, e.g. to rowers by the master of a ship, to soldiers by a commander (with a loud summons, a trumpet call)</OL>'),
(2753, 'keleuvw', 'from a primary kello (to urge on)', 'keleuo', 'None', 'kel-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a primary kello (to urge on); \"hail\"; to incite by word, i.e. order:--bid, (at, give) command(-ment).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to command, to order</OL>'),
(2754, 'kenodoxiva', 'from (2755)', 'kenodoxia', '3:662,426', 'ken-od-ox-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2755»; empty glorying, i.e. self-conceit:--vain-glory.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vain glory, groundless, self esteem, empty pride<LI>a vain opinion, error</OL>'),
(2755, 'kenovdoxoß', 'from (2756) and (1391)', 'kenodoxos', '3:662,426', 'ken-od\'-ox-os', 'Adjective', 'from «2756» and «1391»; vainly glorifying, i.e. self-conceited:--desirous of vain-glory.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>glorying without reason, conceited, vain glorious, eager for empty glory</OL>'),
(2756, 'kenovß', 'apparently a primary word', 'kenos', '3:659,426', 'ken-os\'', 'Adjective', 'apparently a primary word; empty (literally or figuratively):--empty, (in) vain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>empty, vain, devoid of truth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of places, vessels, etc. which contain nothing<LI>of men<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>empty handed<LI>without a gift</OL><LI>metaph. destitute of spiritual wealth, of one who boasts of his faith as a transcendent possession, yet is without the fruits of faith<LI>metaph. of endeavours, labours, acts, which result in nothing, vain, fruitless, without effect<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vain of no purpose</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2757, 'kenofwniva', 'from a presumed compound of (2756) and (5456)', 'kenophonia', 'None', 'ken-of-o-nee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a presumed compound of «2756» and «5456»; empty sounding, i.e. fruitless discussion:--vain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>empty discussion, discussion of vain and useless matters</OL>'),
(2758, 'kenovw', 'from (2756)', 'kenoo', '3:661,426', 'ken-o\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2756»; to make empty, i.e. (figuratively) to abase, neutralize, falsify:--make (of none effect, of no reputation, void), be in vain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to empty, make empty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of Christ, he laid aside equality with or the form of God</OL><LI>to make void<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>deprive of force, render vain, useless, of no effect</OL><LI>to make void<OL TYPE=\"b\"><LI>cause a thing to be seen to be empty, hollow, false</OL></OL>'),
(2759, 'kevntron', 'from kenteo (to prick)', 'kentron', '3:663,427', 'ken\'-tron', 'Noun Neuter', 'from kenteo (to prick); a point (\"centre\"), i.e. a sting (figuratively, poison) or goad (figuratively, divine impulse):--prick, sting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a sting, as that of bees, scorpions, locusts. Since animals wound by their sting and even cause death, Paul attributes death, personified as a sting, i.e. a deadly weapon<LI>an iron goad, for urging on oxen, horses and other beasts of burden<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>hence the proverb, \"to kick against the goad\", i.e. to offer vain and perilous or ruinous resistance</OL></OL>'),
(2760, 'kenturivwn', 'of Latin origin', 'kenturion', 'None', 'ken-too-ree\'-ohn', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; a centurion, i.e. captain of one hundred soldiers:--centurion.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>centurion, an officer in the Roman army</OL>'),
(2761, 'kenw\'ß', 'from (2756)', 'kenos', 'None', 'ken-oce\'', 'Adverb', 'adverb from «2756»; vainly, i.e. to no purpose:--in vain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vainly, in vain</OL>'),
(2762, 'keraiva', 'from a presumed derivative of the base of (2768)', 'keraia', 'None', 'ker-ah\'-yah', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of a presumed derivative of the base of «2768»; something horn-like, i.e. (specially) the apex of a Hebrew letter (figuratively, the least particle):--tittle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a little horn<LI>extremity, apex, point<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used by grammarians of the accents and diacritical points. Jesus used it of the little lines or projections, by which the Hebrew letters in other respects similar differ from one another; the meaning is, \"not even the minutest part of the law shall perish\".</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2763, 'kerameuvß', 'from (2766)', 'kerameus', 'None', 'ker-am-yooce\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2766»; a potter:--potter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a potter</OL>'),
(2764, 'keramikovß', 'from (2766)', 'keramikos', 'None', 'ker-am-ik-os\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2766»; made of clay, i.e. earthen:--of a potter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of or belonging to a potter<LI>made of clay, earthen</OL>'),
(2765, 'keravmion', 'from a presumed derivative of (2766)', 'keramion', 'None', 'ker-am\'-ee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of «2766»; an earthenware vessel, i.e. jar:--pitcher.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an earthen vessel, a pot, jar<LI>a jug or pitcher<LI>a water pitcher</OL>'),
(2766, 'kevramoß', 'probably from the base of (2767) (through the idea of mixing clay and water)', 'keramos', 'None', 'ker\'-am-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from the base of «2767» (through the idea of mixing clay and water); earthenware, i.e. a tile (by analogy, a thin roof or awning):--tiling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>clay, potter\'s earth<LI>anything made of clay, earthen ware<LI>a roofing tile<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the roof itself<LI>the phrase \"through the roof\", means through the door in the roof to which a ladder or stairway led up from the street (according to the Rabbis distinguish two ways of entering a house, \"the way through the door\" and \"the way through the roof\"</OL></OL>'),
(2767, 'keravnnumi', 'a prolonged form of a more primary kerao {ker-ah\'-o} (which is used in certain tenses)', 'kerannumi', 'None', 'ker-an\'-noo-mee', 'Verb', 'prolonged form of a more primary kerao ker-ah\'-o (which is used in certain tenses); to mingle, i.e. (by implication) to pour out (for drinking):--fill, pour out. Compare «3396».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mix, mingle<LI>to mix wine, water<LI>to pour out for drinking.</OL>'),
(2768, 'kevraß', 'from a primary kar (the hair of the head)', 'keras', '3:669,428', 'ker\'-as', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a primary kar (the hair of the head); a horn (literally or figuratively):--horn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a horn<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of animals<LI>since animals (esp. bulls) defend themselves with their horns, the horn with the Hebrews (and other nations) is a symbol of strength and courage, and used as such in a variety of phrases<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mighty and valiant helper, the author of deliverance, of the Messiah</OL><LI>a projecting extremity in a shape like a horn, a point, apex: as of an altar</OL></OL>'),
(2769, 'keravtion', 'from a presumed derivative of (2768)', 'keration', 'None', 'ker-at\'-ee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of «2768»; something horned, i.e. (specially) the pod of the carob-tree:--husk.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a little horn<LI>the name of the fruit, Ceratonia silqua or carobtree (called also John\'s Bread [from the notion that its pods, which resemble those of the \"locust\", constituted the food of the Baptist]. This fruit was shaped like a horn and has a sweet taste; it was and is used not only for fattening swine, but as an article of food by the lower classes.</OL>'),
(2770, 'kerdaivnw', 'from (2771)', 'kerdaino', '3:672,428', 'ker-dah\'-ee-no', 'Verb', 'from «2771»; to gain (literally or figuratively):--(get) gain, win.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to gain, acquire, to get gain<LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of gain arising from shunning or escaping from evil (where we say \"to spare one\'s self\", \"be spared\")<LI>to gain any one i.e. to win him over to the kingdom of God, to gain one to faith in Christ<LI>to gain Christ\'s favour and fellowship</OL></OL>'),
(2771, 'kevrdoß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'kerdos', '3:672,428', 'ker\'-dos', 'Noun Neuter', 'of uncertain affinity; gain (pecuniary or genitive case):--gain, lucre.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gain, advantage</OL>'),
(2772, 'kevrma', 'from (2751)', 'kerma', 'None', 'ker\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2751»; a clipping (bit), i.e. (specially) a coin:--money.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>small pieces of money, small coin, change, money</OL>'),
(2773, 'kermatisthvß', 'from a derivative of (2772)', 'kermatistes', 'None', 'ker-mat-is-tace\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a derivative of «2772»; a handler of coins, i.e. money-broker:--changer of money.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a money changer, money broker</OL>'),
(2774, 'kefavlaion', 'from a derivative of (2776)', 'kephalaion', 'None', 'kef-al\'-ah-yon', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a derivative of «2776»; a principal thing, i.e. main point; specially, an amount (of money):--sum.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the chief or main point, the principal thing<LI>the pecuniary sum total of a reckoning, amount<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the principal, capital, as distinguished from the interest<LI>a sum of money, sum</OL></OL>'),
(2775, 'kefalaiovw', 'from the same as (2774)', 'kephalaioo', 'None', 'kef-al-ahee-o\'-o', 'Verb', 'from the same as «2774»; (specially) to strike on the head:--wound in the head.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bring under headings, to sum up, to summarise<LI>to smite or wound in the head, to smite on the cheek</OL>'),
(2776, 'kefalhv', 'from the primary kapto (in the sense of seizing)', 'kephale', '3:673,429', 'kef-al-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the primary kapto (in the sense of seizing); the head (as the part most readily taken hold of), literally or figuratively:--head.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the head, both of men and often of animals. Since the loss of the head destroys life, this word is used in the phrases relating to capital and extreme punishment.<LI>metaph. anything supreme, chief, prominent<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of persons, master lord: of a husband in relation to his wife<LI>of Christ: the Lord of the husband and of the Church<LI>of things: the corner stone</OL></OL>'),
(2777, 'kefalivß', 'from (2776)', 'kephalis', 'None', 'kef-al-is\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2776»; properly, a knob, i.e. (by implication) a roll (by extension from the end of a stick on which the manuscript was rolled):--volume.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a little head<LI>the highest part, extremity of anything<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as the capital of a column<LI>the tips or knobs of the wooden rod around which parchments were rolled were called by this word, because they resembled little heads</OL><LI>the Alexandrian writers transferred the name to the roll or volume itself<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in the roll of the book</OL></OL>'),
(2778, 'khmovw', 'of Latin origin', 'kensos', 'None', 'kane\'-sos', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; properly, an enrollment (\"census\"), i.e. (by implication) a tax:--tribute.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>census (among the Romans, denoting a register and valuation of property in accordance with which taxes were paid), in the NT the tax or tribute levied on individuals and to be paid yearly. (our capitation or poll tax)<LI>the coin with which the tax is paid, tribute money</OL>'),
(2779, 'kh\'poß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'kepos', 'None', 'kay\'-pos', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain affinity; a garden:--garden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a garden</OL>'),
(2780, 'khpourovß', 'from (2779) and ouros (a warden)', 'kepouros', 'None', 'kay-poo-ros\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2779» and ouros (a warden); a garden-keeper, i.e. gardener:--gardener.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a keeper of a garden, a gardener</OL>'),
(2781, 'khrivon', 'diminutive from keos (wax)', 'kerion', 'None', 'kay-ree\'-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'diminutive from keos (wax); a cell for honey, i.e. (collectively) the comb:--(honey-)comb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>honeycomb</OL>'),
(2782, 'khvrugma', 'from (2784)', 'kerugma', '3:714,430', 'kay\'-roog-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2784»; a proclamation (especially of the gospel; by implication, the gospel itself):--preaching.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that which is proclaimed by a herald or public crier, a proclamation by herald<LI>in the NT the message or proclamation of the heralds of God or Christ</OL>'),
(2783, 'kh\'rux', 'from (2784)', 'kerux', '3:683,430', 'kay\'-roox', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2784»; a herald, i.e. of divine truth (especially of the gospel):--preacher.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a herald or messenger vested with public authority, who conveyed the official messages of kings, magistrates, princes, military commanders, or who gave a public summons or demand, and performed various other duties. In the NT God\'s ambassador, and the herald or proclaimer of the divine word.</OL>'),
(2784, 'khruvssw', 'of uncertain affinity', 'kerusso', '3:697,430', 'kay-roos\'-so', 'Verb', 'of uncertain affinity; to herald (as a public crier), especially divine truth (the gospel):--preacher(-er), proclaim, publish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be a herald, to officiate as a herald<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to proclaim after the manner of a herald<LI>always with the suggestion of formality, gravity and an authority which must be listened to and obeyed</OL><LI>to publish, proclaim openly: something which has been done<LI>used of the public proclamation of the gospel and matters pertaining to it, made by John the Baptist, by Jesus, by the apostles and other Christian teachers</OL>'),
(2785, 'kh\'toß', 'probably from the base of (5490)', 'ketos', 'None', 'kay\'-tos', 'Noun Neuter', 'probably from the base of «5490»; a huge fish (as gaping for prey):--whale.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a sea monster, whale, huge fish</OL>'),
(2786, 'Khfa\'ß', 'of Aramaic origin cf (03710)', 'Kephas', '6:100,835', 'kay-fas\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Chaldee origin (compare «03710»); the Rock; Cephas (i.e. Kepha), a surname of Peter:--Cephas.', 'Cephas = \"stone\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>another name for the apostle Peter</OL>'),
(2787, 'kibwtovß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'kibotos', 'None', 'kib-o-tos\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain derivation; a box, i.e. the sacred ark and that of Noah:--ark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a wooden chest or box<LI>in the NT the ark of the covenant, in the temple at Jerusalem<LI>of Noah\'s vessel built in the form of an ark</OL>'),
(2788, 'kiqavra', 'of uncertain affinity', 'kithara', 'None', 'kith-ar\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain affinity; a lyre:--harp.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a harp to which praises of God are sung in heaven</OL>'),
(2789, 'kiqarivzw', 'from (2788)', 'kitharizo', 'None', 'kith-ar-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2788»; to play on a lyre:--harp.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to play upon the harp</OL>'),
(2790, 'kiqarw/dovß', 'from (2788) and a derivative of the same as (5603)', 'kitharoidos', 'None', 'kith-ar-o\'-dos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2788» and a derivative of the same as «5603»; a lyre-singer(-player), i.e. harpist:--harper.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a harper, one who plays the harp and accompanies it with his voice</OL>'),
(2791, 'Kilikiva', 'probably of foreign origin', 'Kilikia', 'None', 'kil-ik-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Location', 'probably of foreign origin; Cilicia, a region of Asia Minor:--Cilicia.', 'Cilicia = \"the land of Celix\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a maritime province in the southeast of Asia Minor, boarding on Pamphylia in the west, Lycaonia and Cappadocia in the north and Syria in the east. Its capital, Tarsus, was the birth place of Paul</OL>'),
(2792, 'kinavmwmon', 'of foreign origin cf (7076)', 'kinamomon', 'None', 'kin-am\'-o-mon', 'Noun Neuter', 'of foreign origin (compare «07076»); cinnamon:--cinnamon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cinnamon was a well known aromatic substance, the rind of \"Laurus cinnamonum\" called \"Korunda-gauhah\" in Ceylon</OL>'),
(2793, 'kinduneuvw', 'from (2794)', 'kinduneuo', 'None', 'kin-doon-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2794»; to undergo peril:--be in danger, be (stand) in jeopardy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be in jeopardy, to be in danger, to put in peril</OL>'),
(2794, 'kivndunoß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'kindunos', 'None', 'kin\'-doo-nos', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; danger:--peril.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a danger, a peril</OL>'),
(2795, 'kinevw', 'from kio (poetic for eimi, to go)', 'kineo', '3:718,435', 'kin-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from kio (poetic for eimi, to go); to stir (transitively), literally or figuratively:--(re-)move(-r), way.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to go, i.e. to move, set in motion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be moved, move: of that motion which is evident in life<LI>to move from a place, to remove</OL><LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to move excite<LI>a riot, disturbance<LI>to throw into commotion</OL></OL>'),
(2796, 'kivnhsiß', 'from (2795)', 'kinesis', 'None', 'kin\'-ay-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2795»; a stirring:--moving.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a moving, agitation</OL>'),
(2797, 'Kivß', 'of Hebrew origin (07027)', 'Kis', 'None', 'kis', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («07027»); Cis (i.e. Kish), an Israelite:--Cis.', 'Kish = \"a snare\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the father of Saul, the first king of Israel</OL>'),
(2798, 'klavdoß', 'from (2806)', 'klados', '3:720,*', 'klad\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', '', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a young tender shoot, broken off for grafting<LI>a branch<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>as the Jewish patriarchs are likened to a root, so their posterity are likened to branches</OL></OL>'),
(2799, 'klaivw', 'of uncertain affinity', 'klaio', '3:722,436', 'klah\'-yo', 'Verb', 'of uncertain affinity; to sob, i.e. wail aloud (whereas 1145 is rather to cry silently):--bewail, weep.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mourn, weep, lament<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>weeping as the sign of pain and grief for the thing signified (i.e. for the pain and grief)<LI>of those who mourn for the dead</OL><LI>to weep for, mourn for, bewail, one</OL>'),
(2800, 'klavsiß', 'from (2806)', 'klasis', '3:726,437', 'klas\'-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2806»; fracture (the act):--breaking.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a breaking</OL>'),
(2801, 'klavsma', 'from (2806)', 'klasma', '3:726,437', 'klas\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2806»; a piece (bit):--broken, fragment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a fragment, broken piece<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>remnants of food</OL></OL>'),
(2802, 'Klau\'da', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Klaude', 'None', 'klow\'-day', 'Noun Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Claude, an island near Crete:--Clauda.', 'Clauda = \"lame\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a small island nearly due west of Cape Malta on the south coast of Crete, and nearly due south of Phoenice</OL>'),
(2803, 'Klaudiva', 'from (2804)', 'Klaudia', 'None', 'klow-dee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «2804»; Claudia, a Christian woman:--Claudia.', 'Claudia = \"lame\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Christian woman</OL>'),
(2804, 'Klauvdioß', 'of Latin origin', 'Klaudios', 'None', 'klow\'-dee-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; Claudius, the name of two Romans:--Claudius.', 'Claudius = \"lame\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>C. Caesar the name of the fourth Roman emperor, who came to power in 41 A.D. and was poisoned by his wife Agrippina, in 54 A.D.<LI>C. Lysias a tribune of the Roman cohort who rescued Paul from the hands of the mob at Jerusalem</OL>'),
(2805, 'klauqmovß', 'from (2799)', 'klauthmos', '3:725,436', 'klowth-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2799»; lamentation:--wailing, weeping, × wept.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>weeping, lamentation</OL>'),
(2806, 'klavw', 'a primary verb', 'klao', '3:726,437', 'klah\'-o', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to break (specially, of bread):--break.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used in the NT of the breaking of bread or communion</OL></OL>'),
(2807, 'kleivß', 'from (2808)', 'kleis', '3:744,439', 'klice', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2808»; a key (as shutting a lock), literally or figuratively:--key.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a key<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>since the keeper of the keys has the power to open and to shut<LI>metaph. in the NT to denote power and authority of various kinds</OL></OL>'),
(2808, 'kleivw', 'a primary verb', 'kleio', 'None', 'kli\'-o', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to close (literally or figuratively):--shut (up).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shut, shut up<LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to cause the heavens to withhold rain<LI>to shut up compassion so that it is like a thing inaccessible to one, to be devoid of pity towards one<LI>to obstruct the entrance into the kingdom of heaven</OL></OL>'),
(2809, 'klevmma', 'from (2813)', 'klemma', 'None', 'klem\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2813»; stealing (properly, the thing stolen, but used of the act):--theft.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>thing stolen<LI>the act of theft</OL>'),
(2810, 'Kleopa\'ß', 'probably contracted from Kleopatros (compound of (2811) and (3962))', 'Kleopas', 'None', 'kleh-op\'-as', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably contracted from Kleopatros (compound of «2811» and «3962»); Cleopas, a Christian:--Cleopas.', 'Cleopas = \"of a renowned father\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the two disciples who were going to Emmaus on the day of the resurrection</OL>'),
(2811, 'klevoß', 'from a shorter form of (2564)', 'kleos', 'None', 'kleh\'-os', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a shorter form of «2564»; renown (as if being called):--glory.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>rumour, report<LI>glory, praise</OL>'),
(2812, 'klevpthß', 'from (2813)', 'kleptes', '3:754,441', 'klep\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2813»; a stealer (literally or figuratively):--thief. Compare «3027».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an embezzler, pilferer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the name is transferred to false teachers, who do not care to instruct men, but abuse their confidence for their own gain</OL></OL>'),
(2813, 'klevptw', 'a primary verb', 'klepto', '3:754,441', 'klep\'-to', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to filch:--steal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to steal<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to commit a theft<LI>take away by theft i.e take away by stealth</OL></OL>'),
(2814, 'klh\'ma', 'from (2806)', 'klema', '3:757,441', 'kaly\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2806»; a limb or shoot (as if broken off):--branch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a tender and flexible branch<LI>spec. the shoot or branch of a vine, a vine sprout</OL>'),
(2815, 'Klhvmhß', 'of Latin origin', 'Klemes', 'None', 'klay\'-mace', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; merciful; Clemes (i.e. Clemens), a Christian:--Clement.', 'Clement = \"mild, merciful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a companion of Paul and apparently a member of the church of Philippi. According to tradition, he is identical with that Clement who was bishop of Rome towards the close of the first century.</OL>'),
(2816, 'klhronomevw', 'from (2818)', 'kleronomeo', '3:767,442', 'klay-ron-om-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2818»; to be an heir to (literally or figuratively):--be heir, (obtain by) inherit(-ance).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to receive a lot, receive by lot<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>esp. to receive a part of an inheritance, receive as an inheritance, obtain by right of inheritance<LI>to be an heir, to inherit</OL><LI>to receive the portion assigned to one, receive an allotted portion, receive as one\'s own or as a possession<LI>to become partaker of, to obtain</OL>'),
(2817, 'klhronomiva', 'from (2818)', 'kleronomia', '3:767,442', 'klay-ron-om-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2818»; heirship, i.e. (concretely) a patrimony or (genitive case) a possession:--inheritance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inheritance, property received (or to be received) by inheritance<LI>what is given to one as a possession<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the eternal blessedness of the consummated kingdom of God which is to be expected after the visible return of Christ<LI>the share which an individual will have in that eternal blessedness</OL></OL>'),
(2818, 'klhronovmoß', 'from (2819) and the base of (3551) (in its original sense of partitioning, i.e. [reflexively] getting by apportionment)', 'kleronomos', '3:767,442', 'klay-ron-om\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2819» and the base of «3551» (in its original sense of partitioning, i.e. (reflexively) getting by apportionment); a sharer by lot, i.e. inheritor (literally or figuratively); by implication, a possessor:--heir.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one who receives by lot, an heir<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an heir<LI>in Messianic usage, one who receives his allotted possession by right of sonship</OL><LI>one who has acquired or obtained the portion allotted to him</OL>'),
(2819, 'klh\'roß', 'probably from (2806) (through the idea of using bits of wood, etc., for the purpose)', 'kleros', '3:758,442', 'klay\'-ros', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «2806» (through the idea of using bits of wood, etc., for the purpose; a die (for drawing chances); by implication, a portion (as if so secured); by extension, an acquisition (especially a patrimony, figuratively):--heritage, inheritance, lot, part.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an object used in casting or drawing lots, which was either a pebble, or a potsherd, or a bit of wood<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the lots of several persons concerned, inscribed with their names, were thrown together into a vase, which was then shaken, and he whose lot fell out first upon the ground was the one chosen</OL><LI>what is obtained by lot, allotted portion<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a portion of the ministry common to the apostles<LI>used of the part which one will have in eternal salvation<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of salvation itself<LI>the eternal salvation which God has assigned to the saints</OL><LI>of persons<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>those whose care and oversight has been assigned to one [allotted charge], used of Christian churches, the administration of which falls to the lot of presbyters</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2820, 'klhrovw', 'from (2819)', 'kleroo', '3:764,442', 'klay-ro\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2819»; to allot, i.e. (figuratively) to assign (a privilege):--obtain an inheritance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cast lots, determine by lot<LI>to choose by lot<LI>to allot, assign by lot<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>on to another as a possession</OL><LI>in NT: to make a lot, i.e. a heritage, private possession</OL>'),
(2821, 'klh\'siß', 'from a shorter form of (2564)', 'klesis', '3:491,394', 'klay\'-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a shorter form of «2564»; an invitation (figuratively):--calling.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a calling, calling to<LI>a call, invitation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to a feast<LI>of the divine invitation to embrace salvation of God</OL></OL>'),
(2822, 'klhtovß', 'from the same as (2821)', 'kletos', '3:494,394', 'klay-tos\'', 'Adjective', 'from the same as «2821»; invited, i.e. appointed, or (specially), a saint:--called.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>called, invited (to a banquet)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>invited (by God in the proclamation of the Gospel) to obtain eternal salvation in the kingdom through Christ<LI>called to (the discharge of) some office<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>divinely selected and appointed</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2823, 'klivbanoß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'klibanos', 'None', 'klib\'-an-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; an earthen pot used for baking in:--oven.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a clibanus, a earthen vessel for baking bread. It was broader at the bottom than above at the orifice, and when sufficiently heated by a fire kindled within, the dough was baked by being spread upon the outside. [but according to others, the dough was baked by being placed inside and the fire or coals outside, the vessel being perforated with small holes that the heat might better penetrate.<LI>a furnace, oven</OL>'),
(2824, 'klivma', 'from (2827)', 'klima', 'None', 'klee\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2827»; a slope, i.e. (specially) a \"clime\" or tract of country:--part, region.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an inclination, slope, declivity<LI>the [supposed] sloping of the earth from the equator towards the poles, a zone<LI>a tract of land, a region</OL>'),
(2825, 'klinavrion', 'from (2827)', 'kline', 'None', 'klee\'-nay', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2827»; a couch (for sleep, sickness, sitting or eating):--bed, table.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a small bed, a couch<LI>a couch to recline on at meals<LI>a couch on which a sick man is carried</OL>'),
(2826, 'klinivdion', 'from a presumed derivative of (2825)', 'klinidion', 'None', 'klin-id\'-ee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of «2825»; a pallet or little couch:--bed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a small bed, a couch</OL>'),
(2827, 'klivnw', 'a root word', 'klino', 'None', 'klee\'-no', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to slant or slope, i.e. incline or recline (literally or figuratively):--bow (down), be far spent, lay, turn to flight, wear away.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>transitively<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to incline, bow<LI>to cause to fall back<LI>to recline<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in a place for repose</OL></OL><LI>intransitively<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to incline one\'s self<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of the declining of the day</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2828, 'klisiva', 'from a derivative of (2827)', 'klisia', 'None', 'klee-see\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a derivative of «2827»; properly, reclination, i.e. (concretely and specially), a party at a meal:--company.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a hut erected to pass the night in<LI>a tent<LI>anything to recline on<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a chair in which to lean back the head<LI>a reclining chair</OL><LI>a company reclining<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a row or party of persons reclining at meal</OL></OL>'),
(2829, 'klophv', 'from (2813)', 'klope', 'None', 'klop-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2813»; stealing:--theft.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>theft</OL>'),
(2830, 'kluvdwn', 'from kluzo (to billow or dash over)', 'kludon', 'None', 'kloo\'-dohn', 'Noun Masculine', 'from kluzo (to billow or dash over); a surge of the sea (literally or figuratively):--raging, wave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a dashing or surging wave, a surge, a violent agitation of the sea</OL>'),
(2831, 'kludwnivzomai', 'middle voice from (2830)', 'kludonizomai', 'None', 'kloo-do-nid\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «2830»; to surge, i.e. (figuratively) to fluctuate:--toss to and fro.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be tossed by the waves<LI>metaph. to be agitated (like the waves) mentally</OL>'),
(2832, 'Klwpa\'ß', 'of Aramaic origin (corresponding to (0256))', 'Klopas', 'None', 'klo-pas\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Chaldee origin (corresponding to «0256»); Clopas, an Israelite:--Cleophas.', 'Cleophas = \"my exchanges\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the father of James the less, the husband of Mary the sister of the mother of Jesus</OL>'),
(2833, 'knhvqw', 'from a primary knao (to scrape)', 'knetho', 'None', 'knay\'-tho', 'Verb', 'from a primary knao (to scrape); to scratch, i.e. (by implication) to tickle:--X itching.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to scratch, tickle, make to itch<LI>to itch<LI>desirous of hearing something pleasant</OL>'),
(2834, 'Knivdoß', 'probably of foreign origin', 'Knidos', 'None', 'knee\'-dos', 'Noun Location', 'probably of foreign origin; Cnidus, a place in Asia Minor:--Cnidus.', 'Cnidus or Gnidus = \"nettled\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a peninsula [now Cape Crio] and a city by the same name, situated at the extreme south west of the peninsula of Asia Minor, on a promontory now called Cape Crio, which projects between the islands of Cos and Rhodes</OL>'),
(2835, 'kodravnthß', 'of Latin origin', 'kodrantes', 'None', 'kod-ran\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; a quadrans, i.e. the fourth part of an as:--farthing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a quadrans (about the fourth part of an \"as\"); in the NT a coin equal to one half the Attic chalcus worth about 3/8 of a cent</OL>'),
(2836, 'koiliva', 'from koilos (\"hollow\")', 'koilia', '3:786,446', 'koy-lee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from koilos (\"hollow\"); a cavity, i.e. (especially) the abdomen; by implication, the matrix; figuratively, the heart:--belly, womb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the whole belly, the entire cavity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the upper [i.e. stomach] and the lower belly are distinguished</OL><LI>the lower belly, the lower region, the receptacle of the excrement<LI>the gullet<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be given up to the pleasures of the palate, to gluttony</OL><LI>the womb, the place where the foetus is conceived and nourished until birth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the uterus of animals</OL><LI>the innermost part of a man, the soul, heart as the seat of thought, feeling, choice</OL>'),
(2837, 'koimavw', 'from (2749)', 'koimao', 'None', 'koy-mah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2749»; to put to sleep, i.e. (passively or reflexively) to slumber; figuratively, to decease:--(be a-, fall a-, fall on) sleep, be dead.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause to sleep, put to sleep<LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to still, calm, quiet<LI>to fall asleep, to sleep<LI>to die</OL></OL>'),
(2838, 'koivmhsiß', 'from (2837)', 'koimesis', 'None', 'koy\'-may-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2837»; sleeping, i.e. (by implication) repose:--taking of rest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a reposing, taking rest<LI>a lying, reclining</OL>'),
(2839, 'koinovß', 'probably from (4862)', 'koinos', '3:789,447', 'koy-nos\'', 'Adjective', 'probably from «4862»; common, i.e. (literally) shared by all or several, or (ceremonially) profane:--common, defiled, unclean, unholy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>common<LI>common i.e. ordinary, belonging to generality<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>by the Jews, unhallowed, profane, Levitically unclean</OL></OL>'),
(2840, 'koinovw', 'from (2839)', 'koinoo', '3:809,447', 'koy-no\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2839»; to make (or consider) profane (ceremonially):--call common, defile, pollute, unclean.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make common<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to make (Levitically) unclean, render unhallowed, defile, profane<LI>to declare or count unclean</OL></OL>'),
(2841, 'koinwnevw', 'from (2844)', 'koinoneo', '3:797,447', 'koy-no-neh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2844»; to share with others (objectively or subjectively):--communicate, distribute, be partaker.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to come into communion or fellowship with, to become a sharer, be made a partner<LI>to enter into fellowship, join one\'s self to an associate, make one\'s self a sharer or partner</OL>'),
(2842, 'koinwniva', 'from (2844)', 'koinonia', '3:797,447', 'koy-nohn-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2844»; partnership, i.e. (literally) participation, or (social) intercourse, or (pecuniary) benefaction:--(to) communicate(-ation), communion, (contri-)distribution, fellowship.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fellowship, association, community, communion, joint participation, intercourse<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the share which one has in anything, participation<LI>intercourse, fellowship, intimacy<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the right hand as a sign and pledge of fellowship (in fulfilling the apostolic office)</OL><LI>a gift jointly contributed, a collection, a contribution, as exhibiting an embodiment and proof of fellowship</OL></OL>'),
(2843, 'koinwnikovß', 'from (2844)', 'koinonikos', '3:809,447', 'koy-no-nee-kos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2844»; communicative, i.e. (pecuniarily) liberal:--willing to communicate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>social, sociable, ready and apt to form and maintain communion and fellowship<LI>inclined to make others sharers in one\'s possessions, inclined to impart, free in giving, liberal</OL>'),
(2844, 'koinwnovß', 'from (2839)', 'koinonos', '3:797,447', 'koy-no-nos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2839»; a sharer, i.e. associate:--companion, × fellowship, partaker, partner.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a partner, associate, comrade, companion<LI>a partner, sharer, in anything<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the altar in Jerusalem on which the sacrifices are offered<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sharing in the worship of the Jews</OL><LI>partakers of (or with) demons<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>brought into fellowship with them, because they are the authors of heathen worship</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2845, 'koivth', 'from (2749)', 'koite', 'None', 'koy\'-tay', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2749»; a couch; by extension, cohabitation; by implication, the male sperm:--bed, chambering, × conceive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place for laying down, resting, sleeping in<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a bed, couch</OL><LI>the marriage bed<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of adultery</OL><LI>cohabitation, whether lawful or unlawful<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>sexual intercourse</OL></OL>'),
(2846, 'koitwvn', 'from (2845)', 'koiton', 'None', 'koy-tone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2845»; a bedroom:--+ chamberlain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a sleeping room, bed chamber<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the officer who is over the bed chamber, the chamberlain</OL></OL>'),
(2847, 'kovkkinoß', 'from (2848) (from the kernel-shape of the insect)', 'kokkinos', '3:812,450', 'kok\'-kee-nos', 'Adjective', 'from «2848» (from the kernel-shape of the insect); crimson-colored:--scarlet (colour, coloured).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>crimson, scarlet coloured. A kernel, the grain or berry of the \"ilex coccifera\"; these berries are the clusters of the eggs of a female insect, the \"kermes\" (resembling the cochineal), and when collected and pulverised produces a red which was used in dyeing (Pliny)<LI>scarlet cloth or clothing</OL>'),
(2848, 'kovkkoß', 'apparently a primary word', 'kokkos', '3:810,450', 'kok\'-kos', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently a primary word; a kernel of seed:--corn, grain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a grain</OL>'),
(2849, 'kolavzw', 'from kolos (dwarf)', 'kolazo', '3:814,451', 'kol-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from kolos (dwarf); properly, to curtail, i.e. (figuratively) to chastise (or reserve for infliction):--punish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lop or prune, as trees and wings<LI>to curb, check, restrain<LI>to chastise, correct, punishment<LI>to cause to be punished</OL>'),
(2850, 'kolakeiva', 'from a derivative of kolax (a fawner)', 'kolakeia', '3:817,451', 'kol-ak-i\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a derivative of kolax (a fawner); flattery:--X flattering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flattery, flattering discourse</OL>'),
(2851, 'kovlasiß', 'from (2849)', 'kolasis', '3:816,451', 'kol\'-as-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2849»; penal infliction:--punishment, torment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>correction, punishment, penalty</OL>'),
(2852, 'kolafivzw', 'from a derivative of the base of (2849)', 'kolaphizo', '3:818,451', 'kol-af-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from a derivative of the base of «2849»; to rap with the fist:--buffet.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strike with the fist, give one a blow with the fist<LI>to maltreat, treat with violence and contumely</OL>'),
(2853, 'kollavw', 'from kolla (\"glue\")', 'kollao', '3:822,452', 'kol-lah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from kolla (\"glue\"); to glue, i.e. (passively or reflexively) to stick (figuratively):--cleave, join (self), keep company.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to glue, to glue together, cement, fasten together<LI>to join or fasten firmly together<LI>to join one\'s self to, cleave to</OL>'),
(2854, 'kollouvrion', 'from a presumed derivative of kollura (a cake - prob akin to the base of (2853))', 'kollourion', 'None', 'kol-loo\'-ree-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of kollura (a cake; prob akin to the base of «2853»); properly, a poultice (as made of or in the form of crackers), i.e. (by analogy) a plaster:-- eyesalve.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a preparation composed of various materials and used as a remedy for tender eyelids</OL>'),
(2855, 'kollubisthvß', 'from a presumed derivative of kollubos (a small coin - probably akin to (2854))', 'kollubistes', 'None', 'kol-loo-bis-tace\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a presumed derivative of kollubos (a small coin; probably akin to «2854»); a coin-dealer:--(money-)changer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a money-changer, banker</OL>'),
(2856, 'kolobovw', 'from a derivative of the base of (2849)', 'koloboo', '3:823,452', 'kol-ob-o\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a derivative of the base of «2849»; to dock, i.e. (figuratively) abridge:--shorten.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mutilate<LI>in NT: to shorten, abridge, curtail</OL>'),
(2857, 'Kolossaiv', 'apparently feminine plural of kolossos (\"colossal\")', 'Kolossai', 'None', 'kol-os-sah\'-ee', 'Noun Location', 'apparently feminine plural of kolossos (\"colossal\"); Colossae, a place in Asia Minor:--Colosse.', 'Colosse = \"monstrosities\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anciently a large and flourishing city, but in Strabo\'s time a small town of Phrygia Major situated on the Lycus not far from its junction with the Maeander and in the neighbourhood of Laodicea and Hierapolis</OL>'),
(2858, 'from (2857)', 'Kolossaeus', 'Kolossaeus', 'kol-os-sayoos\'', 'kol-os-sayoos\'', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Colossian</OL>', 'from «2857»; a Colossaean, (i.e. inhabitant of Colossae:--Colossian.', ''),
(2859, 'kovlpoß', 'apparently a primary word', 'kolpos', '3:824,452', 'kol\'-pos', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently a primary word; the bosom; by analogy, a bay:--bosom, creek.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the front of the body between the arms<LI>the bosom of a garment, i.e. the hollow formed by the upper forepart of a rather loose garment bound by a girdle or sash, used for keeping and carrying things (the fold or pocket)<LI>a bay of the sea</OL>'),
(2860, 'kolumbavw', 'from kolumbos (a diver)', 'kolumbao', 'None', 'kol-oom-bah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from kolumbos (a diver); to plunge into water:--swim.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dive, to swim</OL>'),
(2861, 'kolumbhvqra', 'from (2860)', 'kolumbethra', 'None', 'kol-oom-bay\'-thrah', 'Noun Feminine', 'a diving-place, i.e. pond for bathing (or swimming):--pool.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a place for diving, a swimming hole, a reservoir or pool for bathing</OL>'),
(2862, 'kolwniva', 'of Latin origin', 'kolonia', 'None', 'kol-o-nee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'of Latin origin; a Roman \"colony\" for veterans:--colony.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a colony<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the city of Philippi is so called, where Octavius had planted a Roman colony</OL></OL>'),
(2863, 'komavw', 'from (2864)', 'komao', 'None', 'kom-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2864»; to wear tresses of hair:--have long hair.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to let the hair grow, have long hair</OL>'),
(2864, 'kovmh', 'apparently from the same as (2865)', 'kome', 'None', 'kom\'-ay', 'Noun Feminine', 'apparently from the same as «2865»; the hair of the head (locks, as ornamental, and thus differing from «2359»; which properly denotes merely the scalp):--hair.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hair, head of hair</OL>'),
(2865, 'komivzw', 'from a primary komeo (to tend, i.e. take care of)', 'komizo', 'None', 'kom-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from a primary komeo (to tend, i.e. take care of); properly, to provide for, i.e. (by implication) to carry off (as if from harm; genitive case obtain):--bring, receive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to care for, take care of, provide for<LI>to take up or carry away in order to care for and preserve<LI>to carry away, bear off<LI>to carry, bear, bring to, to carry away for one\'s self, to carry off what is one\'s own, to bring back<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to receive, obtain: the promised blessing<LI>to receive what was previously one\'s own, to get back, receive back, recover</OL></OL>'),
(2866, 'komyovteron', 'neuter comparative of a derivative of the base of (2865) (meaning properly, well dressed, i.e. nice)', 'kompsoteron', 'None', 'komp-sot\'-er-on', 'Adverb', 'neuter comparative of a derivative of the base of 2865 (meaning, properly, well dressed, i.e. nice); figuratively, convalescent:--+ began to amend.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>more finely, better</OL>'),
(2867, 'koniavw', 'from konia (dust, by analogy, lime)', 'koniao', '3:827,453', 'kon-ee-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from konia (dust; by analogy, lime); to whitewash:--whiten.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cover with lime, plaster over, whitewash<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the Jews were accustomed to whitewash the entrances to their sepulchres, as a warning against defilement by touching them<LI>term applied to a hypocrite who conceals his malice under an outward assumption of piety</OL></OL>'),
(2868, 'koniortovß', 'from the base of (2867) and ornumi (to \"rouse\")', 'koniortos', 'None', 'kon-ee-or-tos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the base of «2867» and ornumi (to \"rouse\"); pulverulence (as blown about):--dust.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>raised dust, flying dust<LI>dust</OL>'),
(2869, 'kopavzw', 'from (2873)', 'kopazo', 'None', 'kop-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2873»; to tire, i.e. (figuratively) to relax:--cease.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to grow weary or tired<LI>to cease from violence, cease raging</OL>'),
(2870, 'kopetovß', 'from (2875)', 'kopetos', '3:830,453', 'kop-et-os\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2875»; mourning (properly, by beating the breast):--lamentation.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lamentation with beating of the breast as a sign of grief</OL>'),
(2871, 'kophv', 'from (2875)', 'kope', 'None', 'kop-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2875»; cutting, i.e. carnage:--slaughter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the act of cutting, a cut<LI>a cutting in pieces, slaughter</OL>'),
(2872, 'kopiavw', 'from a derivative of (2873)', 'kopiao', '3:827,453', 'kop-ee-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a derivative of «2873»; to feel fatigue; by implication, to work hard:--(bestow) labour, toil, be wearied.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to grow weary, tired, exhausted (with toil or burdens or grief)<LI>to labour with wearisome effort, to toil<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of bodily labour</OL></OL>'),
(2873, 'kovpoß', 'from (2875)', 'kopos', '3:827,453', 'kop\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2875»; a cut, i.e. (by analogy) toil (as reducing the strength), literally or figuratively; by implication, pains:--labour, + trouble, weariness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a beating<LI>a beating of the breast with grief, sorrow<LI>labour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>trouble<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cause one trouble, make work for him</OL><LI>intense labour united with trouble and toil</OL></OL>'),
(2874, 'kopriva', 'from kopros (ordure, perhaps akin to (2875))', 'kopria', 'None', 'kop-ree\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from kopros (ordure; perhaps akin to «2875»); manure:--dung(-hill).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dung, manure</OL>'),
(2875, 'kovptw', 'a root word', 'kopto', '3:830,453', 'kop\'-to', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to \"chop\"; specially, to beat the breast in grief:--cut down, lament, mourn, (be-)wail. Compare the base of «5114».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut, strike, smite<LI>to cut from, cut off<LI>to beat one\'s breast for grief</OL>'),
(2876, 'kovrax', 'perhaps from (2880)', 'korax', 'None', 'kor\'-ax', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps from «2880»; a crow (from its voracity):--raven.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a raven</OL>'),
(2877, 'koravsion', 'from a presumed derivative of kore (a maiden)', 'korasion', 'None', 'kor-as\'-ee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of kore (a maiden); a (little) girl:--damsel, maid.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a girl, damsel, maiden</OL>'),
(2878, 'korba\'n', 'of Hebrew and Aramaic origin respectively (07133)', 'korban', '3:860,459', 'kor-ban\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew and Chaldee origin respectively («07133»); a votive offering and the offering; a consecrated present (to the Temple fund); by extension (the latter term) the Treasury itself, i.e. the room where the contribution boxes stood:--Corban, treasury.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a gift offered (or to be offered) to God<LI>the sacred treasury</OL>'),
(2879, 'Korev', 'of Hebrew origin (07141)', 'Kore', 'None', 'kor-eh\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («07141»); Core (i.e. Korach), an Israelite:--Core.', 'Korah = \"baldness\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a man who, with others, rebelled against Moses</OL>'),
(2880, 'korevnnumi', 'a root word', 'korennumi', 'None', 'kor-en\'-noo-mee', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to cram, i.e. glut or sate:--eat enough, full.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to satiate, sate, satisfy</OL>'),
(2881, 'Korivnqioß', 'from (2882)', 'Korinthios', 'None', 'kor-in\'-thee-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2882»; a Corinthian, i.e. inhabitant of Corinth:--Corinthian.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Corinthian, and inhabitant of Corinth</OL>'),
(2882, 'Kovrinqoß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Korinthos', 'None', 'kor\'-in-thos', 'Noun Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Corinthus, a city of Greece:--Corinth.', 'Corinth = \"satiated\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an ancient and famous city of Greece, on the Isthmus of Corinth, and about 40 miles (65 km) west of Athens</OL>'),
(2883, 'Kornhvlioß', 'of Latin origin', 'Kornelios', 'None', 'kor-nay\'-lee-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; Cornelius, a Roman:--Cornelius.', 'Cornelius = \"of a horn\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Roman centurion of the Italian cohort stationed in Caesarea who converted to Christianity</OL>'),
(2884, 'kovroß', 'of Hebrew origin (03734)', 'koros', 'None', 'kor\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («03734»); a cor, i.e. a specific measure:--measure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a corus or cor, the largest Hebrew dry measure (i.e, for wheat, meal etc.) about 10 to 11 bushels (350 to 400 l)</OL>'),
(2885, 'kosmevw', 'from (2889)', 'kosmeo', '3:867,459', 'kos-meh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2889»; to put in proper order, i.e. decorate (literally or figuratively); specially, to snuff (a wick):--adorn, garnish, trim.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to put in order, arrange, make ready, prepare<LI>to ornament, adore<LI>metaph. to embellish with honour, gain honour</OL>'),
(2886, 'kosmikovß', 'from (2889) (in its secondary sense)', 'kosmikos', '3:897,459', 'kos-mee-kos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2889» (in its secondary sense); terrene (\"cosmic\"), literally (mundane) or figuratively (corrupt):--worldly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of or belonging to the world<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>relating to the universe<LI>earthly<LI>worldly, i.e. having the character of this present corrupt age</OL></OL>'),
(2887, 'kovsmioß', 'from (2889) (in its primary sense)', 'kosmios', '3:895,459', 'kos\'-mee-os', 'Adjective', 'from «2889» (in its primary sense); orderly, i.e. decorous:--of good behaviour, modest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>well arranged, seemly, modest</OL>'),
(2888, 'kosmokravtwr', 'from (2889) and (2902)', 'kosmokrator', '3:913,466', 'kos-mok-fat\'-ore', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2889» and «2902»; a world-ruler, an epithet of Satan:--ruler.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lord of the world, prince of this age<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the devil and his demons</OL></OL>'),
(2889, 'kovsmoß', 'probably from the base of (2865)', 'kosmos', '3:868,459', 'kos\'-mos', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from the base of «2865»; orderly arrangement, i.e. decoration; by implication, the world (in a wide or narrow sense, including its inhabitants, literally or figuratively (morally)):--adorning, world.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an apt and harmonious arrangement or constitution, order, government<LI>ornament, decoration, adornment, i.e. the arrangement of the stars, \'the heavenly hosts\', as the ornament of the heavens. 1 Pet. 3:<LI>the world, the universe<LI>the circle of the earth, the earth<LI>the inhabitants of the earth, men, the human family<LI>the ungodly multitude; the whole mass of men alienated from God, and therefore hostile to the cause of Christ<LI>world affairs, the aggregate of things earthly<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the whole circle of earthly goods, endowments riches, advantages, pleasures, etc, which although hollow and frail and fleeting, stir desire, seduce from God and are obstacles to the cause of Christ</OL><LI>any aggregate or general collection of particulars of any sort<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the Gentiles as contrasted to the Jews (Rom. 11:12 etc)<LI>of believers only, John 1:29; 3:16; 3:17; 6:33; 12:47 1 Cor. 4:9; 2 Cor. 5:19</OL></OL>'),
(2890, 'Kouvartoß', 'of Latin origin (fourth)', 'Kouartos', 'None', 'koo\'-ar-tos', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin (fourth); Quartus, a Christian:--Quartus.', 'Quartus = \"fourth\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Roman; probably before he lived at Rome, and therefore sends his salutations to the Christians there: he is mentioned among the seventy disciples, and said to be bishop of Berytus. (Gill)</OL>'),
(2891, 'kou\'m', 'of Aramaic origin (06966)', 'koumi', 'None', 'koo\'-mee', 'Verb', 'of Chaldee origin («06966»); cumi (i.e. rise!):--cumi.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>arise</OL>'),
(2892, 'koustwdiva', 'of Latin origin', 'koustodia', 'None', 'koos-to-dee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'of Latin origin; \"custody\", i.e. a Roman sentry:--watch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>guard: used of Roman soldiers guarding the sepulchre of Christ</OL>'),
(2893, 'koufivzw', 'from kouphos (light in weight)', 'kouphizo', 'None', 'koo-fid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from kouphos (light in weight); to unload:--lighten.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be light<LI>to lighten<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a ship by throwing the cargo overboard</OL></OL>'),
(2894, 'kovfinoß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'kophinos', 'None', 'kof\'-ee-nos', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; a (small) basket:--basket.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a basket, wicker basket</OL>'),
(2895, 'kravbattoß', 'probably of foreign origin', 'krabbatos', 'None', 'krab\'-bat-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably of foreign origin; a mattress:--bed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a pallet, camp bed (a rather simple bed holding only one person)</OL>'),
(2896, 'kravzw', 'a primary word', 'krazo', '3:898,465', 'krad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; properly, to \"croak\" (as a raven) or scream, i.e. (genitive case) to call aloud (shriek, exclaim, intreat):--cry (out).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to croak<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the cry of a raven<LI>hence, to cry out, cry aloud, vociferate<LI>to cry or pray for vengeance</OL><LI>to cry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>cry out aloud, speak with a loud voice</OL></OL>'),
(2897, 'kraipavlh', 'probably from the same as (726)', 'kraipale', 'None', 'krahee-pal\'-ay', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from the same as «726»; properly, a headache (as a seizure of pain) from drunkenness, i.e. (by implication) a debauch (by analogy, a glut):--surfeiting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the giddiness and headache caused by drinking wine to excess</OL>'),
(2898, 'kranivon', 'diminutive of a derivative of the base of (2768)', 'kranion', 'None', 'kran-ee\'-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'diminutive of a derivative of the base of «2768»; a skull (\"cranium\"):--Calvary, skull.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a skull</OL>'),
(2899, 'kravspedon', 'of uncertain derivation', 'kraspedon', '3:904,466', 'kras\'-ped-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'of uncertain derivation; a margin, i.e. (specially), a fringe or tassel:--border, hem.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the extremity or prominent part of a thing, edge, skirt, margin<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the fringe of a garment<LI>in the NT a little appendage hanging down from the edge of the mantle or cloak, made of twisted wool<LI>a tassel, tuft: the Jews had such appendages attached to their mantles to remind them of the law</OL></OL>'),
(2900, 'krataiovß', 'from (2904)', 'krataios', '3:912,466', 'krat-ah-yos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2904»; powerful:--mighty.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mighty<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the mighty power of God</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(2901, 'krataiovw', 'from (2900)', 'krataioo', '3:912,466', 'krat-ah-yo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2900»; to empower, i.e. (passively) increase in vigor:--be strengthened, be (wax) strong.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to strengthen, make strong<LI>to be made strong, to increase in strength, to grow strong</OL>'),
(2902, 'kratevw', 'from (2904)', 'krateo', '3:910,466', 'krat-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «2904»; to use strength, i.e. seize or retain (literally or figuratively):--hold (by, fast), keep, lay hand (hold) on, obtain, retain, take (by).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to have power, be powerful<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be chief, be master of, to rule</OL><LI>to get possession of<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to become master of, to obtain<LI>to take hold of<LI>to take hold of, take, seize<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lay hands on one in order to get him into one\'s power</OL></OL><LI>to hold<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to hold in the hand<LI>to hold fast, i.e. not discard or let go<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to keep carefully and faithfully</OL><LI>to continue to hold, to retain<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of death continuing to hold one<LI>to hold in check, restrain</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2903, 'kravtistoß', 'superlative of a derivative of (2904)', 'kratistos', 'None', 'krat\'-is-tos', 'Adjective', 'superlative of a derivative of «2904»; strongest, i.e. (in dignity) very honorable:--most excellent (noble).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mightiest, strongest, noblest, most illustrious, best, most excellent<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used in addressing men of prominent rank or office</OL></OL>'),
(2904, 'kravtoß', 'perhaps a primary word', 'kratos', '3:905,466', 'krat\'-os', 'Noun Neuter', 'perhaps a primary word; vigor (\"great\") (literally or figuratively):--dominion, might(-ily), power, strength.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>force, strength<LI>power, might: mighty with great power<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a mighty deed, a work of power</OL><LI>dominion</OL>'),
(2905, 'kraugavzw', 'from (2906)', 'kraugazo', '3:898,465', 'krow-gad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2906»; to clamor:--cry out.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cry out, cry aloud, to shout, to cry out to one</OL>'),
(2906, 'kraughv', 'from (2896)', 'krauge', '3:898,465', 'krow-gay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «2896»; an outcry (in notification, tumult or grief):--clamour, cry(-ing).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a crying, outcry, clamour</OL>'),
(2907, 'krevaß', 'perhaps a primary word', 'kreas', 'None', 'kreh\'-as', 'Noun Neuter', 'perhaps a primary word; (butcher\'s) meat:--flesh.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>(the) flesh (of a sacrificed animal)</OL>'),
(2908, 'krei\'sson', 'neuter of an alternate form of (2909)', 'kreisson', 'None', 'krice\'-son', 'Adverb', 'neuter of an alternate form of «2909»; (as noun) better, i.e. greater advantage:--better.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>better</OL>'),
(2909, 'kreivttwn', 'comparative of a derivative of (2904)', 'kreitton', 'None', 'krite\'-tohn', 'Adjective', 'comparative of a derivative of «2904»; stronger, i.e. (figuratively) better, i.e. nobler:--best, better.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>more useful, more serviceable, more advantageous<LI>more excellent</OL>'),
(2910, 'kremavnnumi', 'a prolonged form of a primary verb', 'kremannumi', '3:915,468', 'krem-an\'-noo-mee', 'Verb', 'a prolonged form of a primary verb; to hang:--hang.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hang up, suspend<LI>to be suspended, to hang<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used of one hanging on a cross<LI>used of the Law and the Prophets, they is summed up or hanging on two precepts</OL></OL>'),
(2911, 'krhmnovß', 'from (2910)', 'kremnos', 'None', 'krame-nos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2910»; overhanging, i.e. a precipice:--steep place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a steep place, a precipice</OL>'),
(2912, 'Krhvß', 'from (2914)', 'Kres', 'None', 'krace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2914»; a Cretan, i.e. inhabitant of Crete:--Crete, Cretian.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Cretan, an inhabitant of the island of Crete</OL>'),
(2913, 'Krhvskhß', 'of Latin origin', 'Kreskes', 'None', 'krace\'-kace', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; growing; Cresces (i.e. Crescens), a Christian:--Crescens.', 'Crescens = \"growing\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an assistant of Paul, said to be one of the seventy disciples</OL>'),
(2914, 'Krhvth', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Krete', 'None', 'kray\'-tay', 'Noun Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Crete, an island in the Mediterranean:--Crete.', 'Crete = \"fleshy\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the largest and most fertile island of the Mediterranean archipelago or Aegean Sea, now the modern Candia</OL>'),
(2915, 'kriqhv', 'f uncertain derivation', 'krithe', 'None', 'kree-thay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain derivation; barley:--barley.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>barley</OL>'),
(2916, 'krivqinoß', 'from (2915)', 'krithinos', 'None', 'kree\'-thee-nos', 'Adjective', 'from «2915»; consisting of barley:--barley.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of barley, made of barley</OL>'),
(2917, 'krivma', 'from (2919)', 'krima', '3:942,469', 'kree\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «2919»; a decision (the function or the effect, for or against (\"crime\")):--avenge, condemned, condemnation, damnation, + go to law, judgment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a decree, judgments<LI>judgment<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>condemnation of wrong, the decision (whether severe or mild) which one passes on the faults of others<LI>in a forensic sense<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the sentence of a judge<LI>the punishment with which one is sentenced<LI>condemnatory sentence, penal judgment, sentence</OL></OL><LI>a matter to be judicially decided, a lawsuit, a case in court</OL>'),
(2918, 'krivnon', 'perhaps a primitive word', 'krinon', 'None', 'kree\'-non', 'Noun Neuter', 'perhaps a prim word; a lily:--lily.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a flower, the lily</OL>'),
(2919, 'krivnw', 'perhaps a primitive word', 'krino', '3:921,469', 'kree\'-no', 'Verb', 'properly, to distinguish, i.e. decide (mentally or judicially); by implication, to try, condemn, punish:--avenge, conclude, condemn, damn, decree, determine, esteem, judge, go to (sue at the) law, ordain, call in question, sentence to, think.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to separate, put asunder, to pick out, select, choose<LI>to approve, esteem, to prefer<LI>to be of opinion, deem, think, to be of opinion<LI>to determine, resolve, decree<LI>to judge<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to pronounce an opinion concerning right and wrong<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be judged, i.e. summoned to trial that one\'s case may be examined and judgment passed upon it</OL><LI>to pronounce judgment, to subject to censure<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of those who act the part of judges or arbiters in matters of common life, or pass judgment on the deeds and words of others</OL></OL><LI>to rule, govern<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to preside over with the power of giving judicial decisions, because it was the prerogative of kings and rulers to pass judgment</OL><LI>to contend together, of warriors and combatants<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to dispute<LI>in a forensic sense<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to go to law, have suit at law</OL></OL></OL>'),
(2920, 'krivsiß', 'perhaps a primitive word', 'krisis', '3:941,469', 'kree\'-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'decision (subjectively or objectively, for or against); by extension, a tribunal; by implication, justice (especially, divine law):--accusation, condemnation, damnation, judgment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a separating, sundering, separation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a trial, contest</OL><LI>selection<LI>judgment<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>opinion or decision given concerning anything<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>esp. concerning justice and injustice, right or wrong</OL><LI>sentence of condemnation, damnatory judgment, condemnation and punishment</OL><LI>the college of judges (a tribunal of seven men in the several cities of Palestine; as distinguished from the Sanhedrin, which had its seat at Jerusalem)<LI>right, justice</OL>'),
(2921, 'Krivspoß', 'of Latin origin', 'Krispos', 'None', 'kris\'-pos', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; \"crisp\"; Crispus, a Corinthian:--Crispus.', 'Crispus = \"curled\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the ruler of the Jewish synagogue in Corinth, baptised by Paul</OL>'),
(2922, 'krithvrion', 'from a presumed derivative of (2923)', 'kriterion', '3:943,469', 'kree-tay\'-ree-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of «2923»; a rule of judging (\"criterion\"), i.e. (by implication) a tribunal:--to judge, judgment (seat).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the instrument or means of trying or judging anything<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the rule by which one judges</OL><LI>the place where judgment is given<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the tribunal of a judge<LI>a bench of judges</OL><LI>the matter judged, thing to be decided, suit, case</OL>'),
(2923, 'krithvß', 'from (2919)', 'krites', '3:942,469', 'kree-tace\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «2919»; a judge (genitive case or specially):--judge.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one who passes or arrogates to himself, judgment on anything<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an arbiter<LI>of a Roman procurator administering justice<LI>of God passing judgment on men<LI>of the leaders or rulers of the Israelites</OL></OL>'),
(2924, 'kritikovß', 'from (2923)', 'kritikos', '3:943,469', 'krit-ee-kos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2923»; decisive (\"critical\"), i.e. discriminative:--discerner.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>relating to judging, fit for judging, skilled in judging</OL>'),
(2925, 'krouvw', 'apparently a primary verb', 'krouo', '3:954,475', 'kroo\'-o', 'Verb', 'apparently a primary verb; to rap:--knock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to knock: at the door</OL>'),
(2926, 'kruvpth', 'from (2927)', 'krupte', '3:957,476', 'kroop-tay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «2927»; a hidden place, i.e. cellar (\"crypt\"):--secret.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>crypt, a covered way, vault, cellar</OL>'),
(2927, 'kruptovß', 'from (2928)', 'kruptos', '3:957,476', 'kroop-tos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «2928»; concealed, i.e. private:--hid(-den), inward(-ly), secret.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hidden, concealed, secret</OL>'),
(2928, 'kruvptw', 'a primary verb', 'krupto', '3:957,476', 'kroop\'-to', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to conceal (properly, by covering):--hide (self), keep secret, secret(-ly).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hide, conceal, to be hid<LI>escape notice<LI>metaph. to conceal (that it may not become known)</OL>'),
(2929, 'krustallivzw', 'from (2930)', 'krustallizo', 'None', 'kroos-tal-lid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «2930»; to make (i.e. intransitively, resemble) ice (\"crystallize\"):--be clear as crystal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be of crystalline brightness and transparency<LI>to shine like crystal</OL>'),
(2930, 'kruvstalloß', 'from a derivative of kruos (frost)', 'krustallos', 'None', 'kroos\'-tal-los', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a derivative of kruos (frost); ice, i.e. (by analogy) rock \"crystal\":--crystal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>crystal, a kind of precious stone</OL>'),
