(3303, 'mevn', 'a primary particle', 'men', 'None', 'men', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>truly, certainly, surely, indeed</OL>', 'a primary particle; properly, indicative of affirmation or concession (in fact); usually followed by a contrasted clause with «1161» (this one, the former, etc.):--even, indeed, so, some, truly, verily. Often compounded with other particles in an intensive or asseverative sense.', ''),
(3304, 'menou\'n', 'from (3203) and (3767) and (1065)', 'menounge', 'None', 'men-oon\'-geh', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nay surely, nay rather</OL>', 'from «3203» and «3767» and «1065»; so then at least:--nay but, yea doubtless (rather, verily).', ''),
(3305, 'mevntoi', 'from (3203) and (5104)', 'mentoi', 'None', 'men\'-toy', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>but yet, nevertheless, howbeit</OL>', 'from «3203» and «5104»; indeed though, i.e. however:--also, but, howbeit, nevertheless, yet.', ''),
(3306, 'mevnw', 'a root word', 'meno', '4:574,581', 'men\'-o', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to stay (in a given place, state, relation or expectancy):--abide, continue, dwell, endure, be present, remain, stand, tarry (for), × thine own.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to remain, abide<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in reference to place<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to sojourn, tarry<LI>not to depart 1a</OL><LI>to continue to be present 1a<LI>to be held, kept, continually<LI>in reference to time<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to continue to be, not to perish, to last, endure 1b</OL><LI>of persons, to survive, live<LI>in reference to state or condition<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to remain as one, not to become another or different</OL></OL><LI>to wait for, await one</OL>'),
(3307, 'merivzw', 'from (3313)', 'merizo', 'None', 'mer-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «3313»; to part, i.e. (literally) to apportion, bestow, share, or (figuratively) to disunite, differ:--deal, be difference between, distribute, divide, give participle', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to separate into parts, cut into pieces<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to divide into parties, i.e. be split into factions</OL><LI>to distribute<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a thing among people<LI>bestow, impart</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3308, 'mevrimna', 'from (3307) (through the idea of distraction)', 'merimna', '4:589,584', 'mer\'-im-nah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3307» (through the idea of distraction); solicitude:--care.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>care, anxiety</OL>'),
(3309, 'merimnavw', 'from (3308)', 'merimnao', '4:589,584', 'mer-im-nah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «3308»; to be anxious about:--(be, have) care(-ful), take thought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be anxious<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be troubled with cares</OL><LI>to care for, look out for (a thing)<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to seek to promote one\'s interests<LI>caring or providing for</OL></OL>'),
(3310, 'merivß', 'from (3313)', 'meris', 'None', 'mer-ece\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of «3313»; a portion, i.e. province, share or (abstractly) participation:--part (X -akers).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a part as distinct from the whole<LI>an assigned part, a portion, share</OL>'),
(3311, 'merismovß', 'from (3307)', 'merismos', 'None', 'mer-is-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3307»; a separation or distribution:--dividing asunder, gift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a division, partition<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>distribution (of various kinds)</OL><LI>a separation<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>so far as to cleave asunder or separate</OL></OL>'),
(3312, 'meristhvß', 'from (3307)', 'meristes', 'None', 'mer-is-tace\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3307»; an apportioner (administrator):--divider.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a divider<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of an inheritance</OL></OL>'),
(3313, 'mevroß', 'from an obsolete but more primary form of meiromai (to get as a section or allotment)', 'meros', '4:594,585', 'mer\'-os', 'Noun Neuter', 'from an obsolete but more primary form of meiromai (to get as a section or allotment); a division or share (literally or figuratively, in a wide application):--behalf, course, coast, craft, particular (+ -ly), part (+ -ly), piece, portion, respect, side, some sort(-what).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a part<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a part due or assigned to one<LI>lot, destiny</OL><LI>one of the constituent parts of a whole<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in part, partly, in a measure, to some degree, as respects a part, severally, individually<LI>any particular, in regard to this, in this respect</OL></OL>'),
(3314, 'meshmbriva', 'from (3319) and (2250)', 'mesembria', 'None', 'mes-ame-bree\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3319» and «2250»; midday; by implication, the south:--noon, south.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as respects to time: noon<LI>as respects to locality<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the south</OL></OL>'),
(3315, 'mesiteuvw', 'from (3316)', 'mesiteuo', '4:598,585', 'mes-it-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «3316»; to interpose (as arbiter), i.e (by implication) to ratify (as surety):--confirm.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to act as a mediator between litigating or covenanting parties<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to accomplish something by interposing between two parties<LI>to mediate</OL><LI>act as a sponsor or surety<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to pledge one\'s self, give surety</OL></OL>'),
(3316, 'mesivthß', 'from (3319)', 'mesites', '4:598,585', 'mes-ee\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3319»; a go-between, i.e. (simply) an internunciator, or (by implication) a reconciler (intercessor):--mediator.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one who intervenes between two, either in order to make or restore peace and friendship, or form a compact, or for ratifying a covenant<LI>a medium of communication, arbitrator</OL>'),
(3317, 'mesonuvktion', 'neuter of compound of (3319) and (3571)', 'mesonuktion', 'None', 'mes-on-ook\'-tee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of compound of «3319» and «3571»; midnight (especially as a watch):--midnight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>midnight</OL>'),
(3318, 'Mesopotamiva', 'from (3319) and (4215)', 'Mesopotamia', 'None', 'mes-op-ot-am-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Location', 'from «3319» and «4215»; Mesopotamia (as lying between the Euphrates and the Tigris; compare 0763), a region of Asia:--Mesopotamia.', 'Mesopotamia = \"between two rivers\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the entire country between the two rivers, the Tigris and the Euphrates</OL>'),
(3319, 'mevsoß', 'from (3326)', 'mesos', 'None', 'mes\'-os', 'Adjective', 'from «3326»; middle (as an adjective or (neuter) noun):--among, × before them, between, + forth, mid(-day, -night), midst, way.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>middle<LI>the midst<LI>in the midst of, amongst</OL>'),
(3320, 'mesovtoicon', 'from (3319) and (5109)', 'mesotoichon', '4:625,589', 'mes-ot\'-oy-khon', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3319» and «5109»; a partition (figuratively):--middle wall.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a partition wall</OL>'),
(3321, 'mesouravnhma', 'from a presumed compound of (3319) and (3772)', 'mesouranema', 'None', 'mes-oo-ran\'-ay-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a presumed compound of «3319» and «3772»; mid-sky:--midst of heaven.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mid-heaven<LI>the highest point in the heavens, which the sun occupies at noon, where what is done can be seen and heard by all</OL>'),
