(3525, 'nhvfw', 'of uncertain affinity', 'nepho', '4:936,633', 'nay\'-fo', 'Verb', 'of uncertain affinity: to abstain from wine (keep sober), i.e. (figuratively) be discreet:--be sober, watch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be sober, to be calm and collected in spirit<LI>to be temperate, dispassionate, circumspect</OL>'),
(3526, 'Nivger', 'of Latin origin', 'Niger', 'None', 'neeg\'-er', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; black; Niger, a Christian:--Niger.', 'Niger = \"black\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>surname of the prophet Simeon</OL>'),
(3527, 'Nikavnwr', 'probably from (3528)', 'Nikanor', 'None', 'nik-an\'-ore', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from «3528»; victorious; Nicanor, a Christian:--Nicanor.', 'Nicanor = \"conqueror\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the seven deacons in the church at Jerusalem</OL>'),
(3528, 'nikavw', 'from (3529)', 'nikao', '4:942,634', 'nik-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «3529»; to subdue (literally or figuratively):--conquer, overcome, prevail, get the victory.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to conquer<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to carry off the victory, come off victorious<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of Christ, victorious over all His foes<LI>of Christians, that hold fast their faith even unto death against the power of their foes, and temptations and persecutions<LI>when one is arraigned or goes to law, to win the case, maintain one\'s cause</OL></OL></OL>'),
(3529, 'nivkh', 'apparently a primary word', 'nike', '4:942,634', 'nee\'-kay', 'Noun Feminine', 'apparently a primary word; conquest (abstractly), i.e. (figuratively) the means of success:--victory.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>victory</OL>'),
(3530, 'Nikovdhmoß', 'from (3534) and (1218)', 'Nikodemos', 'None', 'nik-od\'-ay-mos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3534» and «1218»; victorious among his people; Nicodemus, an Israelite:--Nicodemus.', 'Nicodemus = \"conqueror\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a member of the Sanhedrin who took the part of Jesus</OL>'),
(3531, 'Nikolai?thß', 'from (3532)', 'Nikolaites', 'None', 'nik-ol-ah-ee\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3532»; a Nicolaite, i.e. adherent of Nicolaus:--Nicolaitane.', 'Nicolaitans = \"destruction of people\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a sect mentioned in Rev. 2:6,15, who were charged with holding the error of Balaam, casting a stumbling block before the church of God by upholding the liberty of eating things sacrificed to idols as well as committing fornication</OL>'),
(3532, 'Nikovlaoß', 'from (3534) and (2994)', 'Nikolaos', 'None', 'nik-ol\'-ah-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3534» and «2994»; victorious over the people; Nicolaus, a heretic:--Nicolaus.', 'Nicolas = \"victor of the people\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>was a proselyte of Antioch and one of the seven deacons of the church at Jerusalem</OL>'),
(3533, 'Nikovpoliß', 'from (3534) and (4172)', 'Nikopolis', 'None', 'nik-op\'-ol-is', 'Noun Location', 'from «3534» and «4172»; victorious city; Nicopolis, a place in Macedonia:--Nicopolis.', 'Nicopolis meaning \"city of victory\"'),
(3534, 'ni\'koß', 'from (3529)', 'nikos', '4:942,634', 'nee\'-kos', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3529»; a conquest (concretely), i.e. (by implication) triumph:--victory.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>victory<LI>to utterly vanquish</OL>'),
(3535, 'Nineui?', 'of Hebrew origin (05210)', 'Nineui', 'None', 'nin-yoo-ee\'', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin («05210»); Ninevi (i.e. Nineveh), the capital of Assyria:--Nineve.', 'Nineveh = \"offspring of ease: offspring abiding\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the capital of the ancient kingdom of Assyria</OL>'),
(3536, 'Nineuivthß', 'from (3535)', 'Nineuites', 'None', 'nin-yoo-ee\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3535»; a Ninevite, i.e. inhabitant of Nineveh:--of Nineve, Ninevite.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Ninevite, an inhabitant of Nineveh</OL>'),
(3537, 'nipthvr', 'from (3538)', 'nipter', 'None', 'nip-tare\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3538»; a ewer:--bason.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a vessel for washing the hands and the feet, a basin</OL>'),
(3538, 'nivptw', 'to cleanse (especially the hands or the feet or the face)', 'nipto', '4:946,635', 'nip\'-to', 'Verb', 'to cleanse (especially the hands or the feet or the face); ceremonially, to perform ablution:--wash. Compare «3068».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wash<LI>to wash one\'s self</OL>'),
(3539, 'noevw', 'from (3563)', 'noieo', '4:948,636', 'noy-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «3563»; to exercise the mind (observe), i.e. (figuratively) to comprehend, heed:--consider, perceive, think, understand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to perceive with the mind, to understand, to have understanding<LI>to think upon, heed, ponder, consider</OL>'),
(3540, 'novhma', 'from (3539)', 'noema', '4:960,636', 'no\'-ay-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3539»; a perception, i.e. purpose, or (by implication) the intellect, disposition, itself:--device, mind, thought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a mental perception, thought<LI>an evil purpose<LI>that which thinks, the mind, thoughts or purposes</OL>'),
(3541, 'novqoß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'nothos', 'None', 'noth\'-os', 'Adjective', 'of uncertain affinity; a spurious or illegitimate son:--bastard.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>illegitimate, bastard<LI>one born, not in lawful wedlock, but of a concubine or female slave</OL>'),
(3542, 'nomhv', 'from the same as (3551)', 'nome', 'None', 'nom-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine from the same as «3551»; pasture, i.e. (the act) feeding (figuratively, spreading of a gangrene), or (the food) pasturage:--X eat, pasture.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pasturage, fodder, food<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>fig. he shall not want the needful supplies for the true life</OL><LI>growth, increase<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of evils spreading like a gangrene<LI>of ulcers<LI>of a conflagration</OL></OL>'),
(3543, 'nomivzw', 'from (3551)', 'nomizo', 'None', 'nom-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «3551»; properly, to do by law (usage), i.e. to accustom (passively, be usual); by extension, to deem or regard:-- suppose, thing, be wont.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hold by custom or usage, own as a custom or usage, to follow a custom or usage<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>it is the custom, it is the received usage</OL><LI>to deem, think, suppose</OL>'),
(3544, 'nomikovß', 'from (3551)', 'nomikos', '4:1088,646', 'nom-ik-os\'', 'Adjective', 'from «3551»; according (or pertaining) to law, i.e. legal (ceremonially); as noun, an expert in the (Mosaic) law:--about the law, lawyer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pertaining to the law, one learned in the law<LI>in the NT an interpreter and teacher of the Mosaic law</OL>'),
(3545, 'nomivmwß', 'adverb from a derivative of (3551)', 'nomimos', '4:1088,646', 'nom-im\'-oce', 'Noun Masculine', 'adverb from a derivative of «3551»; legitimately (specially, agreeably to the rules of the lists):--lawfully.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lawfully, agreeable to the law, properly</OL>'),
(3546, 'novmisma', 'from (3543)', 'nomisma', 'None', 'nom\'-is-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3543»; what is reckoned as of value (after the Latin numisma), i.e. current coin:--money.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anything received and sanctioned by usage or law<LI>money, (current) coin, legal tender</OL>'),
(3547, 'nomodidavskaloß', 'from (3551) and (1320)', 'nomodidaskalos', '2:159,161', 'nom-od-id-as\'-kal-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3551» and «1320»; an expounder of the (Jewish) law, i.e. a Rabbi:--doctor (teacher) of the law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a teacher and interpreter of the law: among the Jews<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of those who among Christians went about as champions and interpreters of the Mosaic law</OL></OL>'),
(3548, 'nomoqesiva', 'from (3550)', 'nomothesia', '4:1089,646', 'nom-oth-es-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3550»; legislation (specially, the institution of the Mosaic code):--giving of the law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>law giving, legislation</OL>'),
(3549, 'nomoqetevw', 'from (3550)', 'nomotheteo', '4:1090,646', 'nom-oth-et-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «3550»; to legislate, i.e. (passively) to have (the Mosaic) enactments injoined, be sanctioned (by them):--establish, receive the law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to enact laws<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>laws are enacted or prescribed for one, to be legislated for, furnished with laws</OL><LI>to sanction by law, enact</OL>'),
(3550, 'nomoqevthß', 'from (3551) and a derivative of (5087)', 'nomothetes', '4:1089,646', 'nom-oth-et\'-ace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3551» and a derivative of «5087»; a legislator:--lawgiver.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a lawgiver</OL>'),
(3551, 'novmoß', 'from a primary nemo (to parcel out, especially food or grazing to animals)', 'nomos', '4:1022,646', 'nom\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a primary nemo (to parcel out, especially food or grazing to animals); law (through the idea of prescriptive usage), genitive case (regulation), specially, (of Moses (including the volume); also of the Gospel), or figuratively (a principle):--law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anything established, anything received by usage, a custom, a law, a command<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of any law whatsoever<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a law or rule producing a state approved of God 1a</OL><LI>by the observance of which is approved of God<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>a precept or injunction<LI>the rule of action prescribed by reason</OL><LI>of the Mosaic law, and referring, acc. to the context. either to the volume of the law or to its contents<LI>the Christian religion: the law demanding faith, the moral instruction given by Christ, esp. the precept concerning love<LI>the name of the more important part (the Pentateuch), is put for the entire collection of the sacred books of the OT</OL></OL>'),
(3552, 'nosevw', 'from (3554)', 'noseo', '4:1091,655', 'nos-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «3554»; to be sick, i.e. (by implication, of a diseased appetite) to hanker after (figuratively, to harp upon):--dote.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be sick<LI>metaph. of any ailment of the mind<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be taken with such an interest in a thing as amounts to a disease, to have a morbid fondness for</OL></OL>'),
(3553, 'novshma', 'from (3552)', 'nosema', '4:1091,655', 'nos\'-ay-ma', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3552»; an ailment:--disease.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>disease, sickness</OL>'),
(3554, 'novsoß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'nosos', '4:1091,655', 'nos\'-os', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain affinity; a malady (rarely figuratively, of moral disability):--disease, infirmity, sickness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>disease, sickness</OL>'),
(3555, 'nossiav', 'from (3502)', 'nossia', 'None', 'nos-see-ah\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3502»; a brood (of chickens):--brood.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a nest of birds<LI>a brood of birds</OL>'),
(3556, 'nossivon', 'dimin. of (3502)', 'nossion', 'None', 'nos-see\'-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'diminutive of «3502»; a birdling:--chicken.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a brood of birds</OL>'),
(3557, 'nosfivzw', 'middle voice from nosphi (apart or clandestinely)', 'nosphizomai', 'None', 'nos-fid\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from nosphi (apart or clandestinely); to sequestrate for oneself, i.e. embezzle:--keep back, purloin.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to set apart, separate, divide<LI>to set apart or separate for one\'s self<LI>to purloin, embezzle, withdraw covertly and appropriate to one\'s own use</OL>'),
(3558, 'novtoß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'notos', 'None', 'not\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain affinity; the south(-west) wind; by extension, the southern quarter itself:--south (wind).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the south wind<LI>the south, the southern quarter</OL>'),
(3559, 'nouqesiva', 'from (3563) and a derivative of (5087)', 'nouthesia', '4:1019,636', 'noo-thes-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3563» and a derivative of «5087»; calling attention to, i.e. (by implication) mild rebuke or warning:--admonition.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>admonition, exhortation</OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(3560, 'nouqetevw', 'from the same as (3559)', 'noutheteo', '4:1019,636', 'noo-thet-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from the same as «3559»; to put in mind, i.e. (by implication) to caution or reprove gently:--admonish, warn.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to admonish, warn, exhort</OL>'),
(3561, 'noumhniva', 'from of a compound of (3501) and (3376) (as noun by implication of (2250))', 'noumenia', '4:638,*', 'noo-may-nee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of a compound of «3501» and «3376» (as noun by implication, of «2250»); the festival of new moon:--new moon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>new moon<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the Jewish festival of the new moon</OL></OL>'),
(3562, 'nounecw\'ß', 'from a comparative of the accusative case of (3563) and (2192)', 'nounechos', '2:816,*', 'noon-ekh-oce\'', 'Adverb', 'adverb from a comparative of the accusative case of «3563» and «2192»; in a mind-having way, i.e. prudently:--discreetly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wisely, discreetly, prudently</OL>'),
(3563, 'nou\'ß', 'probably from the base of (1097)', 'nous', '4:951,636', 'nooce', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably from the base of «1097»; the intellect, i.e. mind (divine or human; in thought, feeling, or will); by implication, meaning:--mind, understanding. Compare «5590».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the mind, comprising alike the faculties of perceiving and understanding and those of feeling, judging, determining<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the intellectual faculty, the understanding<LI>reason in the narrower sense, as the capacity for spiritual truth, the higher powers of the soul, the faculty of perceiving divine things, of recognising goodness and of hating evil<LI>the power of considering and judging soberly, calmly and impartially</OL><LI>a particular mode of thinking and judging, i.e thoughts, feelings, purposes, desires</OL>'),
(3564, 'Nuvmfa', 'probably contracted for a compound of (3565) and (1435)', 'Numphas', 'None', 'noom-fas\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably contracted for a compound of «3565» and «1435»; nymph-given (i.e. -born); Nymphas, a Christian:--Nymphas.', 'Nymphas = \"bridegroom\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a wealthy and zealous Christian in Laodicea</OL>'),
(3565, 'nuvmfh', 'from a primary but obsolete verb nupto (to veil as a bride, cf Latin \"nupto,\" to marry)', 'numphe', '4:1099,657', 'noom-fay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a primary but obsolete verb nupto (to veil as a bride; compare Latin \"nupto,\" to marry); a young married woman (as veiled), including a betrothed girl; by implication, a son\'s wife:--bride, daughter in law.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a betrothed woman, a bride<LI>a recently married woman, young wife<LI>a young woman<LI>a daughter-in-law</OL>'),
(3566, 'numfivoß', 'from (3565)', 'numphios', '4:1099,657', 'noom-fee\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3565»; a bride-groom (literally or figuratively):--bridegroom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a bridegroom</OL>'),
(3567, 'numfwvn', 'from (3565)', 'numphon', 'None', 'noom-fohn\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3565»; the bridal room:--bridechamber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the chamber containing the bridal bed, the bridal chamber<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the friends of the bridegroom whose duty it was to provide and care for whatever pertained to the bridal chamber, i.e. whatever was needed for the due celebration of the nuptials<LI>the room in which the marriage ceremonies are held</OL></OL>'),
(3568, 'nu\'n', 'a primary particle of present time', 'nun', '4:1106,658', 'noon', 'Adverb', 'a primary particle of present time; \"now\" (as adverb of date, a transition or emphasis); also as noun or adjective present or immediate:--henceforth, + hereafter, of late, soon, present, this (time). See also «3569», «3570».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>at this time, the present, now</OL>'),
(3569, 'tanu\'n', 'from neuter plural of (3588) and (3568)', 'tanun', 'None', 'tan-oon\'', 'Adverb', 'from neuter plural of «3588» and «3568»; the things now, i.e. (adverbially) at present:--(but) now.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>now, the present</OL>'),
(3570, 'nuniv', 'a prolonged form of (3568) for emphasis', 'nuni', 'None', 'noo-nee\'', 'Adverb', 'a prolonged form of «3568» for emphasis; just now:--now.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>now, at this very moment</OL>'),
(3571, 'nuvx', 'a primary word', 'nux', '4:1123,661', 'noox', 'Noun Feminine', 'a primary word; \"night\" (literally or figuratively):-- (mid-)night.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>night<LI>metaph. the time when work ceases<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the time of death<LI>the time for deeds of sin and shame<LI>the time of moral stupidity and darkness<LI>the time when the weary and also the drunken give themselves up to slumber</OL></OL>'),
(3572, 'nuvssw', 'apparently a primary word', 'nusso', 'None', 'noos\'-so', 'Verb', 'apparently a primary word; to prick (\"nudge\"):--pierce.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>pierce<LI>to pierce through, transfix<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>often of severe or even deadly wounds given one</OL></OL>'),
(3573, 'nustavzw', 'from a presumed derivative of (3506)', 'nustazo', 'None', 'noos-tad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from a presumed derivative of «3506»; to nod, i.e. (by implication) to fall asleep; figuratively, to delay:--slumber.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to nod in sleep, to sleep<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be overcome or oppressed with sleep<LI>to fall asleep, drop off to sleep</OL><LI>to be negligent, careless<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a thing i.e. to linger, delay</OL></OL>'),
(3574, 'nucqhvmeron', 'from (3571) and (2250)', 'nuchthemeron', 'None', 'nookh-thay\'-mer-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3571» and «2250»; a day-and-night, i.e. full day of twenty-four hours:--night and day.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a night and a day, the space of twenty four hours</OL>'),
(3575, 'Nw\'e', 'of Hebrew origin (05146)', 'Noe', 'None', 'no\'-eh', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Hebrew origin («05146»); Noe, (i.e. Noach), a patriarch:--Noe.', 'Noah = \"rest\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the tenth in descent from Adam, second father of the human family</OL>'),
(3576, 'nwqrovß', 'from a derivative of (3541)', 'nothros', '4:1126,661', 'no-thros\'', 'Adjective', 'from a derivative of «3541»; sluggish, i.e. (literally) lazy, or (figuratively) stupid:--dull, slothful.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>slow, sluggish, indolent, dull, languid</OL>'),
(3577, 'nw\'toß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'notos', 'None', 'no\'-tos', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain affinity; the back:--back.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the back</OL>'),
(3578, 'xeniva', 'from (3581)', 'xenia', '5:1,661', 'xen-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3581»; hospitality, i.e. (by implication) a place of entertainment:--lodging.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>hospitality, hospitable reception<LI>a lodging place, lodgings</OL>'),
(3579, 'xenivzw', 'from (3581)', 'xenizo', '5:1,661', 'xen-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «3581»; to be a host (passively, a guest); by implication, be (make, appear) strange:--entertain, lodge, (think it) strange.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to receive as a guest, to entertain, hospitably<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be received hospitably<LI>to stay as a guest, to lodge<LI>be lodged</OL><LI>to surprise or astonish by the strangeness and novelty of a thing<OL TYPE=\"b\"><LI>to think strange, be shocked</OL></OL>'),
(3580, 'xenodocevw', 'from a compound of (3581) and (1209)', 'xenodocheo', '5:1,661', 'xen-od-okh-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a compound of «3581» and «1209»; to be hospitable:--lodge strangers.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to receive and entertain hospitably, to be hospitable</OL>'),
(3581, 'xevnoß', 'apparently a primary word', 'xenos', '5:1,661', 'xen\'-os', 'Adjective', 'apparently a primary word; foreign (literally, alien, or figuratively, novel); by implication, a guest or (vice-versa) entertainer:--host, strange(-r).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a foreigner, a stranger<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>alien (from a person or a thing)<LI>without the knowledge of, without a share in<LI>new, unheard of</OL><LI>one who receives and entertains another hospitably<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>with whom he stays or lodges, a host</OL></OL>'),
(3582, 'xevsthß', 'as if from xeo (properly, to smooth, by implication [of friction] to boil or heat)', 'xestes', 'None', 'xes\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'as if from xeo (properly, to smooth; by implication, (of friction) to boil or heat); a vessel (as fashioned or for cooking) (or perhaps by corruption from the Latin sextarius, the sixth of a modius, i.e. about a pint), i.e. (specially), a measure for liquids or solids, (by analogy, a pitcher):--pot.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a sextarius<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a vessel for measuring liquids, holding about a pint (.5 litre)</OL><LI>a wooden pitcher or ewer from which water or wine is poured, whether holding a sextarius or not</OL>'),
(3583, 'xhraivnw', 'from (3584)', 'xeraino', 'None', 'xay-rah\'-ee-no', 'Verb', 'from «3584»; to desiccate; by implication, to shrivel, to mature:--dry up, pine away, be ripe, wither (away).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make dry, dry up, wither<LI>to become dry, to be dry, be withered<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of plants<LI>of the ripening of crops<LI>of fluids<LI>of the members of the body</OL><LI>to waste away, pine away, i.e. a withered hand</OL>'),
(3584, 'xhrovß', 'from the base of (3582) (through the idea of scorching)', 'xeros', 'None', 'xay-ros\'', 'Adjective', 'from the base of «3582» (through the idea of scorching); arid; by implication, shrunken, earth (as opposed to water):--dry land, withered.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>dry<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of members of the body deprived of their natural juices, shrunk, wasted, withered<LI>of the land in distinction from the water</OL></OL>'),
(3585, 'xuvlinoß', 'from (3586)', 'xulinos', 'None', 'xoo\'-lin-os', 'Adjective', 'from «3586»; wooden:--of wood.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wooden, made of wood</OL>'),
(3586, 'xuvlon', 'from another form of the base of (3582)', 'xulon', '5:37,665', 'xoo\'-lon', 'Noun Neuter', 'from another form of the base of «3582»; timber (as fuel or material); by implication, a stick, club or tree or other wooden article or substance:--staff, stocks, tree, wood.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>wood<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>that which is made of wood<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>as a beam from which any one is suspended, a gibbet, a cross<LI>a log or timber with holes in which the feet, hands, neck of prisoners were inserted and fastened with thongs<LI>a fetter, or shackle for the feet<LI>a cudgel, stick, staff</OL></OL><LI>a tree</OL>'),
(3587, 'xuravw', 'from a derivative of the same as (3586) (meaning a razor)', 'xurao', 'None', 'xoo-rah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a derivative of the same as «3586» (meaning a razor); to shave or \"shear\" the hair:--shave.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to shear, shave<LI>to get one\'s self shaved</OL>'),
(3588, 'oJ', 'in all their inflections, the definite article', 'ho', 'None', 'ho,', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>this, that, these, etc.</OL>', 'in all their inflections; the definite article; the (sometimes to be supplied, at others omitted, in English idiom):--the, this, that, one, he, she, it, etc.', ''),
(3589, 'ojgdohvkonta', 'from (3590)', 'ogdoekonta', 'None', 'og-do-ay\'-kon-tah', 'Noun', 'from «3590»; ten times eight:--fourscore.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>eighty</OL>'),
(3590, 'o[gdooß', 'from (3638)', 'ogdoos', 'None', 'og\'-do-os', 'Adjective', 'from «3638»; the eighth:--eighth.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the eighth</OL>'),
