(3655, 'o[mbroß', 'of uncertain affinity', 'ombros', 'None', 'om\'-bros', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain affinity; a thunder storm:--shower.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a shower<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a violent storm, accompanied by high wind with thunder and lightning</OL></OL>'),
(3656, 'oJmilevw', 'from (3658)', 'homileo', 'None', 'hom-il-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «3658»; to be in company with, i.e. (by implication) to converse:--commune, talk.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be in company with<LI>to associate with<LI>to stay with<LI>to converse with, talk about: with one</OL>'),
(3657, 'oJmiliva', 'from (3658)', 'homilia', 'None', 'hom-il-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3658»; companionship (\"homily\"), i.e. (by implication) intercourse:--communication.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>companionship, intercourse, communion</OL>'),
(3658, 'oJmivclh', 'from the base of (3674) and a derivative of the alternate of (138) (meaning a crowd)', 'homilos', 'None', 'hom\'-il-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the base of «3674» and a derivative of the alternate of «138» (meaning a crowd); association together, i.e. a multitude:--company.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a multitude of men gathered together, a crowd, a throng</OL>'),
(3659, 'o[mma', 'from (3700)', 'omma', 'None', 'om\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3700»; a sight, i.e. (by implication) the eye:--eye.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an eye</OL>'),
(3660, 'ojmnuvw', 'a prolonged form of a primary but obsolete omo, for which another prolonged form (omoo {om-o\'-o}) is used in certain tenses', 'omnuo', '5:176,683', 'om-noo\'-o,', 'Verb', 'to swear, i.e. take (or declare on) oath:--swear.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to swear<LI>to affirm, promise, threaten, with an oath<LI>in swearing to call a person or thing as witness, to invoke, swear by</OL>'),
(3661, 'oJmoqumadovn', 'from a compound of the base of (3674) and (2372)', 'homothumadon', '5:185,684', 'hom-oth-oo-mad-on\'', 'Adverb', 'adverb from a compound of the base of «3674» and «2372»; unanimously:--with one accord (mind).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>with one mind, with one accord, with one passion</OL>A unique Greek word, used 10 of its 12 New Testament occurrences inthe Book of Acts, helps us understand the uniqueness of the Christiancommunity. Homothumadon is a compound of two words meaning to \"rushalong\" and \"in unison\". The image is almost musical; a number ofnotes are sounded which, while different, harmonise in pitch andtone. As the instruments of a great concert under the direction of aconcert master, so the Holy Spirit blends together the lives ofmembers of Christ\'s church.'),
(3662, 'oJmoiavzw', 'from (3664)', 'homoiazo', 'None', 'hom-oy-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «3664»; to resemble:--agree.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be like</OL>'),
(3663, 'oJmoiopaqhvß', 'from (3664) and the alternate of (3958)', 'homoiopathes', '5:938,798', 'hom-oy-op-ath-ace\'', 'Adjective', 'from «3664» and the alternate of «3958»; similarly affected:--of (subject to) like passions.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>suffering the like with another, of like feelings or affections</OL>'),
(3664, 'o&moioß', 'from the base of (3674)', 'homoios', '5:186,684', 'hom\'-oy-os', 'Adjective', 'from the base of «3674»; similar (in appearance or character):--like, + manner.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>like, similar, resembling<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>like: i.e. resembling<LI>like: i.e. corresponding to a thing</OL></OL>'),
(3665, 'oJmoiovthß', 'from (3664)', 'homoiotes', '5:189,684', 'hom-oy-ot\'-ace', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3664»; resemblance:--like as, similitude.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>likeness</OL>'),
(3666, 'oJmoiovw', 'from (3664)', 'homoioo', '5:188,684', 'hom-oy-o\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «3664»; to assimilate, i.e. compare; passively, to become similar:--be (make) like, (in the) liken(-ess), resemble.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be made like<LI>to liken, compare<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>illustrate by comparisons</OL></OL>'),
(3667, 'oJmoivwma', 'from (3666)', 'homoioma', '5:191,684', 'hom-oy\'-o-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3666»; a form; abstractly, resemblance:--made like to, likeness, shape, similitude.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that which has been made after the likeness of something<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a figure, image, likeness, representation<LI>likeness i.e. resemblance, such as amounts almost to equality or identity</OL></OL>'),
(3668, 'oJmoivwß', 'from (3664)', 'homoios', 'None', 'hom-oy\'-oce', 'Adverb', 'adverb from «3664»; similarly:--likewise, so.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>likewise, equally, in the same way</OL>'),
(3669, 'oJmoivwsiß', 'from (3666)', 'homoiosis', '5:190,684', 'hom-oy\'-o-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3666»; assimilation, i.e. resemblance:--similitude.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a making like<LI>likeness: after the likeness of God</OL>'),
(3670, 'oJmologevw', 'from a compound of the base of (3674) and (3056)', 'homologeo', '5:199,687', 'hom-ol-og-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a compound of the base of «3674» and «3056»; to assent, i.e. covenant, acknowledge:--con- (pro-)fess, confession is made, give thanks, promise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to say the same thing as another, i.e. to agree with, assent<LI>to concede<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>not to refuse, to promise<LI>not to deny<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to confess<LI>declare<LI>to confess, i.e. to admit or declare one\'s self guilty of what one is accused of</OL></OL><LI>to profess<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to declare openly, speak out freely<LI>to profess one\'s self the worshipper of one</OL><LI>to praise, celebrate</OL>'),
(3671, 'oJmologiva', 'from the same as (3670)', 'homologia', '5:199,687', 'hom-ol-og-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «3670»; acknowledgment:--con- (pro-)fession, professed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>profession<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>subjectively: whom we profess to be ours<LI>objectively: profession [confession] i.e. what one professes [confesses]</OL></OL>'),
(3672, 'oJmologoumevnwß', 'from present passive participle of (3670)', 'homologoumenos', '5:199,687', 'hom-ol-og-ow-men\'-oce', 'Adverb', 'adverb of present passive participle of «3670»; confessedly:--without controversy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>by consent of all, confessedly, without controversy</OL>'),
(3673, 'oJmovtecnoß', 'from the base of (3674) and (5078)', 'homothechnos', 'None', 'hom-ot\'-ekh-nos', 'Adjective', 'from the base of «3674» and «5078»; a fellow-artificer:--of the same craft.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>practising the same trade or craft, of the same trade</OL>'),
(3674, 'oJmou\'', 'genitive case of homos (the same, akin to (260)) as adv', 'homou', 'None', 'hom-oo\'', 'Adverb', 'genitive case of homos (the same; akin to «260») as adverb; at the same place or time:--together.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>together: of persons assembled together</OL>'),
(3675, 'oJmovfrwn', 'from the base of (3674) and (5424)', 'homophron', 'None', 'hom-of\'-rone', 'Adjective', 'from the base of «3674» and «5424»; like-minded, i.e. harmonious:--of one mind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of one mind, concordant</OL>'),
(3676, 'o&mwß', 'from the base of (3674)', 'homos', 'None', 'hom\'-oce', 'Adverb', 'adverb from the base of «3674»; at the same time, i.e. (conjunctionally) notwithstanding, yet still:--and even, nevertheless, though but.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nevertheless, yet</OL>'),
(3677, 'o[nar', 'of uncertain derivation', 'onar', '5:220,690', 'on\'-ar', 'Noun Neuter', 'of uncertain derivation; a dream:--dream.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a dream</OL>'),
(3678, 'ojnavrion', 'from a presumed derivative of (3688)', 'onarion', '5:283,700', 'on-ar\'-ee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of «3688»; a little ass:--young ass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a little ass</OL>'),
(3679, 'ojneidivzw', 'from (3681)', 'oneidizo', '5:239,693', 'on-i-did\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «3681»; to defame, i.e. rail at, chide, taunt:--cast in teeth, (suffer) reproach, revile, upbraid.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to reproach, upbraid, revile<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of deserved reproach<LI>of undeserved reproach, to revile<LI>to upbraid, cast (favours received) in one\'s teeth</OL></OL>'),
(3680, 'ojneidismovß', 'from (3679)', 'oneidismos', '5:241,693', 'on-i-dis-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3679»; contumely:--reproach.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a reproach<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>such as Christ suffered, for the cause of God, from his enemies</OL></OL>'),
(3681, 'o[neidoß', 'probably akin to the base of (3686)', 'oneidos', '5:238,693', 'on\'-i-dos', 'Noun Neuter', 'probably akin to the base of «3686»; notoriety, i.e. a taunt (disgrace):--reproach.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>reproach<LI>shame</OL>'),
(3682, 'ÅOnhvsimoß', 'from (3685)', 'Onesimos', 'None', 'on-ay\'-sim-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «3685»; profitable; Onesimus, a Christian:--Onesimus.', 'Onesimus = \"profitable or useful\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Christian slave of Philemon</OL>'),
(3683, 'ÅOnhsivforoß', 'from a derivative of (3685) and (5411)', 'Onesiphoros', 'None', 'on-ay-sif\'-or-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a derivative of «3685» and «5411»; profit-bearer; Onesiphorus, a Christian:--Onespiphorus.', 'Onesiphorus = \"bringing profit\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the name of a certain Christian in 2 Ti. 1:16-18, 4:19</OL>'),
(3684, 'ojnikovß', 'from (3688)', 'onikos', 'None', 'on-ik-os\'', 'Adjective', 'from «3688»; belonging to a ass, i.e. large (so as to be turned by a ass):--millstone.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of or for an ass, turned by an ass<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>these beasts were often employed to turn millstones</OL></OL>'),
(3685, 'ojnivnhmi', 'a prolonged form of an apparently primary verb (onomai, to slur), for which another prolonged form (onao) is used as an alternate in some tenses [unless indeed it be identical with the base of (3686) through the idea of notoriety]', 'oninemi', 'None', 'on-in\'-ay-mee', 'Verb', 'a prolonged form of an apparently primary verb (onomai, to slur); for which another prolonged form (onao) is used as an alternate in some tenses (unless indeed it be identical with the base of «3686» through the idea of notoriety); to gratify, i.e. (middle voice) to derive pleasure or advantage from:--have joy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be useful, to profit, help<LI>to receive profit or advantage, be helped [or have joy]</OL>'),
(3686, 'o[noma', 'from a presumed derivative of the base of (1097) (cf (3685))', 'onoma', '5:242,694', 'on\'-om-ah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a presumed derivative of the base of «1097» (compare «3685»); a \"name\" (literally or figuratively) (authority, character):--called, (+ sur-)name(-d).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>name: univ. of proper names<LI>the name is used for everything which the name covers, everything the thought or feeling of which is aroused in the mind by mentioning, hearing, remembering, the name, i.e. for one\'s rank, authority, interests, pleasure, command, excellences, deeds etc.<LI>persons reckoned up by name<LI>the cause or reason named: on this account, because he suffers as a Christian, for this reason</OL>'),
(3687, 'ojnomavzw', 'from (3686)', 'onomazo', '5:282,694', 'on-om-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «3686»; to name, i.e. assign an appellation; by extension, to utter, mention, profess:--call, name.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to name<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to name, to utter, to make mention of the name<LI>to name<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>give name to, one<LI>be named 1b</OL><LI>to bear the name of a person or thing<LI>to utter the name of a person or thing</OL></OL>'),
(3688, 'o[noß', 'apparently a root word', 'onos', '5:283,700', 'on\'-os', 'Noun', 'apparently a primary word; a donkey:--an ass.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>an ass</OL>'),
(3689, 'o[ntwß', 'from the oblique cases of (5607)', 'ontos', 'None', 'on\'-toce', 'Adverb', 'adverb of the oblique cases of «5607»; really:--certainly, clean, indeed, of a truth, verily.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>truly, in reality, in point of fact, as opp. to what is pretended, fictitious, false, conjectural<LI>that which is truly etc., that which is indeed</OL>'),
(3690, 'o[xoß', 'from (3691)', 'oxos', '5:288,701', 'oz-os', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3691»; vinegar, i.e. sour wine:--vinegar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>vinegar<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the mixture of sour wine or vinegar and water which the Roman soldiers were accustomed to drink</OL></OL>'),
(3691, 'ojxuvß', 'probably akin to the base of (188) [\"acid\"]', 'oxus', 'None', 'oz-oos\'', 'Adjective', 'probably akin to the base of «188» (\"acid\"); keen; by analogy, rapid:--sharp, swift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>sharp<LI>swift, quick</OL>'),
(3692, 'ojphv', 'probably from (3700)', 'ope', 'None', 'op-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'probably from «3700»; a hole (as if for light), i.e. cavern; by analogy, a spring (of water):--cave, place.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>through which one can see, an opening, an aperture<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a window<LI>of fissures in the earth<LI>of caves in rocks or mountains, holes</OL></OL>'),
(3693, 'o[pisqen', 'from opis (regard, from (3700)) with enclitic of source', 'opisthen', '5:289,702', 'op\'-is-then', 'Adjective', 'from opis (regard; from «3700») with enclitic of source; from the rear (as a secure aspect), i.e. at the back (adverb and preposition of place or time):--after, backside, behind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>from behind, on the back, behind, after</OL>'),
(3694, 'ojpivsw', 'from the same as (3693) with enclitic of direction', 'opiso', '5:289,702', 'op-is\'-o', 'Adverb', 'from the same as «3693» with enclitic of direction; to the back, i.e. aback (as adverb or preposition of time or place; or as noun):--after, back(-ward), (+ get) behind, + follow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>back, behind, after, afterwards<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of place: things that are behind<LI>of time: after</OL></OL>'),
(3695, 'oJplivzw', 'from (3696)', 'hoplizo', '5:294,702', 'hop-lid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «3696»; to equip (with weapons (middle voice and figuratively)):--arm self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to arm, furnish with arms<LI>to provide<LI>to furnish one\'s self with a thing (as with arms)<LI>metaph. take on the same mind</OL>'),
(3696, 'o&plon', 'probably from a primary hepo (to be busy about)', 'hoplon', '5:292,702', 'hop\'-lon', 'Noun Neuter', 'probably from a primary hepo (to be busy about); an implement or utensil or tool (literally or figuratively, especially, offensive for war):--armour, instrument, weapon.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>any tool or implement for preparing a thing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>arms used in warfare, weapons</OL><LI>an instrument</OL>'),
(3697, 'oJpoi\'oß', 'from (3739) and (4169)', 'hopoios', 'None', 'hop-oy\'-os', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of what sort or quality, what manner of</OL>', 'from «3739» and «4169»; of what kind that, i.e. how (as) great (excellent) (specially, as an indefinite correlative to the definite antecedent «5108» of quality):--what manner (sort) of, such as whatsoever.', ''),
(3698, 'oJpovte', 'from (3739) and (4218)', 'hopote', 'None', 'hop-ot\'-eh', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>when</OL>', 'from «3739» and «4218»; what(-ever) then, i.e. (of time) as soon as:--when.', ''),
(3699, 'o&pou', 'from (3739) and (4225)', 'hopou', 'None', 'hop\'-oo', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>where, whereas</OL>', 'from «3739» and «4225»; what(-ever) where, i.e. at whichever spot:--in what place, where(-as, -soever), whither (+ soever).', ''),
(3700, 'ojptavnomai', 'a (middle voice) prolonged form of the primary (middle voice) optomai {op\'-tom-ahee}, which is used for it in certain tenses, and both as alternate of (3708)', 'optanomai', '5:315,706', 'op-tan\'-om-ahee,', 'Verb', 'to gaze (i.e. with wide-open eyes, as at something remarkable; and thus differing from «991», which denotes simply voluntary observation; and from «1492», which expresses merely mechanical, passive or casual vision; while «2300», and still more emphatically its intensive «2334», signifies an earnest but more continued inspection; and «4648» a watching from a distance):--appear, look, see, shew self.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to look at, behold<LI>to allow one\'s self to be seen, to appear</OL>'),
(3701, 'ojptasiva', 'from a presumed derivative of (3700)', 'optasia', '5:372,706', 'op-tas-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a presumed derivative of «3700»; visuality, i.e. (concretely) an apparition:--vision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the act of exhibiting one\'s self to view<LI>a sight, a vision, an appearance presented to one whether asleep or awake</OL>'),
(3702, 'ojptovß', 'from an obsolete verb akin to hepso (to \"steep\")', 'optos', 'None', 'op-tos\'', 'Adjective', 'from an obsolete verb akin to hepso (to \"steep\"); cooked, i.e. roasted:--broiled.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cooked, broiled</OL>'),
(3703, 'ojpwvra', 'apparently from the base of (3796) and (5610)', 'opora', 'None', 'op-o\'-rah', 'Noun Feminine', 'apparently from the base of «3796» and «5610»; properly, even-tide of the (summer) season (dog-days), i.e. (by implication) ripe fruit:--fruit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the season which succeeds summer, from the rising of Sirius to that of Arcturus, i.e. from late summer, early autumn, our dog days<LI>ripe fruits (of trees)</OL>'),
(3704, 'o&pwß', 'from (3739) and (4459)', 'hopos', 'None', 'hop\'-oce', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>how, that</OL>', 'from «3739» and «4459»; what(-ever) how, i.e. in the manner that (as adverb or conjunction of coincidence, intentional or actual):--because, how, (so) that, to, when.', '');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(3705, 'o&rama', 'from (3708)', 'horama', '5:371,706', 'hor\'-am-ah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «3708»; something gazed at, i.e. a spectacle (especially supernatural):--sight, vision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that which is seen, spectacle<LI>a sight divinely granted in an ecstasy or in a sleep, a vision</OL>'),
(3706, 'o&rasiß', 'from (3708)', 'horasis', '5:370,706', 'hor\'-as-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3708»; the act of gazing, i.e. (externally) an aspect or (internally) an inspired appearance:--sight, vision.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the act of seeing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the sense of sight, the eyes</OL><LI>appearance, visible form<LI>a vision<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an appearance divinely granted in an ecstasy or dream</OL></OL>'),
(3707, 'oJratovß', 'from (3708)', 'horatos', '5:368,706', 'hor-at-os\'', 'Adjective', 'from «3708»; gazed at, i.e. (by implication) capable of being seen:--visible.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>visible, open to view</OL>'),
(3708, 'oJravw', 'properly, to stare at [cf (3700)]', 'horao', '5:315,706', 'hor-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'properly, to stare at (compare «3700»), i.e. (by implication) to discern clearly (physically or mentally); by extension, to attend to; by Hebraism, to experience; passively, to appear:--behold, perceive, see, take heed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to see with the eyes<LI>to see with the mind, to perceive, know<LI>to see, i.e. become acquainted with by experience, to experience<LI>to see, to look to<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to take heed, beware<LI>to care for, pay heed to</OL><LI>I was seen, showed myself, appeared</OL>'),
(3709, 'ojrghv', 'from (3713)', 'orge', '5:382,716', 'or-gay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3713»; properly, desire (as a reaching forth or excitement of the mind), i.e. (by analogy), violent passion (ire, or (justifiable) abhorrence); by implication punishment:--anger, indignation, vengeance, wrath.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anger, the natural disposition, temper, character<LI>movement or agitation of the soul, impulse, desire, any violent emotion, but esp. anger<LI>anger, wrath, indignation<LI>anger exhibited in punishment, hence used for punishment itself<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of punishments inflicted by magistrates</OL></OL>'),
(3710, 'ojrgivzw', 'from (3709)', 'orgizo', '5:382,*', 'or-gid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «3709»; to provoke or enrage, i.e. (passively) become exasperated:--be angry (wroth).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to provoke, to arouse to anger<LI>to be provoked to anger, be angry, be wroth</OL>'),
(3711, 'ojrgivloß', 'from (3709)', 'orgilos', '5:382,716', 'org-ee\'-los', 'Adjective', 'from «3709»; irascible:--soon angry.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>prone to anger, irascible</OL>'),
(3712, 'ojrguiav', 'from (3713)', 'orguia', 'None', 'org-wee-ah\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3713»; a stretch of the arms, i.e. a fathom:--fathom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fathom, the distance across the breast from the tip of one middle finger to the tip of the other when the arms are outstretched, 5 to 6 feet (2 m)</OL>'),
(3713, 'ojrevgw', 'middle voice of apparently a prolonged form of an obsolete primary [cf (3735)]', 'oregomai', '5:447,727', 'or-eg\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice of apparently a prolonged form of an obsolete primary (compare «3735»); to stretch oneself, i.e. reach out after (long for):--covet after, desire.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to stretch one\'s self out in order to touch or to grasp something, to reach after or desire something<LI>to give one\'s self up to the love of money</OL>'),
(3714, 'ojreinovß', 'from (3735)', 'oreinos', 'None', 'or-i-nos', 'Adjective', 'from «3735»; mountainous, i.e. (feminine by implication, of «5561») the Highlands (of Judaea):--hill country.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>mountainous, hilly<LI>the mountain district, hill country</OL>'),
(3715, 'o[rexiß', 'from (3713)', 'orexis', '5:447,727', 'or\'-ex-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «3713»; excitement of the mind, i.e. longing after:--lust.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>desire, longing, craving for<LI>eager desire, lust, appetite<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>used both in a good and a bad sense, as well of natural and lawful and even of proper cravings (of appetite for food), also of corrupt and unlawful desires</OL></OL>'),
(3716, 'ojrqopodevw', 'from a compound of (3717) and (4228)', 'orthopodeo', '5:451,727', 'or-thop-od-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a compound of «3717» and «4228»; to be straight-footed, i.e. (figuratively) to go directly forward:--walk uprightly.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to walk in a straight course<LI>metaph. to act uprightly</OL>'),
(3717, 'ojrqovß', 'probably from the base of (3735)', 'orthos', '5:449,727', 'or-thos\'', 'Adjective', 'probably from the base of «3735»; right (as rising), i.e. (perpendicularly) erect (figuratively, honest), or (horizontally) level or direct:--straight, upright.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>straight, erect<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>upright<LI>straight, not crooked</OL></OL>'),
(3718, 'ojrqotomevw', 'from a compound of (3717) and the base of (5114)', 'orthotomeo', '8:111,1169', 'or-thot-om-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a compound of «3717» and the base of «5114», to make a straight cut, i.e. (figuratively) to dissect (expound) correctly (the divine message):--rightly divide.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut straight, to cut straight ways<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to proceed on straight paths, hold a straight course, equiv. to doing right</OL><LI>to make straight and smooth, to handle aright, to teach the truth directly and correctly</OL>'),
(3719, 'ojrqrivzw', 'from (3722)', 'orthrizo', 'None', 'or-thrid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «3722»; to use the dawn, i.e. (by implication) to repair betimes:--come early in the morning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rise early in the morning</OL>'),
(3720, 'ojrqrinovß', 'from (3722)', 'orthrinos', 'None', 'or-thrin-os\'', 'Adjective', 'from «3722»; relating to the dawn, i.e. matutinal (as an epithet of Venus, especially brilliant in the early day):--morning.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>early</OL>'),
