(4419, 'pteruvgion', 'from a presumed derivative of (4420)', 'pterugion', 'None', 'pter-oog\'-ee-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a presumed derivative of «4420»; a winglet, i.e. (figuratively) extremity (top corner):--pinnacle.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a wing, a little wing<LI>any pointed extremity<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of fins of fishes<LI>of part of a dress hanging down in the form of a wing<LI>of the top of the temple at Jerusalem</OL></OL>'),
