(4430, 'ptw\'ma', 'from the alternate of (4098)', 'ptoma', '6:166,846', 'pto\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from the alternate of «4098»; a ruin, i.e. (specially), lifeless body (corpse, carrion):--dead body, carcase, corpse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a fall, downfall<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>metaph. a failure, defeat, calamity<LI>an error, lapse into sin</OL><LI>that which has fallen<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the fallen body of one dead or slain, a corpse, a carcase</OL></OL>'),
