(4448, 'purovw', 'from (4442)', 'puroo', '6:948,975', 'poo-ro\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4442»; to kindle, i.e. (passively) to be ignited, glow (literally), be refined (by implication), or (figuratively) to be inflamed (with anger, grief, lust):--burn, fiery, be on fire, try.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to burn with fire, to set on fire, kindle<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be on fire, to burn<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be incensed, indignant</OL><LI>make to glow<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>full of fire, fiery, ignited 1b</OL><LI>of darts filled with inflammable substances and set on fire<OL TYPE=\"2\"><LI>melted by fire and purged of dross</OL></OL></OL>'),
