(4456, 'pwrovw', 'apparently from poros (a kind of stone)', 'poroo', '5:1025,816', 'po-ro\'-o', 'Verb', 'apparently from poros (a kind of stone); to petrify, i.e. (figuratively) to indurate (render stupid or callous):-- blind, harden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cover with a thick skin, to harden by covering with a callus<LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to make the heart dull<LI>to grow hard, callous, become dull, lose the power of understanding</OL></OL>'),
