(4898, 'sunevkdhmoß', 'from (4862) and the base of (1553)', 'sunekdemos', 'None', 'soon-ek\'-day-mos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «4862» and the base of «1553»; a co-absentee from home, i.e. fellow-traveller:--companion in travel, travel with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a fellow traveller, companion in travel</OL>'),
(4899, 'suneklektovß', 'from a compound of (4862) and (1586)', 'suneklektos', 'None', 'soon-ek-lek-tos\'', 'Adjective', 'from a compound of «4862» and «1586»; chosen in company with, i.e. co-elect (fellow Christian):--elected together with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>elected or chosen (by God to eternal life) together with</OL>'),
(4900, 'sunelauvnw', 'from (4862) and (1643)', 'sunelauno', 'None', 'soon-el-ow\'-no', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «1643»; to drive together, i.e. (figuratively) exhort (to reconciliation):--+ set at one again.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to drive together, compel<LI>to constrain by extortion, urge</OL>'),
(4901, 'sunepimarturevw', 'from (4862) and (1957)', 'sunepimartureo', '4:508,564', 'soon-ep-ee-mar-too-reh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «1957»; to testify further jointly, i.e. unite in adding evidence:--also bear witness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>at attest together with<LI>to join in bearing witness, to unite in adding testimony</OL>'),
(4902, 'sunepitivqhmi', 'middle voice from (4862) and a primary hepo (to follow)', 'sunepomai', 'None', 'soon-ep\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «4862» and a primary hepo (to follow); to attend (travel) in company with:--accompany.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to follow with, to accompany</OL>'),
(4903, 'sunergevw', 'from (4904)', 'sunergeo', '7:871,1116', 'soon-erg-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4904»; to be a fellow-worker, i.e. co-operate:--help (work) with, work(-er) together.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to work together, help in work, be partner in labour<LI>to put forth power together with and thereby to assist</OL>'),
(4904, 'sunergovß', 'from a presumed compound of (4862) and the base of (2041)', 'sunergos', '7:871,1116', 'soon-er-gos\'', 'Adjective', 'from a presumed compound of «4862» and the base of «2041»; a co-laborer, i.e. coadjutor:--companion in labour, (fellow-)helper(-labourer, -worker), labourer together with, workfellow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a companion in work, fellow worker</OL>'),
(4905, 'sunevrcomai', 'from (4862) and (2064)', 'sunerchomai', '2:684,257', 'soon-er\'-khom-ahee', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «2064»; to convene, depart in company with, associate with, or (specially), cohabit (conjugally):--accompany, assemble (with), come (together), come (company, go) with, resort.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to come together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to assemble<LI>of conjugal cohabitation</OL><LI>to go (depart) or come with one, to accompany one</OL>'),
(4906, 'sunesqivw', 'from (4862) and (2068) (including its alternate)', 'sunesthio', 'None', 'soon-es-thee\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «2068» (including its alternate); to take food in company with:--eat with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to eat with, take food together with</OL>'),
(4907, 'suvnesiß', 'from (4920)', 'sunesis', '7:888,1119', 'soon\'-es-is', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «4920»; a mental putting together, i.e. intelligence or (concretely) the intellect:--knowledge, understanding.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a running together, a flowing together with<LI>knowledge<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>understanding<LI>the understanding, i.e the mind so far forth as it understands</OL></OL>'),
(4908, 'sunetovß', 'from (4920)', 'sunetos', '7:888,1119', 'soon-et\'-os', 'Adjective', 'from «4920»; mentally put (or putting) together, i.e. sagacious:--prudent. Compare «5429».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>intelligent, having understanding, wise, learned</OL>'),
(4909, 'suneudokevw', 'from (4862) and (2106)', 'suneudokeo', 'None', 'soon-yoo-dok-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «2106»; to think well of in common, i.e. assent to, feel gratified with:--allow, assent, be pleased, have pleasure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be pleased together with, to approve together (with others)<LI>to be pleased at the same time with, consent, agree to<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to applaud</OL></OL>'),
(4910, 'suneuwcevomai', 'from (4862) and a derivative of a presumed compound of (2095) and a derivative of (2192) (meaning to be in good condition, i.e. [by implication] to fare well, or feast)', 'suneuocheo', 'None', 'soon-yoo-o-kheh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and a derivative of a presumed compound of «2095» and a derivative of «2192» (meaning to be in good condition, i.e. (by implication) to fare well, or feast); to entertain sumptuously in company with, i.e. (middle voice or passive) to revel together:--feast with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to entertain together<LI>to feast sumptuously with</OL>'),
(4911, 'sunefivsthmi', 'from (4862) and (2186)', 'sunephistemi', 'None', 'soon-ef-is\'-tay-mee', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «2186»; to stand up together, i.e. to resist (or assault) jointly:--rise up together.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to place over or appoint together<LI>to rise up together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>against one</OL></OL>'),
(4912, 'sunevcw', 'from (4862) and (2192)', 'sunecho', '7:877,1117', 'soon-ekh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «2192»; to hold together, i.e. to compress (the ears, with a crowd or siege) or arrest (a prisoner); figuratively, to compel, perplex, afflict, preoccupy:--constrain, hold, keep in, press, lie sick of, stop, be in a strait, straiten, be taken with, throng.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to hold together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>any whole, lest it fall to pieces or something fall away from it</OL><LI>to hold together with constraint, to compress<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to press together with the hand<LI>to hold one\'s ears, to shut the heavens that it may not rain<LI>to press on every side<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of a besieged city<LI>of a strait, that forces a ship into a narrow channel<LI>of a cattle squeeze, that pushing in on each side, forcing the beast into a position where it cannot move so the farmer can administer medication</OL></OL><LI>to hold completely<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to hold fast<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of a prisoner</OL><LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be held by, closely occupied with any business<LI>in teaching the word<LI>to constrain, oppress, of ills laying hold of one and distressing him<LI>to be held with, afflicted with, suffering from<LI>to urge, impel 3b</OL></OL><LI>of the soul</OL>'),
(4913, 'sunhvdomai', 'middle voice from (4862) and the base of (2237)', 'sunedomai', 'None', 'soon-ay\'-dom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «4862» and the base of «2237»; to rejoice in with oneself, i.e. feel satisfaction concerning:--delight.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to rejoice together with (another or others)<LI>in the NT once to rejoice or delight with one\'s self or inwardly</OL>'),
(4914, 'sunhvqeia', 'from a compound of (4862) and (2239)', 'sunetheia', 'None', 'soon-ay\'-thi-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a compound of «4862» and «2239»; mutual habituation, i.e. usage:--custom.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>intercourse (with one), intimacy<LI>custom<LI>a being used to, accustomed</OL>'),
(4915, 'sunhlikiwvthß', 'from (4862) and a derivative of (2244)', 'sunelikiotes', 'None', 'soon-ay-lik-ee-o\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «4862» and a derivative of «2244»; a co-aged person, i.e. alike in years:--equal.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>one of the same age, an equal in age</OL>'),
(4916, 'sunqavptw', 'from (4862) and (2290)', 'sunthapto', '7:786,1102', 'soon-thap\'-to', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «2290»; to inter in company with, i.e. (figuratively) to assimilate spiritually (to Christ by a sepulture as to sin):--bury with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to bury together with</OL>'),
(4917, 'sunqlavw', 'from (4862) and thlao (to crush)', 'sunthlao', 'None', 'soon-thlah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and thlao (to crush); to dash together, i.e. shatter:--break.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to break to pieces, shatter</OL>'),
(4918, 'sunqlivbw', 'from (4862) and (2346)', 'sunthlibo', 'None', 'soon-thlee\'-bo', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «2346»; to compress, i.e. crowd on all sides:--throng.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to press together, press on all sides</OL>'),
(4919, 'sunqruvptw', 'from (4862) and thrupto (to crumble)', 'sunthrupto', 'None', 'soon-throop\'-to', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and thrupto (to crumble); to crush together, i.e. (figuratively) to dispirit:--break.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>break in pieces, to crush<LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to break one\'s heart<LI>to deprive of strength and courage, dispirit, incapacitate for enduring trials</OL></OL>'),
(4920, 'sunivhmi', 'from (4862) and hiemi (to send)', 'suniemi', '7:888,1119', 'soon-ee\'-ay-mee', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and hiemi (to send); to put together, i.e. (mentally) to comprehend; by implication, to act piously:-- consider, understand, be wise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to set or bring together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in a hostile sense, of combatants</OL><LI>to put (as it were) the perception with the thing perceived<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to set or join together in the mind<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>i.e. to understand: the man of understanding<LI>idiom for: a good and upright man (having the knowledge of those things which pertain to salvation)</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4921, 'sunivsthmi', 'from (4862) and (2476) (including its collat. forms)', 'sunistao', '7:896,1120', 'soon-is-tah\'-o,', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «2476» (including its collateral forms); to set together, i.e. (by implication) to introduce (favorably), or (figuratively) to exhibit; intransitively, to stand near, or (figuratively) to constitute:--approve, commend, consist, make, stand (with).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to place together, to set in the same place,to bring or band together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to stand with (or near)</OL><LI>to set one with another<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>by way of presenting or introducing him<LI>to comprehend</OL><LI>to put together by way of composition or combination, to teach by combining and comparing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to show, prove, establish, exhibit</OL><LI>to put together, unite parts into one whole<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be composed of, consist</OL></OL>'),
(4922, 'sunodeuvw', 'from (4862) and (3593)', 'sunodeuo', 'None', 'soon-od-yoo\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «3593»; to travel in company with:--journey with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to journey with, travel in company with</OL>'),
(4923, 'sunodiva', 'from a compound of (4862) and (3598) (\"synod\")', 'sunodia', 'None', 'soon-od-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a compound of «4862» and «3598» (\"synod\"); companionship on a journey, i.e. (by implication), a caravan:--company.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a journey in company<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a company of travellers, associates on a journey, a caravan</OL></OL>'),
(4924, 'suvnoida', 'from (4862) and (3611)', 'sunoikeo', 'None', 'soon-oy-keh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «3611»; to reside together (as a family):--dwell together.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to dwell together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the domestic association<LI>of intercourse of a husband and wife</OL></OL>'),
(4925, 'sunoikodomevw', 'from (4862) and (3618)', 'sunoikodomeo', '5:148,674', 'soon-oy-kod-om-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «3618»; to construct, i.e. (passively) to compose (in company with other Christians, figuratively):--build together.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to build together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to build together or with others<LI>to put together or construct by building, out of several things to build up one whole<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of the human body</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4926, 'sunomilevw', 'from (4862) and (3656)', 'sunomileo', 'None', 'soon-om-il-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «3656»; to converse mutually:--talk with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to talk with</OL>'),
