(4928, 'sunochv', 'from (4912)', 'sunoche', '7:886,1117', 'soon-okh-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «4912»; restraint, i.e. (figuratively) anxiety:--anguish, distress.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a holding together, a narrowing<LI>the contracting part of a way<LI>metaph. straits, distress, anguish</OL>'),
(4929, 'suntavssw', 'from (4862) and (5021)', 'suntasso', 'None', 'soon-tas-so', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «5021»; to arrange jointly, i.e. (figuratively) to direct:--appoint.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to put in order with or together, to arrange<LI>to (put together), constitute<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to prescribe, appoint</OL></OL>'),
(4930, 'suntevleia', 'from (4931)', 'sunteleia', '8:64,1161', 'soon-tel\'-i-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «4931»; entire completion, i.e. consummation (of a dispensation):--end.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>completion, consummation, end</OL>'),
(4931, 'suntelevw', 'from (4862) and (5055)', 'sunteleo', '8:62,1161', 'soon-tel-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «5055»; to complete entirely; generally, to execute (literally or figuratively):--end, finish, fulfil, make.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to end together or at the same time<LI>to end completely<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>bring to an end, finish, complete</OL><LI>to accomplish, bring to fulfilment<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to come to pass</OL><LI>to effect, make, (conclude)<LI>to finish<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to make an end of<LI>to bring to an end<LI>destroy</OL></OL>'),
(4932, 'suntevmnw', 'from (4862) and the base of (5114)', 'suntemno', 'None', 'soon-tem\'-no', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and the base of «5114»; to contract by cutting, i.e. (figuratively) do concisely (speedily):--(cut) short.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to cut in pieces<LI>to cut short<LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to dispatch briefly, execute or finish quickly<LI>to hasten<LI>a short word i.e. an expedited prophecy or decree</OL></OL>'),
(4933, 'sunthrevw', 'from (4862) and (5083)', 'suntereo', '8:151,1174', 'soon-tay-reh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «5083»; to keep closely together, i.e. (by implication) to conserve (from ruin); mentally, to remember (and obey):--keep, observe, preserve.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to preserve (a thing from perishing or being lost)<LI>to keep within one\'s self, keep in mind (a thing, lest it be forgotten)</OL>'),
(4934, 'suntivqhmi', 'middle voice from (4862) and (5087)', 'suntithemai', 'None', 'soon-tith\'-em-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «4862» and «5087»; to place jointly, i.e. (figuratively) to consent (bargain, stipulate), concur:--agree, assent, covenant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to put together with, to place together, to join together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to place in one\'s mind<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to resolve, determine<LI>to make an arrangement, to engage</OL><LI>to assent to, to agree to</OL></OL>'),
(4935, 'suntovmoß', 'from a derivative of (4932)', 'suntomos', 'None', 'soon-tom\'-oce', 'Adverb', 'adverb from a derivative of «4932»; concisely (briefly):--a few words.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>concisely, briefly, in a few words</OL>'),
(4936, 'suntrevcw', 'from (4862) and (5143) (including its alternate)', 'suntrecho', 'None', 'soon-trekh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and «5143» (including its alternate); to rush together (hastily assemble) or headlong (figuratively):--run (together, with).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to run together<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the gathering of a multitude</OL><LI>to run along with others<LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to rush with, to cast one\'s self, plunge</OL></OL>'),
(4937, 'suntrivbw', 'from (4862) and the base of (5147)', 'suntribo', '7:919,1124', 'soon-tree\'-bo', 'Verb', 'from «4862» and the base of «5147»; to crush completely, i.e. to shatter (literally or figuratively):--break (in pieces), broken to shivers (+ -hearted), bruise.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>break, to break in pieces, shiver<LI>to tread down<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to put Satan under foot and (as a conqueror) trample on him<LI>to break down, crush<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to tear one\'s body and shatter one\'s strength</OL></OL></OL>'),
(4938, 'suvntrimma', 'from (4937)', 'suntrimma', '7:919,1124', 'soon-trim\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «4937»; concussion or utter fracture (properly, concretely), i.e. complete ruin:--destruction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>that which is broken or shattered, a fracture<LI>calamity, ruin, destruction</OL>'),
(4939, 'suvntrofoß', 'from (4862) and (5162) (in a passive sense)', 'suntrophos', 'None', 'soon\'-trof-os', 'Adjective', 'from «4862» and «5162» (in a passive sense); a fellow-nursling, i.e. comrade:--brought up with.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>nourished with one<LI>brought up with one<LI>companion of one\'s childhood and youth</OL>'),
