(5117, 'tovpoß', 'apparently a primary word', 'topos', '8:187,1184', 'top\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently a primary word; a spot (general in space, but limited by occupancy; whereas «5561» is a large but participle locality), i.e. location (as a position, home, tract, etc.); figuratively, condition, opportunity; specially, a scabbard:--coast, licence, place, × plain, quarter, + rock, room, where.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>place, any portion or space marked off, as it were from surrounding space<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an inhabited place, as a city, village, district<LI>a place (passage) in a book</OL><LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the condition or station held by one in any company or assembly<LI>opportunity, power, occasion for acting</OL></OL>'),
