(5319, 'fanerovw', 'from (5318)', 'phaneroo', '9:3,1244', 'fan-er-o\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «5318»; to render apparent (literally or figuratively):--appear, manifestly declare, (make) manifest (forth), shew (self).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make manifest or visible or known what has been hidden or unknown, to manifest, whether by words, or deeds, or in any other way<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>make actual and visible, realised<LI>to make known by teaching<LI>to become manifest, be made known<LI>of a person<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>expose to view, make manifest, to show one\'s self, appear</OL><LI>to become known, to be plainly recognised, thoroughly understood<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>who and what one is</OL></OL></OL>'),
