(5356, 'fqorav', 'from (5351)', 'phthora', '9:93,1259', 'fthor-ah\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «5351»; decay, i.e. ruin (spontaneous or inflicted, literally or figuratively):--corruption, destroy, perish.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>corruption, destruction, perishing<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>that which is subject to corruption, what is perishable<LI>in the Christian sense, eternal misery in hell</OL><LI>in the NT, in an ethical sense, corruption i.e. moral decay</OL>'),
