(5475, 'calkovß', 'perhaps from (5465) through the idea of hollowing out as a vessel (this metal being chiefly used for that purpose)', 'chalkos', 'None', 'khal-kos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps from «5465» through the idea of hollowing out as a vessel (this metal being chiefly used for that purpose); copper (the substance, or some implement or coin made of it):--brass, money.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>brass<LI>what is made of brass, money, coins of brass (also of silver and gold)</OL>'),
(5476, 'camaiv', 'perhaps from the base of (5490) through the idea of a fissure in the soil', 'chamai', 'None', 'kham-ah\'-ee', 'Adverb', 'adverb perhaps from the base of «5490» through the idea of a fissure in the soil; earthward, i.e. prostrate:--on (to) the ground.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>on the ground, on the earth<LI>to the ground</OL>'),
(5477, 'Canaavn', 'of Hebrew origin (03667)', 'Chanaan', 'None', 'khan-ah-an\'', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin («03667»); Chanaan (i.e. Kenaan), the early name of Palestine:--Chanaan.', 'Canaan = \"lowland\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the land of Canaan<LI>in a narrower sense: the part of Palestine lying west of the Jordan<LI>in a wider sense: all of Palestine</OL>'),
(5478, 'Cananai\'oß', 'from (5477)', 'Chanaanaios', 'None', 'khan-ah-an-ah\'-yos', 'Adjective', 'from «5477»; a Chanaanoean (i.e. Kenaanite), or native of gentile Palestine:--of Canaan.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Canaanite, the name of the ancient inhabitants of Palestine before its conquest by the Israelites<LI>in Christ\'s time: a Phoenician</OL>'),
(5479, 'carav', 'from (5463)', 'chara', '9:359,1298', 'khar-ah\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «5463»; cheerfulness, i.e. calm delight:--gladness, × greatly, (X be exceeding) joy(-ful, -fully, -fulness, -ous).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>joy, gladness<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the joy received from you<LI>the cause or occasion of joy<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of persons who are one\'s joy</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5480, 'cavragma', 'from the same as (5482)', 'charagma', '9:416,1308', 'khar\'-ag-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from the same as «5482»; a scratch or etching, i.e. stamp (as a badge of servitude), or scupltured figure (statue):--graven, mark.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a stamp, an imprinted mark<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the mark stamped on the forehead or the right hand as the badge of the followers of the Antichrist<LI>the mark branded upon horses</OL><LI>thing carved, sculpture, graven work<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of idolatrous images</OL></OL>'),
(5481, 'carakthvr', 'from the same as (5482)', 'charakter', '9:418,1308', 'khar-ak-tare\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «5482»; a graver (the tool or the person), i.e. (by implication) engraving ((\"character\"), the figure stamped, i.e. an exact copy or (figuratively) representation):--express image.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the instrument used for engraving or carving<LI>the mark stamped upon that instrument or wrought out on it<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>a mark or figure burned in (Lev. 13:</OL><LI>or stamped on, an impression<OL TYPE=\"b\"><LI>the exact expression (the image) of any person or thing, marked likeness, precise reproduction in every respect, i.e facsimile</OL></OL>'),
(5482, 'cavrax', 'from charasso (to sharpen to a point, akin to (1125) through the idea of scratching)', 'charax', 'None', 'khar\'-ax', 'Noun Masculine', 'from charasso (to sharpen to a point; akin to «1125» through the idea of scratching); a stake, i.e. (by implication) a palisade or rampart (military mound for circumvallation in a siege):--trench.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a pale or stake, a palisade<LI>a palisade or rampart<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>pales between which earth, stones, trees, and timbers are heaped and packed together</OL></OL>'),
(5483, 'carivzomai', 'middle voice from (5485)', 'charizomai', '9:372,1298', 'khar-id\'-zom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «5485»; to grant as a favor, i.e. gratuitously, in kindness, pardon or rescue:--deliver, (frankly) forgive, (freely) give, grant.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to do something pleasant or agreeable (to one), to do a favour to, gratify<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to show one\'s self gracious, kind, benevolent<LI>to grant forgiveness, to pardon<LI>to give graciously, give freely, bestow<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to forgive<LI>graciously to restore one to another<LI>to preserve for one a person in peril</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5484, 'cavrin', 'accusative case of (5485) as preposition', 'charin', 'None', 'khar\'-in', 'Preposition', 'accusative case of «5485» as preposition; through favor of, i.e. on account of:--be-(for) cause of, for sake of, +...fore, × reproachfully.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>in favour of, for the pleasure of<LI>for, for the sake of<LI>on this account, for this cause</OL>'),
(5485, 'cavriß', 'from (5463)', 'charis', '9:372,1298', 'khar\'-ece', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «5463»; graciousness (as gratifying), of manner or act (abstract or concrete; literal, figurative or spiritual; especially the divine influence upon the heart, and its reflection in the life; including gratitude):--acceptable, benefit, favour, gift, grace(- ious), joy, liberality, pleasure, thank(-s, -worthy).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>grace<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>that which affords joy, pleasure, delight, sweetness, charm, loveliness: grace of speech</OL><LI>good will, loving-kindness, favour<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the merciful kindness by which God, exerting his holy influence upon souls, turns them to Christ, keeps, strengthens, increases them in Christian faith, knowledge, affection, and kindles them to the exercise of the Christian virtues</OL><LI>what is due to grace<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the spiritual condition of one governed by the power of divine grace<LI>the token or proof of grace, benefit<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a gift of grace<LI>benefit, bounty</OL></OL><LI>thanks, (for benefits, services, favours), recompense, reward</OL>'),
(5486, 'cavrisma', 'from (5483)', 'charisma', '9:402,1298', 'khar\'-is-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «5483»; a (divine) gratuity, i.e. deliverance (from danger or passion); (specially), a (spiritual) endowment, i.e. (subjectively) religious qualification, or (objectively) miraculous faculty:--(free) gift.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a favour with which one receives without any merit of his own<LI>the gift of divine grace<LI>the gift of faith, knowledge, holiness, virtue<LI>the economy of divine grace, by which the pardon of sin and eternal salvation is appointed to sinners in consideration of the merits of Christ laid hold of by faith<LI>grace or gifts denoting extraordinary powers, distinguishing certain Christians and enabling them to serve the church of Christ, the reception of which is due to the power of divine grace operating on their souls by the Holy Spirit</OL>'),
(5487, 'caritovw', 'from (5485)', 'charitoo', '9:372,1298', 'khar-ee-to\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «5485»; to grace, i.e. indue with special honor:--make accepted, be highly favoured.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to make graceful<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>charming, lovely, agreeable</OL><LI>to peruse with grace, compass with favour<LI>to honour with blessings</OL>'),
(5488, 'Carravn', 'of Hebrew origin (02771)', 'Charrhan', 'None', 'khar-hran\'', 'Noun Location', 'of Hebrew origin («02771»); Charrhan (i.e. Charan), a place in Mesopotamia:--Charran.', 'Haran = \"a mountaineer\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a city in Mesopotamia, of great antiquity and made famous by the defeat of Crassus</OL>'),
(5489, 'cavrthß', 'from the same as (5482)', 'chartes', 'None', 'khar\'-tace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «5482»; a sheet (\"chart\") of writing-material (as to be scribbled over):--paper.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>paper</OL>'),
(5490, 'cavsma', 'from a form of an obsolete prim chao (to \"gape\" or \"yawn\")', 'chasma', 'None', 'khas\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a form of an obsolete primary chao (to \"gape\" or \"yawn\"); a \"chasm\" or vacancy (impassable interval):--gulf.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a gaping opening, a chasm, a gulf</OL>'),
(5491, 'cei\'loß', 'from a form of the same as (5490)', 'cheilos', 'None', 'khi\'-los', 'Noun Neuter', 'from a form of the same as «5490»; a lip (as a pouring place); figuratively, a margin (of water):--lip, shore.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a lip, of the speaking mouth<LI>metaph. the sea shore</OL>'),
(5492, 'ceimavzw', 'from the same as (5494)', 'cheimazo', 'None', 'khi-mad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from the same as «5494»; to storm, i.e. (passively) to labor under a gale:--be tossed with tempest.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to afflict with a tempest, to toss about upon the waves</OL>'),
(5493, 'ceivmarroß', 'from the base of (5494) and (4482)', 'cheimarrhos', 'None', 'khi\'-mar-hros', 'Adjective', 'from the base of «5494» and «4482»; a storm-runlet, i.e. winter-torrent:--brook.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>flowing in winter, a torrent</OL>'),
(5494, 'ceimwvn', 'from a derivative of cheo (to pour, akin to the base of (5490) through the idea of a channel), meaning a storm (as pouring rain)', 'cheimon', 'None', 'khi-mone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a derivative of cheo (to pour; akin to the base of 5490 through the idea of a channel), meaning a storm (as pouring rain); by implication, the rainy season, i.e. winter:--tempest, foul weather, winter.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>winter<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>stormy or rainy weather, a tempest<LI>winter, the winter season</OL></OL>'),
(5495, 'ceivr', 'perhaps from the base of (5494) in the sense of its congener the base of (5490) (through the idea of hollowness for grasping)', 'cheir', '9:424,1309', 'khire', 'Noun Feminine', 'perhaps from the base of «5494» in the sense of its congener the base of «5490» (through the idea of hollowness for grasping); the hand (literally or figuratively (power); especially (by Hebraism) a means or instrument):--hand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>by the help or agency of any one, by means of any one<LI>fig. applied to God symbolising his might, activity, power<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in creating the universe<LI>in upholding and preserving (God is present protecting and aiding one)<LI>in punishing<LI>in determining and controlling the destinies of men</OL></OL>'),
(5496, 'ceiragwgevw', 'from (5497)', 'cheiragogeo', '9:435,1309', 'khi-rag-ogue-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «5497»; to be a hand-leader, i.e. to guide (a blind person):--lead by the hand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lead by the hand</OL>'),
(5497, 'ceiragwgovß', 'from (5495) and a reduplicated form of (71)', 'cheiragogos', '9:435,1309', 'khi-rag-o-gos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5495» and a reduplicated form of «71»; a hand-leader, i.e. personal conductor (of a blind person):--some to lead by the hand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>leading one by the hand</OL>'),
(5498, 'ceirovgrafon', 'from a compound of (5495) and (1125)', 'cheirographon', '9:435,1309', 'khi-rog\'-raf-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'neuter of a compound of «5495» and «1125»; something hand-written (\"chirograph\"), i.e. a manuscript (specially, a legal document or bond (figuratively)):--handwriting.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a handwriting, what one has written by his own hand<LI>a note of hand or writing in which one acknowledges that money has either been deposited with him or lent to him by another, to be returned at the appointed time</OL>'),
(5499, 'ceiropoivhtoß', 'from (5495) and a derivative of (4160)', 'cheiropoietos', '9:436,1309', 'khi-rop-oy\'-ay-tos', 'Adjective', 'from «5495» and a derivative of «4160»; manufactured, i.e. of human construction:--made by (make with) hands.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>made by the hands i.e the skill of men<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of temples<LI>of circumcision<LI>of idols</OL></OL>'),
(5500, 'ceirotonevw', 'from a comparative of (5495) and teino (to stretch)', 'cheirotoneo', '9:437,1309', 'khi-rot-on-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a comparative of «5495» and teino (to stretch); to be a hand-reacher or voter (by raising the hand), i.e. (generally) to select or appoint:--choose, ordain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to vote by stretching out the hand<LI>to create or appoint by vote: one to have charge of some office or duty<LI>to elect, create, appoint</OL>'),
(5501, 'ceivrwn', 'irregular comparative of (2556)', 'cheiron', 'None', 'khi\'-rone', 'Adjective', 'irregular comparative of «2556»; from an obsolete equivalent cheres (of uncertain derivation); more evil or aggravated (physically, mentally or morally):--sorer, worse.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>worse</OL>'),
(5502, 'Ceroubivn', 'plural of Hebrew origin (03742)', 'cheroubim', '9:438,1312', 'kher-oo-beem\'', 'Noun Neuter', 'plural of Hebrew origin («03742»); \"cherubim\" (i.e. cherubs or kerubim):--cherubims.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cherubim, two golden figures of living creatures with two wings; they were fastened to the lid of the ark of the covenant in the holy of holies (both at the sacred tabernacle and of Solomon\'s temple) in such a manner that their faces were turned towards each other and down towards the lid, which they overshadowed with their expanded wings. Between these figures God was regarded as having fixed his dwelling place.</OL>'),
(5503, 'chvra', 'feminine of a presumed derivative apparently from the base of (5490) through the idea of deficiency', 'chera', '9:440,1313', 'khay\'-rah', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of a presumed derivative apparently from the base of «5490» through the idea of deficiency; a widow (as lacking a husband), literally or figuratively:--widow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a widow<LI>metaph. a city stripped of its inhabitants and riches is represented under the figure of a widow</OL>'),
(5504, 'cqevß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'chthes', 'None', 'khthes', 'Adverb', 'of uncertain derivation; \"yesterday\"; by extension, in time past or hitherto:--yesterday.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>yesterday</OL>'),
(5505, 'ciliavß', 'from (5507)', 'chilias', '9:466,1316', 'khil-ee-as\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «5507»; one thousand (\"chiliad\"):--thousand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a thousand, the number one thousand</OL>'),
(5506, 'cilivarcoß', 'from (5507) and (757)', 'chiliarchos', 'None', 'khil-ee\'-ar-khos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5507» and «757»; the commander of a thousand soldiers (\"chiliarch\"; i.e. colonel:--(chief, high) captain.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chiliarch, the commander of a thousand soldiers<LI>the commander of a Roman cohort (a military tribunal)<LI>any military commander</OL>'),
(5507, 'civlioi', 'plural of uncertain affinity', 'chilioi', '9:466,1316', 'khil\'-ee-oy', 'Adjective', 'plural of uncertain affinity; a thousand:--thousand.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a thousand</OL>'),
(5508, 'Civoß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Chios', 'None', 'khee\'-os', 'Noun Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Chios, an island in the Mediterranean:--Chios.', 'Chios = \"snowy\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>is an island in the Aegean, between Samos and Lesbos, not far from the shore of Lydia</OL>'),
(5509, 'citwvn', 'of foreign origin (03801)', 'chiton', 'None', 'khee-tone\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of foreign origin («03801»); a tunic or shirt:--clothes, coat, garment.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a tunic, an undergarment, usually worn next to the skin, a garment, a vestment</OL>'),
(5510, 'ciwvn', 'perhaps akin to the base of (5490) ((5465)) or (5494) (as descending or empty)', 'chion', 'None', 'khee-one\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'perhaps akin to the base of «5490» («5465») or «5494» (as descending or empty); snow:--snow.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>snow</OL>'),
(5511, 'clamuvß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'chlamus', 'None', 'khlam-ooce\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain derivation; a military cloak:--robe.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a chalamys, an outer garment usually worn over the tunic<LI>a kind of short cloak worn by soldiers, military officers, magistrates, kings, emperors</OL>'),
(5512, 'cleuavzw', 'from a derivative probably of (5491)', 'chleuazo', 'None', 'khlyoo-ad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from a derivative probably of «5491»; to throw out the lip, i.e. jeer at:--mock.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to mock, deride, jeer</OL>'),
(5513, 'cliarovß', 'from chlio (to warm)', 'chliaros', '2:876,296', 'khlee-ar-os\'', 'Adjective', 'from chlio (to warm); tepid:--lukewarm.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>tepid, lukewarm<LI>metaph. of the condition of the soul wretchedly fluctuating between a torpor and a fervour of love</OL>'),
(5514, 'Clovh', 'from apparently a primary word, \"green\"', 'Chloe', 'None', 'khlo\'-ay', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of apparently a primary word; \"green\"; Chloe, a Christian female:--Chloe.', 'Chloe = \"a green herb\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a Christian woman of Corinth</OL>'),
(5515, 'clwrovß', 'from the same as (5514)', 'chloros', 'None', 'khlo-ros\'', 'Adjective', 'from the same as «5514»; greenish, i.e. verdant, dun-colored:--green, pale.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>green<LI>yellowish pale</OL>'),
(5516, 'cxßV', 'the (22)d, (14)th and an obsolete letter ((4742) as a cross) of the Greek alphabet (intermediate between the (5)th and (6)th), used as numbers', 'chi', 'None', 'stigma', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>six hundred and sixty six, the meaning of which is the basis of much vain speculation</OL>', 'the 22nd, 14th and an obsolete letter (4742 as a cross) of the Greek alphabet (intermediate between the 5th and 6th), used as numbers; denoting respectively 600, 60 and 6; 666 as a numeral:--six hundred threescore and six.', ''),
(5517, 'coi>kovß', 'from (5522)', 'choikos', '9:472,1318', 'kho-ik-os\'', 'Adjective', 'from «5522»; dusty or dirty (soil-like), i.e. (by implication) terrene:--earthy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>made of earth, earthy</OL>'),
(5518, 'coi\'nix', 'of uncertain derivation', 'choinix', 'None', 'khoy\'-nix', 'Noun Feminine', 'of uncertain derivation; a choenix or certain dry measure:--measure.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a choenix, a dry measure, containing four cotylae or two setarii (less than our quart, one litre) (or as much as would support a man of moderate appetite for a day)</OL>'),
(5519, 'coi\'roß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'choiros', 'None', 'khoy\'-ros', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; a hog:--swine.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a swine</OL>'),
(5520, 'colavw', 'from (5521)', 'cholao', 'None', 'khol-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «5521»; to be bilious, i.e. (by implication) irritable (enraged, \"choleric\"):--be angry.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be atrabilious<LI>to be mad<LI>to be angry, enraged</OL>'),
(5521, 'colhv', 'from an equivalent perhaps akin to the same as (5514) (from the greenish hue)', 'chole', 'None', 'khol-ay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of an equivalent perhaps akin to the same as 5514 (from the greenish hue); \"gall\" or bile, i.e. (by analogy) poison or an anodyne (wormwood, poppy, etc.):--gall.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>bile, gall<LI>in the OT used of other bitter things<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>wormwood<LI>possibly myrrh</OL></OL>'),
(5522, 'covoß', 'from the base of (5494)', 'choos', 'None', 'kho\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the base of «5494»; a heap (as poured out), i.e. rubbish; loose dirt:--dust.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>earth dug out, an earth heap<LI>dust</OL>'),
(5523, 'Corazivn', 'of uncertain derivation', 'Chorazin', 'None', 'khor-ad-zin\'', 'Noun Location', 'of uncertain derivation; Chorazin, a place in Palestine:--Chorazin.', 'Chorazin = \"a furnace of smoke\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a town in Galilee</OL>'),
(5524, 'corhgevw', 'from a compound of (5525) and (71)', 'choregeo', 'None', 'khor-ayg-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a compound of «5525» and «71»; to be a dance-leader, i.e. (generally) to furnish:--give, minister.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to be a chorus leader, lead a chorus<LI>to furnish the chorus at one\'s own expense<LI>to procure and supply all things necessary to fit out a chorus<LI>to supply, furnish abundantly</OL>'),
(5525, 'corovß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'choros', 'None', 'khor-os\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; a ring, i.e. round dance (\"choir\":--dancing.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a band (of dancers and singers), circular dance, a dance, dancing</OL>'),
(5526, 'cortavzw', 'from (5528)', 'chortazo', 'None', 'khor-tad\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «5528»; to fodder, i.e. (generally) to gorge (supply food in abundance):--feed, fill, satisfy.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to feed with herbs, grass, hay, to fill, satisfy with food, to fatten<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of animals</OL><LI>to fill or satisfy men<LI>to fulfil or satisfy the desire of any one</OL>'),
(5527, 'covrtasma', 'from (5526)', 'chortasma', 'None', 'khor\'-tas-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «5526»; forage, i.e. food:--sustenance.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>feed, fodder for animals<LI>food, (vegetable) sustenance, whether for men or flocks</OL>'),
(5528, 'covrtoß', 'apparently a primary word', 'chortos', 'None', 'khor\'-tos', 'Noun Masculine', 'apparently a primary word; a \"court\" or \"garden\", i.e. (by implication, of pasture) herbage or vegetation:--blade, grass, hay.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the place where grass grows and animals graze<LI>grass, herbage, hay, provender<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of green grass<LI>of growing crops</OL></OL>'),
(5529, 'Couza\'ß', 'of uncertain origin', 'Chouzas', 'None', 'khood-zas\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain origin; Chuzas, an officer of Herod:--Chuza.', 'Chuza = \"the seer\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the house steward of Herod Antipas</OL>'),
(5530, 'cravomai', 'middle voice of a primary verb (perhaps rather from (5495), to handle)', 'chraomai', 'None', 'khrah\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice of a primary verb (perhaps rather from «5495», to handle); to furnish what is needed; (give an oracle, \"graze\" (touch slightly), light upon, etc.), i.e. (by implication) to employ or (by extension) to act towards one in a given manner:--entreat, use. Compare «5531»; «5534».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to receive a loan<LI>borrow<LI>to take for one\'s use, to use<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to make use of a thing</OL></OL>'),
(5531, 'cravw', 'probably the same as the base of (5530)', 'chrao', 'None', 'khrah\'-o', 'Verb', 'probably the same as the base of «5530»; to loan:--lend.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lend</OL>'),
(5532, 'creiva', 'from the base of (5530) or (5534)', 'chreia', 'None', 'khri\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the base of «5530» or «5534»; employment, i.e. an affair; also (by implication) occasion, demand, requirement or destitution:--business, lack, necessary(-ity), need(-ful), use, want.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>necessity, need<LI>duty, business</OL>'),
(5533, 'creofeilevthß', 'from a derivative of (5531) and (3781)', 'chreopheiletes', 'None', 'khreh-o-fi-let\'-ace', 'Noun Masculine', 'from a derivative of «5531» and «3781»; a loan-ower, i.e. indebted person:--debtor.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a debtor</OL>'),
(5534, 'crhv', 'third person singular of the same as (5530) or (5531) used impersonally', 'chre', 'None', 'khray', 'Verb', 'third person singular of the same as «5530» or «5531» used impersonally; it needs (must or should) be:--ought.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>it is necessary<LI>it behooves</OL>'),
(5535, 'crh/vzw', 'from (5532)', 'chreizo', 'None', 'khrade\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «5532»; to make (i.e. have) necessity, i.e. be in want of:--(have) need.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to have need of, to be in want of</OL>'),
(5536, 'crh\'ma', 'a primitive word', 'chrema', '9:480,1319', 'khray\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'something useful or needed, i.e. wealth, price:--money, riches.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a thing, a matter, affair, event, business<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>spec. money, riches</OL></OL>');
INSERT INTO `greek_lexicon` (`number`, `orig_word`, `word_orig`, `translit`, `tdnt`, `phonetic`, `part_of_speech`, `st_def`, `IPD_def`) VALUES
(5537, 'crhmativzw', 'from (5536)', 'chrematizo', '9:480,1319', 'khray-mat-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «5536»; to utter an oracle (compare the original sense of «5530»), i.e. divinely intimate; by implication, (compare the secular sense of «5532») to constitute a firm for business, i.e. (generally) bear as a title:--be called, be admonished (warned) of God, reveal, speak.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to transact business, esp. to manage public affairs<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to advise or consult with one about public affairs<LI>to make answer to those who ask for advice, present enquiries or requests, etc.<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of judges, magistrates, rulers, kings</OL></OL><LI>to give a response to those consulting an oracle, to give a divine command or admonition, to teach from heaven<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to be divinely commanded, admonished, instructed<LI>to be the mouthpiece of divine revelations, to promulgate the commands of God</OL><LI>to assume or take to one\'s self a name from one\'s public business<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to receive a name or title, be called</OL></OL>'),
(5538, 'crhmatismovß', 'from (5537)', 'chrematismos', '9:482,1319', 'khray-mat-is-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5537»; a divine response or revelation:--answer of God.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a divine response, an oracle</OL>'),
(5539, 'crhvsimoß', 'from (5540)', 'chresimos', 'None', 'khray\'-see-mos', 'Adjective', 'from «5540»; serviceable:--profit.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fit for use, useful</OL>'),
(5540, 'crh\'siß', 'from (5530)', 'chresis', 'None', 'khray\'-sis', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «5530»; employment, i.e. (specially), sexual intercourse (as an occupation of the body):--use.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>use<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of the sexual use of a woman</OL></OL>'),
(5541, 'crhsteuvomai', 'middle voice from (5543)', 'chresteuomai', '9:491,1320', 'khraste-yoo\'-om-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice from «5543»; to show oneself useful, i.e. act benevolently:--be kind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to show one\'s self mild, to be kind, use kindness</OL>'),
(5542, 'crhstologiva', 'from a compound of (5543) and (3004)', 'chrestologia', '9:492,1320', 'khrase-tol-og-ee\'-ah', 'Noun Feminine', 'from a compound of «5543» and «3004»; fair speech, i.e. plausibility:--good words.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fair speaking, the smooth and plausible address which simulates goodness</OL>'),
(5543, 'crhstovß', 'from (5530)', 'chrestos', '9:483,1320', 'khrase-tos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «5530»; employed, i.e. (by implication) useful (in manner or morals):--better, easy, good(-ness), gracious, kind.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>fit, fit for use, useful<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>virtuous, good</OL><LI>manageable<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>mild, pleasant (as opp. to harsh, hard sharp, bitter)<LI>of things: more pleasant, of people, kind, benevolent</OL></OL>'),
(5544, 'crhstovthß', 'from (5543)', 'chrestotes', '9:489,1320', 'khray-stot\'-ace', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «5543»; usefulness, i.e. morally, excellence (in character or demeanor):--gentleness, good(-ness), kindness.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>moral goodness, integrity<LI>benignity, kindness</OL>'),
(5545, 'cri\'sma', 'from (5548)', 'chrisma', '9:493,1322', 'khris\'-mah', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «5548»; an unguent or smearing, i.e. (figuratively) the special endowment (\"chrism\") of the Holy Spirit:--anointing, unction.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>anything smeared on, unguent, ointment, usually prepared by the Hebrews from oil and aromatic herbs. Anointing was the inaugural ceremony for priests</OL>'),
(5546, 'Cristianovß', 'from (5547)', 'Christianos', '9:493,1322', 'khris-tee-an-os\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5547»; a Christian, i.e. follower of Christ:--Christian.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Christian, a follower of Christ</OL>'),
(5547, 'Cristovß', 'from (5548)', 'Christos', '9:493,1322', 'khris-tos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «5548»; anointed, i.e. the Messiah, an epithet of Jesus:--Christ.', 'Christ = \"anointed\"<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>Christ was the Messiah, the Son of God<LI>anointed</OL>'),
(5548, 'crivw', 'probably akin to (5530) through the idea of contact', 'chrio', '9:493,1322', 'khree\'-o', 'Verb', 'probably akin to «5530» through the idea of contact; to smear or rub with oil, i.e. (by implication) to consecrate to an office or religious service:--anoint.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to anoint<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>consecrating Jesus to the Messianic office, and furnishing him with the necessary powers for its administration<LI>enduing Christians with the gifts of the Holy Spirit</OL></OL>'),
(5549, 'cronivzw', 'from (5550)', 'chronizo', 'None', 'khron-id\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «5550»; to take time, i.e. linger:--delay, tarry.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to linger, delay, tarry</OL>'),
(5550, 'crovnoß', 'of uncertain derivation', 'chronos', '9:581,1337', 'khron\'-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'of uncertain derivation; a space of time (in general, and thus properly distinguished from «2540», which designates a fixed or special occasion; and from «165», which denotes a particular period) or interval; by extension, an individual opportunity; by implication, delay:--+ years old, season, space, (X often-)time(-s), (a) while.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>time either long or short</OL>'),
(5551, 'cronotribevw', 'from a presumed compound of (5550) and the base of (5147)', 'chronotribeo', 'None', 'khron-ot-rib-eh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from a presumed compound of «5550» and the base of «5147»; to be a time-wearer, i.e. to procrastinate (linger):--spend time.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to wear away time, spend time</OL>'),
(5552, 'crusou\'ß', 'from (5557)', 'chruseos', 'None', 'khroo\'-seh-os', 'Adjective', 'from «5557»; made of gold:--of gold, golden.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>golden<LI>made of gold<LI>overlaid or covered with gold</OL>'),
(5553, 'crusivon', 'diminutive of (5557)', 'chrusion', 'None', 'khroo-see\'-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'diminutive of «5557»; a golden article, i.e. gold plating, ornament, or coin:--gold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gold, both that which lies imbedded in the earth and is dug out of it<LI>that which has been smelted and wrought<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a gold coin<LI>of golden ornaments<LI>of precious things made of gold</OL></OL>'),
(5554, 'crusodaktuvlioß', 'from (5557) and (1146)', 'chrusodaktulios', 'None', 'khroo-sod-ak-too\'-lee-os', 'Adjective', 'from «5557» and «1146»; gold-ringed, i.e. wearing a golden finger-ring or similar jewelry:--with a gold ring.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>gold ringed, adorned with gold rings</OL>'),
(5555, 'crusovliqoß', 'from (5557) and (3037)', 'chrusolithos', 'None', 'khroo-sol\'-ee-thos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5557» and «3037»; gold-stone, i.e. a yellow gem (\"chrysolite\"):--chrysolite.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chrysolite is a precious stone of golden colour</OL>'),
(5556, 'crusovprasoß', 'from (5557) and prason (a leek)', 'chrusoprasos', 'None', 'khroo-sop\'-ras-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5557» and prason (a leek); a greenish-yellow gem (\"chrysoprase\"):--chrysoprase.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>chrysoprasus is a stone of green colour, inclined to that of gold, from whence it has its name; for this is agate in the breast plate, which was Naphtali\'s stone. (Gill)</OL>'),
(5557, 'crusovß', 'perhaps from the base of (5530) (through the idea of the utility of the metal), gold', 'chrusos', 'None', 'khroo-sos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'perhaps from the base of «5530» (through the idea of the utility of the metal); gold; by extension, a golden article, as an ornament or coin:--gold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>precious things made of gold, golden ornaments<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>an image made of gold<LI>stamped gold, gold coin</OL></OL>'),
(5558, 'crusovw', 'from (5557)', 'chrusoo', 'None', 'khroo-so\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «5557»; to gild, i.e. bespangle with golden ornaments:--deck.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to adorn with gold, to gild<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a woman ornamented with gold so profusely that she seems to be gilded</OL></OL>'),
(5559, 'crwvß', 'probably akin to the base of (5530) through the idea of handling', 'chros', 'None', 'khroce', 'Noun Masculine', 'probably akin to the base of «5530» through the idea of handling; the body (properly, its surface or skin):--body.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the surface of the body, the skin</OL>'),
(5560, 'cwlovß', 'apparently a primary word', 'cholos', 'None', 'kho-los\'', 'Adjective', 'apparently a primary word; \"halt\", i.e. limping:--cripple, halt, lame.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lame<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>deprived of a foot, maimed</OL></OL>'),
(5561, 'cwvra', 'from a derivative of the base of (5490) through the idea of empty expanse', 'chora', 'None', 'kho\'-rah', 'Noun Feminine', 'feminine of a derivative of the base of «5490» through the idea of empty expanse; room, i.e. a space of territory (more or less extensive; often including its inhabitants):--coast, county, fields, ground, land, region. Compare «5117».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the space lying between two places or limits<LI>a region or country i.e. a tract of land<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the (rural) region surrounding a city or village, the country<LI>the region with towns and villages which surround a metropolis</OL><LI>land which is ploughed or cultivated, ground</OL>'),
(5562, 'cwrevw', 'from (5561)', 'choreo', 'None', 'kho-reh\'-o', 'Verb', 'from «5561»; to be in (give) space, i.e. (intransitively) to pass, enter, or (transitively) to hold, admit (literally or figuratively):--come, contain, go, have place, (can, be room to) receive.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to leave space (which may be filled or occupied by another), to make room, give place, yield<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to retire<LI>metaph. to betake one\'s self, turn one\'s self</OL><LI>to go forward, advance, proceed, succeed<LI>to have space or room for receiving or holding something</OL>'),
(5563, 'cwrivzw', 'from (5561)', 'chorizo', 'None', 'kho-rid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «5561»; to place room between, i.e. part; reflexively, to go away:--depart, put asunder, separate.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to separate, divide, part, put asunder, to separate one\'s self from, to depart<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to leave a husband or wife<LI>of divorce<LI>to depart, go away</OL></OL>'),
(5564, 'cwrivon', 'diminutive of (5561)', 'chorion', 'None', 'kho-ree\'-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'diminutive of «5561»; a spot or plot of ground:--field, land, parcel of ground, place, possession.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a space, a place, a region, a district<LI>a piece of ground, a field, land</OL>'),
(5565, 'cwrivß', 'from (5561)', 'choris', 'None', 'kho-rece\'', 'Adverb', 'adverb from «5561»; at a space, i.e. separately or apart from (often as preposition):--beside, by itself, without.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>separate, apart<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>without any<LI>besides</OL></OL>'),
(5566, 'cw\'roß', 'of Latin origin', 'choros', 'None', 'kho\'-ros', 'Noun Masculine', 'of Latin origin; the north-west wind:--north west.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the northwest wind<LI>for the quarter of the heavens from which the wind blows</OL>'),
(5567, 'yavllw', 'probably strengthened from psao (to rub or touch the surface, cf (5597))', 'psallo', '8:489,1225', 'psal\'-lo', 'Verb', 'probably strengthened from psao (to rub or touch the surface; compare «5597»); to twitch or twang, i.e. to play on a stringed instrument (celebrate the divine worship with music and accompanying odes):--make melody, sing (psalms).', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to pluck off, pull out<LI>to cause to vibrate by touching, to twang<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>to touch or strike the chord, to twang the strings of a musical instrument so that they gently vibrate<LI>to play on a stringed instrument, to play, the harp, etc.<LI>to sing to the music of the harp<LI>in the NT to sing a hymn, to celebrate the praises of God in song</OL></OL>'),
(5568, 'yalmovß', 'from (5567)', 'psalmos', '8:489,1225', 'psal-mos\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5567»; a set piece of music, i.e. a sacred ode (accompanied with the voice, harp or other instrument; a \"psalm\"); collectively, the book of the Psalms:--psalm. Compare «5603».', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a striking, twanging<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of a striking the chords of a musical instrument<LI>of a pious song, a psalm</OL></OL>'),
(5569, 'yeudavdelfoß', 'from (5571) and (80)', 'pseudadelphos', '1:144,22', 'psyoo-dad\'-el-fos', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5571» and «80»; a spurious brother, i.e. pretended associate:--false brethren.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a false brother<LI>one who ostentatiously professes to be a Christian, but is destitute of Christian knowledge and piety</OL>'),
