(5571, 'yeudhvß', 'from (5574)', 'pseudes', '9:594,1339', 'psyoo-dace\'', 'Adjective', 'from «5574»; untrue, i.e. erroneous, deceitful, wicked:--false, liar.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>lying, deceitful, false</OL>'),
(5572, 'yeudodidavskaloß', 'from (5571) and (1320)', 'pseudodidaskalos', '2:160,161', 'psyoo-dod-id-as\'-kal-os', 'Noun Masculine', 'from «5571» and «1320»; a spurious teacher, i.e. propagator of erroneous Christian doctrine:--false teacher.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a false teacher</OL>'),
(5573, 'yeudolovgoß', 'from (5571) and (3004)', 'pseudologos', 'None', 'psyoo-dol-og\'-os', 'Adjective', 'from «5571» and «3004»; mendacious, i.e. promulgating erroneous Christian doctrine:--speaking lies.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>speaking (teaching) falsely, speaking lies</OL>'),
(5574, 'yeuvdomai', 'middle voice of an apparently primary verb', 'pseudomai', '9:594,1339', 'psyoo\'-dom-ahee', 'Verb', 'middle voice of an apparently primary verb; to utter an untruth or attempt to deceive by falsehood:--falsely, lie.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to lie, to speak deliberate falsehoods<LI>to deceive one by a lie, to lie to</OL>'),
