(5584, 'yhlafavw', 'from the base of (5567) (cf (5586))', 'pselaphao', 'None', 'psay-laf-ah\'-o', 'Verb', 'from the base of «5567» (compare «5586»); to manipulate, i.e. verify by contact; figuratively, to search for:--feel after, handle, touch.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to handle, touch and feel<LI>metaph. mentally to seek after tokens of a person or a thing</OL>'),
(5585, 'yhfivzw', 'from (5586)', 'psephizo', '9:604,1341', 'psay-fid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from «5586»; to use pebbles in enumeration, i.e. (generally) to compute:--count.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to count with pebbles, to compute, calculate, reckon<LI>to give one\'s vote by casting a pebble into the urn<LI>to decide by voting</OL>'),
(5586, 'yh\'foß', 'from the same as (5584)', 'psephos', '9:604,1341', 'psay\'-fos', 'Noun Feminine', 'from the same as «5584»; a pebble (as worn smooth by handling), i.e. (by implication, of use as a counter or ballot) a verdict (of acquittal) or ticket (of admission); a vote:--stone, voice.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a small worn smooth stone, a pebble<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>in the ancient courts of justice the accused were condemned by black pebbles and the acquitted by white</OL><LI>a vote (on account of the use of pebbles in voting)</OL>'),
(5587, 'yiqurismovß', 'from a derivative of psithos (a whisper', 'psithurismos', 'by implication, a slander, probably akin to 5574)', 'psith-oo-ris-mos\'', 'Masculine Neuter', 'from a derivative of psithos (a whisper; by implication, a slander; probably akin to «5574»); whispering, i.e. secret detraction:--whispering.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a whispering, i.e. secret slandering<LI>of the magical murmuring of a charmer of snakes</OL>'),
(5588, 'yiquristhvß', 'from the same as (5587)', 'psithuristes', 'None', 'psith-oo-ris-tace\'', 'Noun Masculine', 'from the same as «5587»; a secret calumniator:--whisperer.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a whisperer, secret slanderer, detractor</OL>'),
(5589, 'yicivon', 'diminutive from a derivative of the base of (5567) (meaning a crumb)', 'psichion', 'None', 'psikh-ee\'-on', 'Noun Neuter', 'diminutive from a derivative of the base of «5567» (meaning a crumb); a little bit or morsel:--crumb.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a little morsel, a crumb</OL>'),
(5590, 'yuchv', 'from (5594)', 'psuche', '9:608,1342', 'psoo-khay\'', 'Noun Feminine', 'from «5594»; breath, i.e. (by implication) spirit, abstractly or concretely (the animal sentient principle only; thus distinguished on the one hand from «4151», which is the rational and immortal soul; and on the other from «2222», which is mere vitality, even of plants: these terms thus exactly correspond respectively to the Hebrew «05315», «07307» and «02416»):--heart (+ -ily), life, mind, soul, + us, + you.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>breath<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the breath of life<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the vital force which animates the body and shows itself in breathing 1a</OL><LI>of animals 1a</OL><LI>of men<OL TYPE=\"b\"><LI>life<LI>that in which there is life<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>a living being, a living soul</OL></OL><LI>the soul<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>the seat of the feelings, desires, affections, aversions (our heart, soul etc.)<LI>the (human) soul in so far as it is constituted that by the right use of the aids offered it by God it can attain its highest end and secure eternal blessedness, the soul regarded as a moral being designed for everlasting life<LI>the soul as an essence which differs from the body and is not dissolved by death (distinguished from other parts of the body)</OL></OL>'),
(5591, 'yucikovß', 'from (5590)', 'psuchikos', '9:661,1342', 'psoo-khee-kos\'', 'Adjective', 'from «5590»; sensitive, i.e. animate (in distinction on the one hand from «4152», which is the higher or renovated nature; and on the other from «5446», which is the lower or bestial nature):--natural, sensual.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>of or belonging to breath<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>having the nature and characteristics of the breath<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the principal of animal life, which men have in common with the brutes</OL><LI>governed by breath<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>the sensuous nature with its subjection to appetite and passion</OL></OL></OL>'),
(5592, 'yuvcoß', 'from (5594)', 'psuchos', 'None', 'psoo\'-khos', 'Noun Neuter', 'from «5594»; coolness:--cold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cold</OL>'),
(5593, 'yucrovß', 'from (5592)', 'psuchros', '2:876,296', 'psoo-chros\'', 'Adjective', 'from «5592»; chilly (literally or figuratively):--cold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>cold, cool<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of cool water</OL><LI>metaph.<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>cold i.e. sluggish, inert<LI>in mind: of one destitute of warm Christian faith and the desire for holiness</OL></OL>'),
(5594, 'yuvcw', 'a primary verb', 'psucho', 'None', 'psoo\'-kho', 'Verb', 'a primary verb; to breathe (voluntarily but gently, thus differing on the one hand from «4154», which denotes properly a forcible respiration; and on the other from the base of «109», which refers properly to an inanimate breeze), i.e. (by implication, of reduction of temperature by  evaporation) to chill (figuratively):--wax cold.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to breathe, blow, cool by blowing<LI>to be made or grow cool or cold<LI>metaph. of waning love</OL>'),
(5595, 'ywmivzw', 'from the base of (5596)', 'psomizo', 'None', 'pso-mid\'-zo', 'Verb', 'from the base of «5596»; to supply with bits, i.e. (generally) to nourish:--(bestow to) feed.', '<OL TYPE=\"1\"><LI>to feed by putting a bit or crumb (of food) into the mouth<OL TYPE=\"a\"><LI>of infants, young animals etc.</OL><LI>to feed, nourish<LI>to give a thing to feed someone, feed out to</OL>'),
